te|FMI]] (record highs and lows 1961- present)<ref name=\"FMI open data\">{{cite web\n| url = http://suja.kapsi.fi/fmi-tilastot.php?taulukkomoodi=true\n| title = FMI open data\n| publisher = [[Finnish Meteorological Institute|FMI]]\n| accessdate = 7 September 2019}}</ref>\n[[Finnish Meteorological Institute|FMI]](record highs and lows 1921-1961)<ref name=\"Suomen Maakuntien ilmasto-Ilmatieteenlaitos\">[https://helda.helsinki.fi/bitstream/handle/10138/15734/2009nro8.pdf?sequence=1&isAllowed=y]</ref>\n|date=April2016\n}}\n</div>\n\n==Demographics==\n{| class=\"infobox\" style=\"float:center;\"\n! style=\"text-align:center;\" colspan=\"2\" | Significant foreign resident groups<ref>http://pxnet2.stat.fi/PXWeb/pxweb/fi/StatFin/StatFin__vrm__vaerak/statfin_vaerak_pxt_032.px/table/tableViewLayout2/?rxid=726cd24d-d0f1-416a-8eec-7ce9b82fd5a4</ref>\n|-\n! Nationality || Population (2018)\n|-\n|{{flag|Sweden}} || 1,899\n|-\n|{{flag|Russia}} || 1,221\n|-\n|{{flag|Iraq}} || 681\n|-\n|{{flag|China}} || 487\n|-\n|{{flag|Vietnam}} || 475\n|-\n|{{flag|Somalia}} || 424\n|-\n|{{flag|Thailand}} || 326\n|-\n|{{flag|Syria}} || 236\n|-\n|{{flag|India}} || 235\n|-\n|{{flag|Turkey}} || 222\n|-\n|}\n\nIn 2008, there were 316 [[Swedish language|Swedish]] speaking inhabitants, which was 0.2% of the total population, making the city unilingual. In 2007, there were 2,417 foreign citizens living in the city, of whom 618 were from elsewhere in the EU. 51.1% of the population is female.\n\n===Population===\n{{bar box\n|title   = The population growth of Oulu (and merged municipalities) 1980\u20132015\n|titlebar= #BD6\n|width   = 650px\n|barwidth= 600px\n|left1= Year\n|right1= Population\n|bars    =\n{{bar pixel|1980|#AAAAAA|315||121 809}}\n{{bar pixel|1985|#AAAAAA|334||128 869}}\n{{bar pixel|1990|#AAAAAA|352||136 029}}\n{{bar pixel|1995|#AAAAAA|379||146 395}}\n{{bar pixel|2000|#AAAAAA|416||160 851}}\n{{bar pixel|2005|#AAAAAA|449||173 436}}\n{{bar pixel|2010|#AAAAAA|480||185 419}}\n{{bar pixel|2015|#AAAAAA|498||196 956}}\n|caption = Source: ''Tilastokeskus''<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://pxweb2.stat.fi/Dialog/varval.asp?ma=060_vaerak_tau_107&ti=V%E4est%F6+kielen+mukaan+sek%E4+ulkomaan+kansalaisten+m%E4%E4r%E4+ja+maa%2Dpinta%2Dala+alueittain+1980+%2D+2012&path=../Database/StatFin/vrm/vaerak/&lang=3&multilang=fi | title=V\u00e4est\u00f6 kielen mukaan sek\u00e4 ulkomaan kansalaisten m\u00e4\u00e4r\u00e4 ja maa-pinta-ala alueittain 1980\u20132012 | date=22 April 2013 | publisher=Tilastokeskus | access-date=1 April 2013 | language=Finnish }}{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n}}\n\n==Culture==\n[[File:20120824- MG 8352.jpg|thumb|240px|[[Air Guitar World Championships]] 2012, an annual event held in Oulu since 1996]]\nThe best known cultural exports of the city of Oulu are the [[Air guitar|Air Guitar World Championships]] held annually in August, [[Mieskuoro Huutajat]] (also known as ''Screaming Men''), the now defunct metal band [[Sentenced]], and one of the best ice hockey teams in Europe, [[Oulun K\u00e4rp\u00e4t]].\n\nMany artists, writers, and musicians live in the city. A variety of concerts \u2014 rock, classical, and jazz \u2014 as well as other cultural events take place each year.  Examples include the [[Oulu Music Video Festival]], the [[Air Guitar World Championships]], and the [[Musixine]] Music Film Competition, all in August.  In July, the annual rock festival [[Qstock]] takes place. The Oulu Music Festival is held in winter and the Oulunsalo Music Festival in summer.  [[The Irish Festival of Oulu]] takes place each October, and the [[Oulu International Children's and Youth Film Festival|International Children's Film Festival]] each November.\n\nMuseums in Oulu include the [[Northern Ostrobothnia museum]], the [[Oulu Museum of Art]] (OMA), the [[Tietomaa]] [[Science museum#Science center|science center]], and the [[Turkansaari]] [[open-air museum]].\n\nNotable statues and sculptures in Oulu include a [[Frans Michael Franz\u00e9n (sculpture)|sculpture of Frans Michael Franz\u00e9n]] and ''[[Toripolliisi|The Bobby at the Market Place]]'' statue.\n\n[[Kalmah]] is a melodic death metal-band from Oulu that formed in 1998.\n\n==Sights==\n<center>\n<gallery heights=\"140px\" widths=\"200px\">\nFile:Oulu City Hall 2006 02 12.JPG|[[Oulu City Hall]].\nFile:Oulu Hydro Energy.jpg|[[Merikoski Power Plant|Merikoski hydroelectric dam]].\nFile:Tuira.jpg|View over the [[Oulujoki]] river towards the district of [[Tuira, Oulu]] from [[Hupisaaret Islands]] city park.\nFile:Kirkkokatu Oulu 20121206 01.JPG|[[Rotuaari]] pedestrian zone\nFile:2019-05-20 Oulu cathedral 1.jpg|[[Oulu Cathedral]]\nFile:Hotel Eden Oulu 2007 07 22.JPG|[[Spa Hotel Eden]] and sand beach in [[Nallikari]] recreation and tourism area.\nFile:Mannerheim Park Oulu 2006 07 23.JPG|[[Mannerheim Park]] is a favourite hangout place for many.\nFile:Oulu market hall 20051028.jpg|[[Oulu Market Hall]].\nFile:Oulu city art museum.jpg|[[Oulu Museum of Art]].\nFile:Tahtitorni Oulu 2006 04 02.JPG|The old observatory in Linnansaari. It was built in 1875 on top of the ruins of the [[Oulu Castle|Castle of Oulu]]. \nFile:Snowy Bicycles Oulu 20100227.JPG|Snowy bicycles in front of library of architecture of [[University of Oulu|Oulu University]].\nFile:Holy Family Nazareth Church Oulu 2006 02 12.JPG|The church of the [[Holy Family of Nazareth Church, Oulu|Holy Family of Nazareth Parish]] in Oulu, built by the [[Neocatechumenal Way]]. February 2006\n</gallery>\n</center>\n*[[Tietomaa]], a science center with over 150 exhibits\n*The Rapids Center, the area in the estuary of the Oulu river consisting of small islands connected with bridges and fountains in the middle of the river, and including a housing area of building blocks planned by [[Alvar Aalto]]\n*[[Market Square, Oulu|The Market Square]] with the [[Oulu City Library|City Library]], the [[Oulu City Theatre|City Theatre]] and old salt and tar storehouses\n* [[Hupisaaret Islands]], a large park area located in the estuary of the Oulu river\n*The F. M. Franzen memorial\n*The [[Koitelinkoski]] rapids\n*The [[Northern Ostrobothnia museum]]\n*The Pateniemi Sawmill Museum\n*The Vehicle Museum\n*The [[University of Oulu Botanical Gardens]] (situated in [[Linnanmaa]])\n*The Arctic Gallery\n*[[Technopolis (Finland)|Technopolis]], the technology village\n*[[Turkansaari]] (historical open-air museum)\n\n=== Churches ===\n* [[Oulu Cathedral|Cathedral]]\n* [[Haukipudas Church]]\n* [[Holy Family of Nazareth Church, Oulu|Holy Family of Nazareth Church]]\n* [[Holy Trinity Cathedral of Oulu]]\n* [[Kiiminki Church]]\n* [[Oulujoki Church]]\n* [[Oulunsalo Church]]\n* [[St. Luke's Chapel, Oulu|St. Luke's Chapel]]\n* [[Tuira Church]]\n* [[Ylikiiminki Church]]\n\n===Other points of interest===\n*[[Oulu Music Video Festival]]\n*[[The Annual Air Guitar World Championship contest|Air Guitar World Championships]]\n*[[Jalometalli Metal Music Festival]]\n*[http://www.irkku.fi The Irish Festival of Oulu]\n*[[Laitakari beacon tower]]\n*Madetoja Hall, housing the Oulu Music Centre ([http://www.ouka.fi/musiikki/english/index.html website]) the residence of the [[Oulu Symphony Orchestra]]\n*Oulu Hall (a large indoor sports facility consisting of a low dome, which looks somewhat like a landed [[flying saucer]])\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080218135811/http://www.oulumaraton.net/ Terwa Marathon & Run] event in late May (since 1989)\n*The Terva-skiing event in early March (since 1889)\n*The Winter Swimming World Championship {{citation needed|date=November 2014}}\n\n==Education==\n[[File:University-of-Oulu-2010.jpg|thumb|240px|[[University of Oulu]] main building.]]\nThe [[University of Oulu]] and [[Oulu University of Applied Sciences]] have their main campuses located in Oulu.\n\nOulu is home to the most northerly architecture school in the world. The school is best known for its strong regionalistic ideas for developing architecture. This movement is named \"the Oulu school\" (\"Oulun koulu\") of architecture. {{Citation needed|date=January 2010}}\n\nOulu Vocational College has over 13 000 students. It houses several different study subjects in different units which are spread over Oulu and neighbouring municipalities. Oulu Vocational College School of Business Studies is one of the few vocational schools which has game programming in its curriculum.\n\n[[Oulu International School]] is one of nine schools in Finland offering basic education in English.\n\n== Transport ==\nOulu is served by [[Oulu Airport]], the second largest airport in Finland by passenger volume. It is located {{convert|15|km|0}} south-west of the city centre.\n\nThe [[Port of Oulu]] is one of the busiest [[harbour]]s on the [[Bothnian Bay]]. It includes four separate harbour areas: Vihre\u00e4saari oil and bulk docks, Nuottasaari docks and Oritkari docks.\n\nThe shortest travel time from [[Oulu railway station]] to [[Helsinki Central railway station]] is 5 h 29 min, operated by [[VR Group|VR]]. Other destinations include [[Kolari]], [[Rovaniemi]], [[Sein\u00e4joki]] and [[Tampere]].\n\nThe most important road in Oulu is [[Finnish national road 4|Highway 4]] ([[European route E8|E8]]/[[European route E75|E75]]) that runs from Helsinki to [[Utsjoki]] via [[Lahti]], [[Jyv\u00e4skyl\u00e4]], Oulu, [[Kemi]] and [[Rovaniemi]]. Other [[Highways in Finland|highways]] running to and from Oulu are Highway 20 to [[Kuusamo]] and Highway 22 to [[Kajaani]].<ref name=\"autoilijan_tiekartta2007\">{{cite map |publisher= AffectoGenimap Finland Oy |title= Autoilijan Tiekartta 2007 \u2013 Road map |url= |edition= |year= 2006 |cartography= |scale= 1:800,000 |isbn= 978-951-593-047-7|id= }}</ref>\n\nOulu is notable for its transportation network dedicated to non-vehicular traffic, including pedestrians and bicycles (termed \"light\" traffic in Finland). In 2010, the city contained more than {{convert|600|km|mi}} of pathways and more than 100 underpasses and bridges devoted exclusively to light traffic. The network is used year-round. The ratio of light traffic pathways to residents is the highest in Finland and the cycling mode share is 20 percent.<ref>Jeffrey Pratte, \"[http://mspace.lib.umanitoba.ca/bitstream/1993/4752/1/Pratte_Jeffrey.pdf Mainstreaming Bicycling in Winter Cities: The case of Oulu, Finland]\", Masters thesis, University of Manitoba (Canada), 2011. P. 99-100</ref><ref>Anders Swanson, \"[http://vimeo.com/67039532 Winter Cycling for Everyone]\", (Video, 21:30 min.), Vimeo, 2013</ref> Oulu is often touted as an excellent city for bicycling.\n\nIn 2015, a large underground parking facility, Kivisyd\u00e4n (''Stone Heart''), opened in the city center directly beneath main shopping streets. The network of parallel roads for cars and pedestrians was drilled in the rock at the depth of 30 meters. The parking facility includes two ramps, 900 visitor parking lots (expandable to 1500), six access points to the ground served by 19 elevators (expandable to nine and 25), a service facility for commercial delivery vehicles, and [[Ubiquitous computing|ubi]]-screens that guide the driver to the selected ground access point and help locate the parked car by its license number.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oulunliikekeskus.fi/parking |title=Archived copy |access-date=2016-03-09 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310085459/http://www.oulunliikekeskus.fi/parking |archive-date=2016-03-10 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sito.fi/en/2014/08/kivisydan-parking-facility-in-oulu/|title=Kivisyd\u00e4n parking facility in Oulu|website=Oulunliikekeskus.fi|access-date=24 December 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160310073910/http://www.sito.fi/en/2014/08/kivisydan-parking-facility-in-oulu/|archive-date=2016-03-10|url-status=dead|df=}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|-\n| [[File:Oulu Bus Station 20161105.jpg|thumb|Oulu Bus Station]] || [[File:Isko Interchange Oulu 20150613.JPG|thumb|[[Finnish national road 4|Highway 4]] [[European route E75|E75]]]] || [[File:OH-LKE Embraer 190 0960-8.jpg|thumb|[[Finnair]] is one of the main operators of the [[Oulu airport]] with regular flights to [[Helsinki]]]] || [[File:Train in Oulu.JPG|thumb|[[VR Group]] operates railway traffic through the [[Oulu railway station]]]]\n|}\n\n== Solar power ==\nIn 2015, the [[Kaleva (newspaper)|Kaleva Media]] printing plant in [[Oulu]] became the most powerful photovoltaic solar plant in Finland, with 1,604 solar photovoltaic (PV) units on its roof. Although the city of Oulu, located near the [[Arctic Circle]], has only two hours of weak sunlight in December, the photovoltaic cells work almost around the clock in the summer. The cold climate means the PV panels can get up to a 25% boost per hour, as they don't overheat.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://insideclimatenews.org/news/22022020/solar-finland-nordic-renewables-sanna-marin-climate-targets-turku|title=Solar Power Just Miles from the Arctic Circle? In Icy Nordic Climes, It\u2019s Become the Norm|last=Hockenos|first=Paul|date=2020-02-24|website=InsideClimate News|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-26}}</ref>\n\nBecause the sun is quite low in the sky at this latitude, vertical PV installations are popular on the sides of buildings. These solar walls also capture light reflected from snow.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nSnow is not necessarily cleared from rooftop solar installations.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nThe local utility, Oulun Energia, is owned by the city of Oulu. The energy mix it receives from the Nordic-wide grid includes wood pellets, waste incineration, bioenergy, hydro-electric, geothermal, wind, nuclear, peat, natural gas and coal.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==Employment==\n[[File:Stora Enso Oulu 2006 01 26.JPG|thumb|right|[[Stora Enso]] has an important paper manufacturing plant in Oulu.]]\n[[File:Nokia Peltola Oulu 2006 04 14.JPG|thumb|right|[[Nokia]] premises in Peltola.]]\n[[File:Technopolis.jpg|thumb|right|Technopolis Linnanmaa is home to nearly 200 corporations.]]\nAs of 31 December 2008, the active working population was employed as follows:<ref name=\"oulu_business_and_industry\">{{cite web |url=http://www.oulu.ouka.fi/city/pdf/2011/tietoaoulusta_ENG_kevyt.pdf |title= Business and industry\n|accessdate=27 June 2012\n|date= 2012-01-01 |work= Information about Oulu |publisher=City of Oulu |location= Oulu}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#efefef;\" | Industries\n! style=\"background:#efefef;\" | Working population\n|-\n| Services || style=\"text-align: right;\" | 43,049\n|-\n| Industry || style=\"text-align: right;\" | 11,111\n|-\n| Commerce || style=\"text-align: right;\" | 10,848\n|-\n| Construction || style=\"text-align: right;\" |  5,449\n|-\n| Transport || style=\"text-align: right;\" | 3,698\n|-\n| Farming, forestry and mining || style=\"text-align: right;\" | 582\n|-\n| Unknown || style=\"text-align: right;\" | 431\n|-\n| Unemployment rate || style=\"text-align: right;\" | 16.3% (2016)\n|-\n! style=\"background:#efefef;\" | Total\n! style=\"background:#efefef; text-align: right;\" | 75,158\n|}\n\nIn 2011, the most important employers were:<ref name=\"oulu_business_and_industry\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:#efefef;\" | Employer\n! style=\"background:#efefef;\" | No. of employees\n|-\n| City of Oulu || style=\"text-align: right;\" | 9,709\n|-\n| [[Oulu University Hospital|Northern Ostrobothnia Hospital District]] || style=\"text-align: right;\" |  6,144\n|-\n| [[University of Oulu]] || style=\"text-align: right;\" |  3,045\n|-\n| [[Nokia Networks]] || style=\"text-align: right;\" |  2,100\n|-\n| [[Nokia|Nokia Group]] || style=\"text-align: right;\" |  2,000\n|-\n| The Oulu Region Joint Authority for Vocational Training || style=\"text-align: right;\" | 1,955\n|-\n| [[Kesko|Kesko Group]] || style=\"text-align: right;\" | 1,426\n|-\n| Cooperative Arina Group ([[S Group]]) || style=\"text-align: right;\" | 1,107\n|-\n| [[Stora Enso|Stora Enso Group]] || style=\"text-align: right;\" | 1,155\n|-\n| [[Itella|Itella Corporation]] || style=\"text-align: right;\" | 780\n|-\n| ISS Palvelut Oy|| style=\"text-align: right;\" | 730\n|-\n| ODL Group || style=\"text-align: right;\" | 653\n|}\n\n==Sports==\n[[File:K\u00e4rp\u00e4t kultaa 2005.jpg|thumb|right|[[K\u00e4rp\u00e4t]] wins the Finnish championship in 2005 after beating [[Jokerit]].]]\n[[File:Bandyliiga Final Oulu 20140315 04.JPG|220px|thumbnail|right|[[Oulun Luistinseura]] beat [[Jyv\u00e4skyl\u00e4n Seudun Palloseura]] in the 2014 Finland men's national bandy championship final.]]\n[[Ice hockey]] is the most popular spectator sport in Oulu. The local club [[K\u00e4rp\u00e4t]] has won the [[SM-liiga]] championship title eight times ([[1980\u201381 SM-liiga season|1981]], [[2003\u201304 SM-liiga season|2004]], [[2004\u201305 SM-liiga season|2005]], [[2006\u201307 SM-liiga season|2007]], [[2007\u201308 SM-liiga season|2008]], [[2013\u201314 SM-liiga season|2014]], [[2014\u201315 Liiga season|2015]] and [[2017\u201318 Liiga season|2018]]). It has also twice been the runner-up in the [[IIHF European Champions Cup]],   in [[2005 IIHF European Champions Cup|2005]] and in [[2006 IIHF European Champions Cup|2006]].\n\nIn [[Association football|football]] [[AC Oulu]] plays in [[Ykk\u00f6nen]], the second tier of the Finnish league system. So far [[Oulun Palloseura (football)|OPS]] has claimed the Finnish football championship only twice by winning [[Mestaruussarja]] in [[1979 Mestaruussarja|1979]] and in [[1980 Mestaruussarja|1980]]. Other notable football clubs include [[Oulun Luistinseura|OLS]], [[Oulun Ty\u00f6v\u00e4en Palloilijat|OTP]] and [[JS Hercules]].\n\nOulu has one well-known [[bandy]] club, [[Oulun Luistinseura|OLS]], which plays in [[Bandyliiga]] and has become [[list of Finnish bandy champions|Finnish champions]] 14 times, most recently in 2014. The other bandy club, [[Oulun Palloseura|OPS]], with its 7 championships and a bronze medal as late as in 2009, announced it would be closing down after the 2009-10 season. In [[2001 Bandy World Championship|2001]] the city was the main venue for the [[Bandy World Championship]].\n\nOulu is also home to several other sports clubs such as [[Oulu Northern Lights]] ([[American football]]), [[Oulun NMKY]] ([[Basketball]]), [[Oulun Lippo]] ([[Pes\u00e4pallo]]), [[Oulun Pyrint\u00f6]] ([[Track and field]]), [[OYUS Rugby|OYUS]] ([[Rugby union]]), [[Oulu Irish Elks]] ([[Gaelic football]]) and [[Lentopalloseura ETTA|ETTA]] ([[Volleyball]]).\n\n[[Oulun Tervahiihto]] is an annual ski marathon event held since 1889.\n\nTerwa Run & Marathon is an annual running event held since 1989 in late May.\n\n==Notable people from Oulu==\n* [[Saara Aalto]], singer, [[The X Factor (UK TV series)|X Factor UK]] finalist\n* [[Peter von Bagh]], film historian and director \n* [[Vladislav Delay]], electronic musician\n* [[Lars Gallenius]], 17th century painter\n* [[Matti Hautam\u00e4ki]], ski jumper\n* [[Aaro Hellaakoski]], poet\n* [[Veikko Antero Koskenniemi|V.A. Koskenniemi]], poet\n* [[Leevi Madetoja]], composer\n* [[Frans Michael Franz\u00e9n]], poet\n* [[Impaled Nazarene]], nuclear metal band\n* [[Iivo Niskanen]], Olympic champion cross-country skier\n* [[Kerttu Niskanen]], cross-country skier\n* [[Leena Peltonen-Palotie]], geneticist\n* [[Susanna P\u00f6yki\u00f6]], figure skater\n* [[Mika Ronkainen]], filmmaker\n* [[Keke Rosberg]], 1982 [[Formula One]] world champion\n* [[Kauko R\u00f6yhk\u00e4]], author and rock musician\n* [[Sara Wacklin]], teacher and writer\n* [[Mikael Toppelius]], church painter\n* Three former Presidents of the country, [[Kaarlo Juho St\u00e5hlberg]], [[Ky\u00f6sti Kallio]] and [[Martti Ahtisaari]], also a [[Nobel Peace Prize]] laureate\n* Ice Hockey players, [[Kari Jalonen]], [[Mikael Granlund]], [[Markus Granlund]], [[Joni Pitk\u00e4nen]], [[Reijo Ruotsalainen]],  [[Mika Py\u00f6r\u00e4l\u00e4]], [[Lasse Kukkonen]], [[Sebastian Aho (ice hockey, born 1997)|Sebastian Aho]]\n* Football players, [[Aki Lahtinen]], [[Seppo Pyykk\u00f6]], [[Antti Niemi (footballer)|Antti Niemi]] and [[Mika Nurmela]]\n\n==International relations==\n{{See also|List of twin towns and sister cities in Finland}}\n\n===Twin towns and sister cities===\nOulu is [[Twin towns and sister cities|twinned]] with:<ref name=\"Oulu Twin Cities\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ouka.fi/oulu/kansainvalisyys/ystavyyskaupungit|title = Yst\u00e4vyyskaupungit (Twin Cities)|accessdate = 2013-07-27|work = Oulun kaupunki (City of Oulu)|language = Finnish}}</ref>\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n*{{flagicon|NOR}} [[Alta, Norway]] <small>''(since 1948)''</small><ref name=\"Oulu Twin Cities\"/><ref name=\"Alta twinning\">{{cite web|url=http://www.alta.kommune.no/vennskapsbyer.530847-72060.html|title=Vennskapsbyer|publisher=Alta kommune|language=Norwegian}}</ref>\n*{{flagicon|RUS}} [[Arkhangelsk]], Russia <small>''(since 1993)''</small><ref name=\"Oulu Twin Cities\"/><ref name=\"Arkhangelsk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.arhcity.ru/?page=232/0 |script-title=ru:\u0418\u043d\u0444\u043e\u0440\u043c\u0430\u0446\u0438\u044f \u043e \u0433\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0434\u0430\u0445-\u043f\u043e\u0431\u0440\u0430\u0442\u0438\u043c\u0430\u0445|website=Arhcity.ru|date=October 26, 2007|accessdate=27 July 2013|language=Russian}}</ref>\n*{{flagicon|SWE}} [[Boden Municipality|Boden]], Sweden <small>''(since 1948)''</small><ref name=\"Oulu Twin Cities\"/>\n*{{flagicon|TUR}} [[Bursa]], Turkey <small>''(since 1978)''</small><ref name=\"Oulu Twin Cities\"/><ref name=\"Bursa twinnings\">{{cite web|url=http://www.bursa.bel.tr/kardes-sehirler/sayfa/261/|title=Karde\u015f \u015eehirler|accessdate = 2013-07-27|work=Bursa B\u00fcy\u00fck\u015fehir Belediyesi Bas\u0131n Koordinasyon Merkez|publisher=T\u00fcm Haklar\u0131 Sakl\u0131d\u0131r}}</ref>\n{{col-2}}\n*{{flagicon|GER}} [[Halle (Saale)|Halle]], Germany <small>''(since 1968)''</small><ref name=\"Oulu Twin Cities\"/>\n*{{flagicon|GER}} [[Leverkusen]], Germany <small>''(since 1968)''</small><ref name=\"Oulu Twin Cities\"/>\n*{{flagicon|UKR}} [[Odessa]], Ukraine <small>''(since 1957)''</small><ref name=\"Oulu Twin Cities\"/>\n*{{flagicon|HUN}} [[Si\u00f3fok]], Hungary <small>''(since 1978)''</small><ref name=\"Oulu Twin Cities\"/>\n*{{flagicon|KAZ}} [[Nur-Sultan]], Kazakhstan <small>''(since 2013)''</small><ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.tengrinews.kz/politics_sub/Astana-and-Finnish-Oulu-become-twin-cities-18692/|title=Astana and Finnish Oulu become twin-cities|website=Tengrinews.kz|accessdate=24 December 2017}}</ref>\n{{col-end}}\n\n===Partnership and twinning cities===\nIn addition Oulu has eight 'Partnership & Twinning cities':<ref name=\"Oulu Partnership and twinning cities\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ouka.fi/oulu/kansainvalisyys/partneri-ja-kummikaupungit|title=Partneri- ja kummikaupungit (Partnership and twinning cities)|accessdate=2013-07-27|work=Oulun kaupunki (City of Oulu)|language=Finnish}}</ref>\n{{col-start}}\n{{col-2}}\n*{{flagicon|SWE}} [[Lule\u00e5]], Sweden<ref name=\"Oulu Partnership and twinning cities\"/>\n*{{flagicon|UK}} [[Glasgow]], UK <ref name=\"Oulu Partnership and twinning cities\"/>\n*{{flagicon|GER}} [[Karlsruhe]], Germany<ref name=\"Oulu Partnership and twinning cities\"/>\n*{{flagicon|JPN}} [[Sendai]], Japan (since 2005)<ref name=\"Oulu Partnership and twinning cities\"/>\n{{col-2}}\n*{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Vienne]], France<ref name=\"Oulu Partnership and twinning cities\"/>\n*{{flagicon|SWE}} [[Ume\u00e5]], Sweden<ref name=\"Oulu Partnership and twinning cities\"/>\n*{{flagicon|NCA}} [[Matagalpa]], Nicaragua<ref name=\"Oulu Partnership and twinning cities\"/>\n*{{flagicon|TAN}} [[Ilembula]], Tanzania<ref name=\"Oulu Partnership and twinning cities\"/>\n{{col-end}}\n\n===International municipal projects===\nThe educational department was apart of the [[Lifelong Learning Programme 2007\u20132013 in Finland]].\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Laanila Highschool]]\n* [[Toppila Power Station]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons and category|Oulu}}\n*{{Official}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20170502221122/http://www.visitoulu.fi/en/home Visitoulu.fi] \u2013 VisitOulu.fi \u2013 Official tourism website of Oulu\n*{{Wikivoyage-inline}}\n\n{{NorthernOstrobothnia}}\n{{50 most populous Nordic urban settlements}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Oulu| ]]\n[[Category:Cities and towns in Finland]]\n[[Category:Grand Duchy of Finland]]\n[[Category:Port cities and towns of the Baltic Sea]]\n[[Category:1605 establishments in Sweden]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1605]]\n", "name_user": "Wokipedoa123", "label": "safe", "comment": "Added images to transport section of the article", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oulu"}
{"title_page": "Giuseppe Conte", "text_new": "{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{short description|58th Prime Minister of Italy}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Giuseppe Conte\n| image               = Giuseppe Conte Official.jpg\n| office              = 58th [[Prime Minister of Italy]]\n| president           = [[Sergio Mattarella]]\n| deputy              = [[Luigi Di Maio]] {{small|(2018\u201319)}}<br/>[[Matteo Salvini]] {{small|(2018\u201319)}}\n| term_start          = 1 June 2018\n| term_end            = \n| predecessor         = [[Paolo Gentiloni]]\n| successor           = \n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1964|8|8|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Volturara Appula]], [[Apulia]], Italy\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| party               = [[Independent politician|Independent]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.agi.it/politica/giuseppe_conte_rassegna_stampa-3931524/news/2018-05-22/ |title=Il premier tecnico di un governo politico\". Cosa dicono i giornali |publisher=AGI \u2013 Agenzia Giornalistica Italia |date=22 May 2018 |accessdate=1 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180913144204/https://www.agi.it/politica/giuseppe_conte_rassegna_stampa-3931524/news/2018-05-22/ |archive-date=13 September 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| spouse              = Valentina Fico ({{abbr|div.|divorced}})<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.today.it/donna/trend/giuseppe-conte-ex-moglie-chi-e-valentina.html |author=Donatella Polito |title=Valentina, chi \u00e8 l'ex moglie di Giuseppe Conte |trans-title=Valentina, who is the former wife of Giuseppe Conte |date=24 May 2018 |accessdate=1 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180712111930/http://www.today.it/donna/trend/giuseppe-conte-ex-moglie-chi-e-valentina.html |archive-date=12 July 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| partner             = Olivia Paladino<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/sfoglio/13343184/giuseppe-conte-olivia-paladino-giovane-fidanzata-bellissima-figlia-padrone-hotel-plaza.html |title=Giuseppe Conte, la sua fidanzata? Olivia Paladino: bellissima e biondissima, \u00e8 la figlia del proprietario dell'Hotel Plaza |trans-title=Who is Giuseppe Conte's girlfriend? Olivia Paladino: Beautiful and very blond, she is the daughter of the owner of the Hotel Plaza |work=[[Libero (newspaper)|Libero]] |date=25 May 2018 |accessdate=1 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224016/https://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/sfoglio/13343184/giuseppe-conte-olivia-paladino-giovane-fidanzata-bellissima-figlia-padrone-hotel-plaza.html |archive-date=1 April 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| children            = 1\n| residence           = [[Chigi Palace]]\n| education           = [[Sapienza University of Rome|Sapienza University]]\n| website             = {{url|governo.it/il-presidente|Official website}}\n| signature           = Giuseppe Conte signature 2.svg\n}}\n{{Giuseppe Conte sidebar}}\n\n'''Giuseppe Conte''' ({{IPA-it|d\u0292u\u02c8z\u025bppe \u02c8konte}}; born 8 August 1964) is an Italian [[jurist]] and [[politician]] who has served as the [[List of Prime Ministers of Italy|58th]] [[Prime Minister of Italy]] since June 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/31/ci-sono-tutte-le-condizioni-per-un-governo-m5s-lega_a_23448003/|title=Raggiunto l'accordo per un governo M5S-Lega con Conte premier|trans-title=Agreement is reached for an M5S-Lega government with premier Conte|language=it|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014829/https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/31/ci-sono-tutte-le-condizioni-per-un-governo-m5s-lega_a_23448003/|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nConte spent the majority of his career as a [[private law|law]] [[professor]] and was also a member of the Italian Bureau of Administrative Justice. Following the inconclusive [[Italian general election, 2018|2018 general election]], Conte was proposed as the potential independent leader of a coalition government between the [[Five Star Movement]] (M5S) and the [[Lega Nord|League]], despite his very low public profile nationally.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-44223034|title=Novice to lead Italian populist cabinet|date=23 May 2018|publisher=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401112700/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-44223034|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> After both parties agreed to a [[Conte I Cabinet|programme for government]], Conte was sworn in as Prime Minister on 1 June by [[President of Italy|President]] [[Sergio Mattarella]], immediately appointing the M5S and League leaders as his deputies.<ref>{{cite news |title=M5S and League agree contract for Italy's 'government of change' |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20180517/m5s-league-contract-italy-government-of-change |accessdate=5 September 2019 |work=thelocal.it |date=17 May 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190905092124/https://www.thelocal.it/20180517/m5s-league-contract-italy-government-of-change |archive-date=5 September 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-31/governo-contatti-maio-salvini-ipotesi-ciocca-all-economia-e-savona-esteri-083656.shtml?uuid=AEnWsmxE|title=Giuramento governo: alle 16 Conte e i ministri al Quirinale|work=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401070024/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-31/governo-contatti-maio-salvini-ipotesi-ciocca-all-economia-e-savona-esteri-083656.shtml?uuid=AEnWsmxE|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nHe became the first Italian Prime Minister without prior political office since [[Silvio Berlusconi]] in 1994, as well as the first from [[Southern Italy]] since [[Ciriaco De Mita]] in 1989.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tpi.it/2018/05/25/conte-premier-non-eletto/|title=Da Renzi a Conte: ecco chi sono i presidenti del Consiglio non-eletti in parlamento|author=Luca Serafini|date=25 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401070054/https://www.tpi.it/2018/05/25/conte-premier-non-eletto/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-23/l-incarico-torna-sud-roma-trent-anni-132910.shtml?uuid=AEToqGtE|title=Da De Mita a Conte, l'incarico torna a sud di Roma dopo trent'anni|work=Il Sole 24 Ore|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401070020/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-23/l-incarico-torna-sud-roma-trent-anni-132910.shtml?uuid=AEToqGtE|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The first Conte Cabinet was described by many publications, such as ''[[The New York Times]]'' and ''[[la Repubblica]]'', as the \"first modern populist government in [[Western Europe]]\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/politica/2018/05/11/italia-primo-regime-populista-europa-occidentale_ACfIrXYfVRuN9kbkERbm1L.html|title=Italia primo governo populista in Europa occidentale|agency=[[Adnkronos]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401043020/https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/politica/2018/05/11/italia-primo-regime-populista-europa-occidentale_ACfIrXYfVRuN9kbkERbm1L.html|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://eu.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2018/05/22/giuseppe-conte-italy-prime-minister/632744002/|author=Eric J. Lyman|title=Giuseppe Conte: Italy's next PM to form western Europe's first populist government|work=[[USA Today]]|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724043047/https://eu.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2018/05/22/giuseppe-conte-italy-prime-minister/632744002/|archive-date=24 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/24/opinion/populists-rome-five-star-movement.html|title=Opinion \u2013 The Populists Take Rome|date=24 May 2018|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|via=NYTimes.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401070043/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/24/opinion/populists-rome-five-star-movement.html|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 August 2019, Conte offered to resign as Prime Minister when the League filed a motion of no confidence in the coalition government.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Borrelli |first1=Silvia Sciorilli |title=Matteo Salvini calls confidence vote in Italian PM |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/italy-salvini-calls-confidence-vote-in-pm-conte/ |accessdate=5 September 2019 |work=POLITICO |date=9 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816182951/https://www.politico.eu/article/italy-salvini-calls-confidence-vote-in-pm-conte/ |archive-date=16 August 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=guardian_resignation /> Subsequently, the M5S and the centre-left [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] agreed to form a [[Conte II Cabinet|new government]], with Conte remaining as Prime Minister.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/notizia_3228466201902a.shtml|title=Consultazioni, Mattarella convoca Conte per gioved\u00ec mattina: il premier al Colle alle 09:30|website=Tgcom24|access-date=29 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828181939/https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/notizia_3228466201902a.shtml|archive-date=28 August 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> In the process, Conte became the first Italian Prime Minister to lead separate governments with both right-wing and left-wing coalition partners.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://formiche.net/2019/09/conte-sinistra-destra-presidentissimo-antonucci/|title=Da sinistra a destra, Conte fa (bene) il presidentissimo. Analisi di Antonucci|first=Maria Cristina|last=Antonucci|date=21 September 2019|website=Formiche.net|access-date=24 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191028052442/https://formiche.net/2019/09/conte-sinistra-destra-presidentissimo-antonucci/|archive-date=28 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iltempo.it/politica/2019/09/18/news/governo-giallorosso-conte-renzi-news-m5s-pd-mastella-trasformismo-1210557/|title=Conte? Campione di trasformismo|website=www.iltempo.it|access-date=24 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191024101345/https://www.iltempo.it/politica/2019/09/18/news/governo-giallorosso-conte-renzi-news-m5s-pd-mastella-trasformismo-1210557/|archive-date=24 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nConte has often been nicknamed \"the lawyer of the people\" (''l'avvocato del popolo''), as he also defined himself during his first speech as prime minister.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/un-anno-e-mezzo-conte-avvocato-popolo-garante-contratto-gialloverde-leader-ACBFGTg|title=Conte bis? I 15 mesi a palazzo Chigi dell' \"avvocato del popolo\" diventato leader politico|website=Il Sole 24 ORE|access-date=28 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828073111/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/un-anno-e-mezzo-conte-avvocato-popolo-garante-contratto-gialloverde-leader-ACBFGTg|archive-date=28 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/photogallery/primopiano/2019/08/20/giuseppe-conte-lavvocato-degli-italiani-_80d2deb1-d864-4c8b-a0bc-29a34a543218.html|title=Conte, l'avvocato del popolo strapazza il capitano - Primopiano|date=20 August 2019|website=ANSA.it|access-date=28 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825073909/http://www.ansa.it/sito/photogallery/primopiano/2019/08/20/giuseppe-conte-lavvocato-degli-italiani-_80d2deb1-d864-4c8b-a0bc-29a34a543218.html|archive-date=25 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and career==\nConte was born on 8 August 1964 into a [[middle class]] family at [[Volturara Appula]], near [[Foggia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-prof-anti-burocrazia-con-un-passato-a-sinistra_32a616ac-8e32-4b2f-8788-5e63912bbca3.html|title=Giuseppe Conte, legalit\u00e0 e semplificazione le sue parole d'ordine \u2013 Politica|date=20 May 2018|agency=[[Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401054423/http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-prof-anti-burocrazia-con-un-passato-a-sinistra_32a616ac-8e32-4b2f-8788-5e63912bbca3.html|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/puglia/notizie/2018/05/21/governo-conte-il-bambino-prodigio-legatissimo-a-volturara_03b14393-6ff3-451d-8ed7-8163ac6f0135.html|title=Governo: Conte, il 'bambino prodigio' legatissimo a Volturara \u2013 Puglia|date=21 May 2018|agency=Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233048/http://www.ansa.it/puglia/notizie/2018/05/21/governo-conte-il-bambino-prodigio-legatissimo-a-volturara_03b14393-6ff3-451d-8ed7-8163ac6f0135.html|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> His father Nicola was a public employee in the local [[municipality]], while his mother Lillina Roberti was an [[elementary school]] teacher.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_21/chi-giuseppe-conte-premier-che-viene-periferia-2d4fe228-5d18-11e8-9df6-a1f7c25f6df9_preview.shtml?reason=unauthenticated&cat=1&cid=Lalukfqy&pids=FR&origin=http://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_21/chi-giuseppe-conte-premier-che-viene-periferia-2d4fe228-5d18-11e8-9df6-a1f7c25f6df9.shtml|title=Chi \u00e8 Giuseppe Conte, il premier che \"viene dalla periferia\" \u2013 Video|author=Borrillo, Michelangelo|work=[[Corriere della Sera]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401070111/https://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_21/chi-giuseppe-conte-premier-che-viene-periferia-2d4fe228-5d18-11e8-9df6-a1f7c25f6df9_preview.shtml?reason=unauthenticated&cat=1&cid=Lalukfqy&pids=FR&origin=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.corriere.it%2Fpolitica%2F18_maggio_21%2Fchi-giuseppe-conte-premier-che-viene-periferia-2d4fe228-5d18-11e8-9df6-a1f7c25f6df9.shtml|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/21/studioso-e-riservato-e-molto-devoto-a-padre-pio-il-racconto-del-miglior-amico-del-premier-conte_a_23440002/|title=Studioso e riservato, e molto devoto a Padre Pio\". Il racconto del miglior amico del \"premier\" Conte|date=21 May 2018|work=[[HuffPost]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330221438/https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/21/studioso-e-riservato-e-molto-devoto-a-padre-pio-il-racconto-del-miglior-amico-del-premier-conte_a_23440002/|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAfter his family moved to [[San Giovanni Rotondo]], Conte attended the [[Liceo classico|Classical Lyceum]] \"[[Pietro Giannone]]\" near [[San Marco in Lamis]] and then studied law at the [[Sapienza University of Rome]], where he graduated in 1988 with honors.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://bari.repubblica.it/cronaca/2018/05/21/news/palazzo_chigi_a_volturara_e_a_san_giovanni_rotondo_fanno_il_tifo_per_il_nuovo_premier_conte-197020155/|title=Governo, a Volturara e a San Giovanni Rotondo nelle citt\u00e0 che fanno il tifo per Conte|date=21 May 2018|work=[[la Repubblica]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401043017/https://bari.repubblica.it/cronaca/2018/05/21/news/palazzo_chigi_a_volturara_e_a_san_giovanni_rotondo_fanno_il_tifo_per_il_nuovo_premier_conte-197020155/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=civilisti/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sanmarcoinlamis.org/sito/gargano/4137-il-candidato-alla-presidenza-del-governo-e-uno-di-noi-sul-gargano|title=Il candidato alla Presidenza del Governo \u00e8 uno di noi...|date=23 May 2018|website=SanMarcoinLamis.eu|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401043020/https://www.sanmarcoinlamis.org/sito/gargano/4137-il-candidato-alla-presidenza-del-governo-e-uno-di-noi-sul-gargano|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> For a short terms, Conte studied abroad. In 1992, he moved to the [[United States]] to study at [[Yale Law School]] and [[Duquesne University]] and at the [[Internationales Kulturinstitut|International Culture Institute]] in [[Vienna]] in 1993. He later researched or lectured at [[Sorbonne University]] in 2000, [[Girton College, Cambridge]] in 2001 and [[New York University]] in 2008.<ref name=cv>{{cite web|url=http://www.camera.it/application/xmanager/projects/leg17/file/ufficio_stampa/Tutti_i_Curricula.pdf|date=17 September 2013|title=Curricula dei candidati alle elezioni a componente del Consiglio di Presidenza della Giustizia Amministrativa|website=Camera dei deputati|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181208001035/http://www.camera.it/application/xmanager/projects/leg17/file/ufficio_stampa/Tutti_i_Curricula.pdf|archive-date=8 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-chi-e-il-favorito-per-la-premiership-nel-governo-m5s-lega_a_23439294/|title=Giuseppe Conte, avvocato civilista e \"sburocratizzatore\". Ecco chi \u00e8 il premier indicato da M5S e Lega a Mattarella|date=20 May 2018|work=HuffPost|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401093507/https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-chi-e-il-favorito-per-la-premiership-nel-governo-m5s-lega_a_23439294/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nHe started his academic career during the 1990s, when he taught at [[Roma Tre University]], at [[Libera Universit\u00e0 Maria SS. Assunta|LUMSA University]] in Rome, at the [[University of Malta]] and at the [[University of Sassari]].<ref name=\"civilisti\">{{cite web|url=https://www.civilistiitaliani.eu/soci/soci-effettivi/200-conte-giuseppe|title=Conte Giuseppe|author=Carlo Michele Cortellessa|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014929/https://www.civilistiitaliani.eu/soci/soci-effettivi/200-conte-giuseppe|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Conte is currently professor of [[private law]] at the [[University of Florence]] and at [[Libera Universit\u00e0 Internazionale degli Studi Sociali Guido Carli|LUISS]] of Rome.<ref>[https://www.unifi.it/p-doc2-2016-0-A-2b333b2d322c-1.html \"Giuseppe Conte\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180522070647/https://www.unifi.it/p-doc2-2016-0-A-2b333b2d322c-1.html |date=22 May 2018 }}.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://docenti.luiss.it/diritto-privato-conte/|title=Diritto Privato \u2013 LUISS Guido Carli|website=docenti.luiss.it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014838/http://docenti.luiss.it/diritto-privato-conte/|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> He sits on the [[board of trustees]] of [[John Cabot University]] in Rome.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.johncabot.edu/2018/05/jcu-trustee-giuseppe-conte-italian-prime-minister/|title=John Cabot Trustee Giuseppe Conte Named New Italian Prime Minister|date=24 May 2018|publisher=John Cabot University|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014649/https://news.johncabot.edu/2018/05/jcu-trustee-giuseppe-conte-italian-prime-minister/|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010 and 2011, Conte served on the [[board of directors]] of the [[Italian Space Agency]] (ASI) and in 2012 he was appointed by the [[Bank of Italy]] as a member of the \"Banking and Financial [[Arbitrage]]\" commission.<ref>[http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/giuseppe-conte/ Giuseppe Conte] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190919172354/http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/giuseppe-conte/ |date=19 September 2019 }}, Enciclopedia Treccani</ref> He served also in scientific committee of the Italian Foundation of [[Notaries]].<ref>[https://www.fondazionenotariato.it/progetti.html Progetti] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191001183935/http://www.fondazionenotariato.it/progetti.html |date=1 October 2019 }}, ''Fondazione Italiana del Notariato''</ref>\n\nOn 18 September 2013, he was elected by the [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]] as a member of the Bureau of Administrative Justice, the self-governing body of administrative magistrates, of which he served also as vice president.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.camera.it/leg17/1132?shadow_primapagina=3150|title=Eletti i componenti dei Consigli di presidenza della Giustizia amministrativa, della Corte dei conti, della Giustizia tributaria|website=Camera dei deputati|date=18 September 2013|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402051232/http://www.camera.it/leg17/1132?shadow_primapagina=3150|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Prime Minister of Italy==\n=== 2018 government formation===\n{{Main|2018 Italian government formation}}\n[[File:Sergio Mattarella and Giuseppe Conte.jpg|thumb|left|220px|Conte with [[President of the Italian Republic|President]] [[Sergio Mattarella]] at the [[Quirinal Palace]] ]]\nIn February 2018, Conte was selected by [[Luigi Di Maio]], leader of the [[Five Star Movement]] (M5S), as the future possible Minister of Public Administration in his cabinet following the [[2018 Italian general election|2018 general election]].<ref>{{cite news|work=[[Il Giornale]]|url=https://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/ecco-tutti-i-ministri-governo-movimento-5-stelle-1500068.html|title=Ecco tutti i \"ministri\" del governo del Movimento 5 Stelle|author=Chiara Sarra|date=1 March 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612235128/http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/ecco-tutti-i-ministri-governo-movimento-5-stelle-1500068.html|archive-date=12 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> However, the election resulted in a [[hung parliament]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/elezioni-2018/notizie/elezioni-2018-exit-poll-risultati-proiezioni-spoglio-eb21387e-1ff1-11e8-a09a-92b478235f6f.shtml|title=Elezioni 2018: M5S primo partito, nel centrodestra la Lega supera FI|author=Alessandro Sala|work=[[Corriere della Sera]]|date=4 March 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328131021/https://www.corriere.it/elezioni-2018/notizie/elezioni-2018-exit-poll-risultati-proiezioni-spoglio-eb21387e-1ff1-11e8-a09a-92b478235f6f.shtml|archive-date=28 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> with the M5S that became the party with the largest number of votes and of parliamentary seats while the [[centre-right coalition]], led by [[Matteo Salvini]]'s [[Lega Nord|League]] and other right-wing parties, emerged with a [[Plurality (voting)|plurality]] of seats in the Chamber of Deputies and in the Senate. The centre-left coalition led by former [[Prime Minister of Italy|Prime Minister]] [[Matteo Renzi]] came in third.<ref>{{cite news|author=Piera Matteucchi|url=https://www.repubblica.it/speciali/politica/elezioni2018/2018/03/04/news/risultati_elezioni_politiche_pd_centrodestra_m5s_fi_lega-190424815/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I0-C12-P1-S1.12-T1|title=Elezioni politiche: vincono M5s e Lega. Crollo del Partito democratico. Centrodestra prima coalizione. Il Carroccio sorpassa Forza Italia|work=la Repubblica|date=4 March 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014841/https://www.repubblica.it/speciali/politica/elezioni2018/2018/03/04/news/risultati_elezioni_politiche_pd_centrodestra_m5s_fi_lega-190424815/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I0-C12-P1-S1.12-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 May after weeks of political deadlock and the failure of various attempts of forming cabinets both between M5S\u2013[[Centre-right coalition|Centre-right]] and M5S\u2013[[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]], Di Maio and Salvini responded to President [[Sergio Mattarella]]'s ultimatum to appoint a neutral technocratic caretaker government by officially requesting that he allow them 24 more hours to achieve a governing agreement between their two parties.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mattarella postpones choice of caretaker premier amid new coalition govt talks|url=https://www.adnkronos.com/aki-en/politics/2018/05/09/mattarella-postpones-choice-caretaker-premier-amid-new-coalition-govt-talks_k6w71PMdtP04WhQ35gsF0I.html|agency=[[Adnkronos]]|date=9 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224018/https://www.adnkronos.com/aki-en/politics/2018/05/09/mattarella-postpones-choice-caretaker-premier-amid-new-coalition-govt-talks_k6w71PMdtP04WhQ35gsF0I.html|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ft.com/content/b253e5a4-53a0-11e8-b3ee-41e0209208ec|newspaper=Financial Times|accessdate=1 April 2019|date=9 May 2018|title=Italy's populist parties given 24 hours to avert fresh elections|url-access=subscription|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014725/https://www.ft.com/content/b253e5a4-53a0-11e8-b3ee-41e0209208ec|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that same day in the evening, [[Silvio Berlusconi]] publicly announced [[Forza Italia (2013)|Forza Italia]] would not support a M5S\u2013League government on a vote of confidence, but he would still maintain the centre-right alliance nonetheless, thus opening the doors to a possible majority government between the two parties.<ref>{{cite news|author=Paolo Gallori|author2=Monica Rubino|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/09/news/governo_salvini_ci_provero_fino_all_ultimo_-195890439/|newspaper=la Repubblica|publisher=GEDI Gruppo Editoriale|accessdate=1 April 2019|date=9 May 2018|title=Governo M5S-Lega, Berlusconi: nessun veto all'intesa ma no alla fiducia|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401225556/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/09/news/governo_salvini_ci_provero_fino_all_ultimo_-195890439/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 May, M5S and League reached an agreement in principle on a government program, likely clearing the way for the formation of a governing coalition between the two parties, but could not find an agreement regarding the members of a government cabinet, most importantly the Prime Minister. M5S and League leaders met with [[President of Italy|President]] [[Sergio Mattarella]] on 14 May to guide the formation of a new government.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marketwatch.com/story/italys-populist-5-star-league-parties-reach-deal-on-government-program-2018-05-13|author=Giovanni Legorano|website=MarketWatch|date=13 May 2018|title=Italy's populist 5 Star, League parties reach deal on government program|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014729/https://www.marketwatch.com/story/italys-populist-5-star-league-parties-reach-deal-on-government-program-2018-05-13|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On their meeting with President Mattarella, both parties asked for an additional week of negotiations to agree on a detailed government program and a Prime Minister to lead the joint government. Both M5S and the League announced their intention to ask their respective members to vote on the government agreement by the weekend.<ref name=\"rai\">{{cite news|url=http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Giuseppe-Conte-un-giurista-per-il-governo-del-cambiamento-LEga-M5S-DI-Maio-premier-un-amico-del-popolo-59393a99-ea98-40d0-91bf-f915e9d5127c.html|title=Giuseppe Conte, un giurista per governo del cambiamento. Di Maio: Premier sar\u00e0 un amico del popolo|date=21 May 2018|work=RAInews|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402003051/http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Giuseppe-Conte-un-giurista-per-il-governo-del-cambiamento-LEga-M5S-DI-Maio-premier-un-amico-del-popolo-59393a99-ea98-40d0-91bf-f915e9d5127c.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/21/news/consultazioni_mattarella_convoca_m5s_alle_17_30_e_lega_alle_18-196958844/?ref=RHPPLF-BL-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|title=M5s e Lega da Mattarella. Di Maio: \"Conte premier di governo politico\". Salvini: \"Interesse italiani al centro|trans-title=[[Five Star Movement|M5s]] & [[Sergio Mattarella|Mattarella]] of Lega, [[Luigi Di Maio|Di Maio]] said 'Conte will be prime minister of a political government|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|newspaper=la Repubblica|publisher=GEDI Gruppo Editoriale|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014756/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/21/news/consultazioni_mattarella_convoca_m5s_alle_17_30_e_lega_alle_18-196958844/?ref=RHPPLF-BL-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 May, Conte was proposed by Di Maio and Salvini for the role of Prime Minister in the [[2018 Italian government formation|2018 Italian government]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://formiche.net/2018/02/giuseppe-conte-scelto-luigi-maio-la-squadra-governo/|title=Chi \u00e8 Giuseppe Conte, scelto da Luigi Di Maio per la possibile squadra di governo|website=formiche.net|date=28 February 2018|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224020/https://formiche.net/2018/02/giuseppe-conte-scelto-luigi-maio-la-squadra-governo/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=bbc>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-44197351|publisher=BBC News|title=Italy populist government pact: Candidate for prime minister named|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402091842/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-44197351|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=21 May 2018|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/may/21/italy-populist-coalition-set-to-name-political-novice-as-pm-nominee|title=Italian president in talks as populist parties put forward novice for PM|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402002652/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/may/21/italy-populist-coalition-set-to-name-political-novice-as-pm-nominee|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> despite reports in the Italian press suggesting that President Mattarella still had significant reservations about the direction of the new government.<ref name=nyt>{{cite news|author=Horowitz, Jason|date=21 May 2018|title=Italy's Populists Offer Giuseppe Conte for Prime Minister; N.Y.U. Claim in Question|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/21/world/europe/italy-government-giuseppe-conte-di-maio.html|work=The New York Times|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233502/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/21/world/europe/italy-government-giuseppe-conte-di-maio.html|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 23 May, Conte was invited to the [[Quirinal Palace]] to receive the presidential mandate to form a new cabinet.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://apnews.com/eb60cc0ac97746b1aeb46be2121d9586|title=The Latest: Premier-designate confirms Italy's place in EU|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224015/https://apnews.com/eb60cc0ac97746b1aeb46be2121d9586|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/23/news/governo_conte_torna_in_bilico_tempi_piu_lunghi_mattarella_vuole_riflettere-197118162/?ref=RHPPLF-BL-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|author=Alberto Custodero|author2=Monica Rubino|title=Di Battista all'attacco di Mattarella: \"Non si opponga agli italiani\". La lunga giornata del Colle|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014825/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/23/news/governo_conte_torna_in_bilico_tempi_piu_lunghi_mattarella_vuole_riflettere-197118162/?ref=RHPPLF-BL-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In the traditional statement after the appointment, Conte said that he would be the \"defense lawyer of [[Italians|Italian people]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/governo-mattarella-conferisce-a-conte-l-incarico-saro-l-avvocato-difensore-degli-italiani-_3141680-201802a.shtml|title=Governo, Conte incaricato da Mattarella: \"Sar\u00f2 l'avvocato difensore degli italiani|language=it|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224018/https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/governo-mattarella-conferisce-a-conte-l-incarico-saro-l-avvocato-difensore-degli-italiani-_3141680-201802a.shtml|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte nel corso delle dichiarazioni in occasione del conferimento dell'incarico - 23 maggio 2018.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Conte during a press conference at the [[Quirinal Palace]], after receiving the task of forming a new cabinet]]\nOn 27 May, Conte renounced his office due to contrasts between Salvini and President Mattarella. Salvini proposed the university professor [[Paolo Savona]] as [[Italian Minister of Economy and Finances|Minister of Economy and Finances]], but Mattarella strongly opposed him, considering Savona too [[Eurosceptic]] and [[Anti-Germans (political current)|anti-German]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Tomasso Ciriaco|author2=Annalisa Cuzzocrea|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/27/news/governo_conte_mattarella_savona-197450521/|title=Governo, il giorno della rinuncia di Conte. Ecco come \u00e8 fallita la trattativa su Savona|date=27 May 2018|work=[[la Repubblica]]|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224015/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/27/news/governo_conte_mattarella_savona-197450521/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In his speech after Conte's resignation, Mattarella declared that the two parties wanted to bring Italy out of the [[Eurozone]] and as the guarantor of the Italian Constitution and the country's interest and stability he could not allow this.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/27/lora-piu-buia-di-mattarella-la-scelta-obbligata-di-difendere-linteresse-nazionale-dopo-il-no-dei-partiti-alla-soluzione-giorgetti-per-leconomia_a_23444708/|author=Alessandro De Angelis|title=L'ora pi\u00f9 buia di Mattarella: la scelta obbligata di difendere l'interesse nazionale dopo il no dei partiti alla soluzione Giorgetti per l'Economia|work=[[HuffPost]]|language=it|date=27 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014939/https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/27/lora-piu-buia-di-mattarella-la-scelta-obbligata-di-difendere-linteresse-nazionale-dopo-il-no-dei-partiti-alla-soluzione-giorgetti-per-leconomia_a_23444708/|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/27/news/governo_dopo_le_minacce_di_impeachment_sui_social_parte_la_solidarieta_a_mattarella-197516727/|author=Serena Riformato|title=Governo, firme e tweet di solidariet\u00e0 a Mattarella. Ma spuntano anche minacce di morte|date=27 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401225607/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/27/news/governo_dopo_le_minacce_di_impeachment_sui_social_parte_la_solidarieta_a_mattarella-197516727/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn the following day, Mattarella gave [[Carlo Cottarelli]], a former director of the [[International Monetary Fund]], the task of forming a new government.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/salvini_radio_capital_centrodestra-197543015/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I0-C12-P1-S1.12-T1|title=Cottarelli accetta l'incarico: \"Senza fiducia il Paese al voto dopo agosto|date=28 May 2018|work=[[la Repubblica]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014818/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/salvini_radio_capital_centrodestra-197543015/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I0-C12-P1-S1.12-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 28 May, the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] (PD) announced that it would abstain from voting the confidence to Cottarelli while the M5S and the center-right parties [[Forza Italia (2013)|Forza Italia]] (FI), [[Brothers of Italy]] (FdI) and the League announced their vote against.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/salvini_se_berlusconi_lo_vota_addio_alleanza_-197549039/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T2|title=Berlusconi: \"No alla fiducia e centrodestra unito al voto\". Ma Salvini: \"Alleanza con Fi? Ci penser\u00f2|date=28 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014848/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/salvini_se_berlusconi_lo_vota_addio_alleanza_-197549039/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T2|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/franceschini_pd_renzi_martina-197570543/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|title=Pd, Martina: \"Fiducia a Cottarelli\". Renzi: \"Salviamo il Paese\". E i dem: manifestazione nazionale a Roma il 1\u00b0 giugno|work=la Repubblica|date=28 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014853/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/franceschini_pd_renzi_martina-197570543/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nCottarelli was expected to submit his list of ministers for approval to President Mattarella on 29 May. On that and the following day, he held only informal consultations with the President, waiting for the formation of a \"political government\".<ref name=\":1\">{{cite news|url=https://roma.corriere.it/notizie/politica/18_maggio_30/governo-cottarelli-quirinale-mattarella-61982f12-63d6-11e8-9b4c-0d37dd8c9cfa.shtml|author=Giuseppe Gaetano|title=Incontro informale in corso tra Cottarelli e MattarellaI tre scenari possibili|work=[[Corriere della Sera]]|date=30 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190607164923/https://roma.corriere.it/notizie/politica/18_maggio_30/governo-cottarelli-quirinale-mattarella-61982f12-63d6-11e8-9b4c-0d37dd8c9cfa.shtml|archive-date=7 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/30/news/trattativa_m5s_lega_cottarelli_colle-197707709/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|author=Umberto Rosso|author2=Monica Rubino|title=Governo, Cottarelli vede Mattarella. Ora al lavoro alla Camera. Riparte la trattativa giallo-verde|date=30 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014857/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/30/news/trattativa_m5s_lega_cottarelli_colle-197707709/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Meanwhile, Salvini and Di Maio announced their willingness to restart the negotiations to form a political government and [[Giorgia Meloni]], leader of FdI, gave her support to the initiative.<ref name=\":1\"/><ref name=\":2\"/><ref>{{cite news|author=Alberto Custodero|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/29/news/di_maio_spero_voto_prima_possibile_ma_pronti_a_collaborare_con_mattarella_-197682177/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|title=Di Maio: \"Impeachment non-pi\u00f9 sul tavolo\". E si riapre l'ipotesi di un governo Lega-M5s|date=29 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014801/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/29/news/di_maio_spero_voto_prima_possibile_ma_pronti_a_collaborare_con_mattarella_-197682177/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 31 May, M5S and the League declared of having reached an agreement about forming a new government without Paolo Savona as Finance Minister (he would become Minister of European Affairs instead) and with Conte at its head.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/31/news/governo_m5s_lega-197794180/|author=Carmelo Lopapa|title=Governo, Conte accetta l'incarico e presenta la lista: 18 ministri, 5 le donne. Tria all'Economia|work=la Repubblica|language=it|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401225609/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/31/news/governo_m5s_lega-197794180/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Giuseppe-Conte-riceve-e-accetta-incarico-Presentata-a-Mattarella-la-lista-dei-ministri-1d8b9d38-c0c1-40c1-a6e9-44558da0fe1a.html|title=Nasce il governo Conte. Presentata a Mattarella la lista dei ministri. Di Maio e Salvini vicepremier|agency=[[RaiNews]]|language=it|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402044240/http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Giuseppe-Conte-riceve-e-accetta-incarico-Presentata-a-Mattarella-la-lista-dei-ministri-1d8b9d38-c0c1-40c1-a6e9-44558da0fe1a.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===First Conte Cabinet===\n{{See also|Conte I Cabinet}}\n[[File:Cerimonia di insediamento del Governo Conte 2018.jpg|thumb|Conte with [[Paolo Gentiloni]] during the swearing-in ceremony]]\nOn 1 June 2018, Conte officially succeeded the Democrat [[Paolo Gentiloni]] at the head of the Italian government and was sworn in as the new prime minister in the afternoon.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lastampa.it/2018/05/31/italia/lannuncio-del-quirinale-conte-ha-accettato-lincarico-domani-giuramento-alle-0bBgKEhl0wxOO9g9bpTK1L/pagina.html|title=L'annuncio del Quirinale: \"Conte accetta l'incarico, domani si giura alle 16|work=[[La Stampa]]|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224019/https://www.lastampa.it/2018/05/31/italia/lannuncio-del-quirinale-conte-ha-accettato-lincarico-domani-giuramento-alle-0bBgKEhl0wxOO9g9bpTK1L/pagina.html|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> His cabinet was predominantly composed of members of the M5S and the League but also of prominent independent [[technocrat]]s like the [[Italian Minister of Foreign Affairs|Minister of Foreign Affairs]] [[Enzo Moavero Milanesi]], who previously served as the minister of European affairs in the government of [[Mario Monti]], the university professor [[Giovanni Tria]] as the [[Italian Minister of Economy and Finances|minister of economy and finances]] and economist [[Paolo Savona]], who served in the cabinet of [[Carlo Azeglio Ciampi]] in the 1990s and is currently known for his [[Eurosceptic]] views, who became the new minister of European affairs.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/31/news/governo_conte_premier_tria_all_economia_milnesi_agli_esteri_savona_alle_politiche_comunitarie-197852722/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P2-S1.8-T1|title=Nasce il governo Conte, Di Maio e Salvini vice. Ecco i ministri dell'esecutivo M5s-Lega|author=Alberto Custodero|date=31 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014836/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/31/news/governo_conte_premier_tria_all_economia_milnesi_agli_esteri_savona_alle_politiche_comunitarie-197852722/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P2-S1.8-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-31/totoministri-ecco-nuova-squadra-governo-conte-195902.shtml?uuid=AEOyqIyE|author=Nicoletta Cottone|title=Nuovi ministri: la lista completa dell'esecutivo Lega-M5S|work=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014700/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-31/totoministri-ecco-nuova-squadra-governo-conte-195902.shtml?uuid=AEOyqIyE|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBoth parties' leaders Salvini and Di Maio were appointed [[Deputy Prime Minister of Italy|Deputy Prime Ministers]]. While the first became [[Italian Minister of the Interior|Minister of the Interior]], with the main aim of drastically reducing the [[Immigration to Italy|number of illegal immigrants]], the latter served as [[Italian Minister of Economic Development|Minister of Economic Development]], [[Italian Minister of Labour and Social Policies|Labour and Social Policies]] to introduce the [[universal basic income]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/31/governo-conte-ecco-chi-sono-veramente-ministri-dai-politici-come-di-maio-salvini-bonafede-agli-istituzionali-come-moavero-poi-il-prof-di-educazione-fisica-e-il-generale/4381994/|title=Governo Conte, chi sono i ministri: da Di Maio e Salvini (con i fedelissimi) agli \"istituzionali\" come Moavero. Poi il prof di educazione fisica e il generale che indag\u00f2 su Terra dei Fuochi \u2013 Il Fatto Quotidiano|author=M. Castigliani|author2=D. Pretini|work=[[Il Fatto Quotidiano]]|language=it|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lastampa.it/2018/06/01/italia/nasce-il-governo-legams-salvini-e-di-maio-vice-che-pesano-pi-del-premier-iWRvm6d4yZDNTGt1UQwpOO/pagina.html|title=Nasce il governo Lega-M5S: Salvini e Di Maio vice che pesano pi\u00f9 del premier|work=La Stampa|language=it|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224017/https://www.lastampa.it/2018/06/01/italia/nasce-il-governo-legams-salvini-e-di-maio-vice-che-pesano-pi-del-premier-iWRvm6d4yZDNTGt1UQwpOO/pagina.html|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe coalition of the two populist parties which Conte led was also known as [[Government of Change]],<ref>{{cite news|author=Luca Romano|date=23 May 2018|url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/premier-incaricato-conte-governo-cambiamento-1531213.html|title=Il premier incaricato Conte: \"Governo del cambiamento\"|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233337/http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/premier-incaricato-conte-governo-cambiamento-1531213.html|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> thanks to a document that summarized the electoral programmes of the two parties, which was called \"Contract for the Government of Change\".<ref>{{cite news|language=it|url=http://espresso.repubblica.it/palazzo/2018/05/18/news/contratto-di-governo-lega-m5s-ecco-il-testo-definitivo-1.322214|title=Contratto di governo Lega-M5s: ecco il testo|work=[[L'espresso]]|publisher=la Repubblica|date=18 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233345/http://espresso.repubblica.it/palazzo/2018/05/18/news/contratto-di-governo-lega-m5s-ecco-il-testo-definitivo-1.322214|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rt.com/news/427573-italy-pm-euroskeptic-coalition/|title='Government of change': Euroskeptic coalition's choice for Italian PM officially approved|agency=[[RT (TV network)|RT]]|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233402/https://www.rt.com/news/427573-italy-pm-euroskeptic-coalition/|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte @ the EP (33199171148).jpg|thumb|left|Conte speaks to the [[European Parliament]] in February 2019]]\nDuring his speech before the investiture vote in the [[Italian Senate]] on 5 June, Conte announced his willingness to reduce [[illegal immigration]] and increase the contrast to human traffickers and smugglers. He also advocated a fight against [[political corruption]], the introduction of a law which regulates the [[conflict of interest]]s, a new bill which expands the [[right of self-defense]], a [[tax]]es reduction and a drastic cut to politics's costs, thanks to the [[Annuity|annuities]]' abolition.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/05/news/conte_discorso_fiducia_senato-198193413/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|author=Monica Rubino|title=Conte, il discorso della fiducia: \"Basta business dei migranti, daspo per corrotti e corruttori\". E apre alla Russia|language=it|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014816/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/05/news/conte_discorso_fiducia_senato-198193413/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-06-05/conte-via-discorso-programmatico-quale-conte-chiedera-fiducia--114755.shtml?uuid=AE51Te0E|author=Andrea Gagliardi|author2=Vittorio Nuti|title=Il Governo Conte ottiene la prima fiducia con 171 \"s\u00ec\". Salvini: \"No aumento Iva\"|work=Il Sole 24 Ore|language=it|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014655/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-06-05/conte-via-discorso-programmatico-quale-conte-chiedera-fiducia--114755.shtml?uuid=AE51Te0E|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>[http://www.governo.it/sites/governo.it/files/5giugno2018_Comunicazioni_Conte_Senato.pdf \"Comunicazioni del Presidente del Consiglio dei ministri. Senato della Repubblica \u2013 seduta del 5 giugno 2018. Resoconto stenografico\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612135955/http://www.governo.it/sites/governo.it/files/5giugno2018_Comunicazioni_Conte_Senato.pdf |date=12 June 2018 }} (PDF). Full text of his speech.</ref> Conte also proposed to lift off the [[International sanctions during the Ukrainian crisis|international sanctions]] against [[Russia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/italy-prime-minister-giuseppe-conte-russia-sanctions-end-populist-five-star-vladimir-putin-crimea-a8385626.html|author=Jon Stone|title=Italy breaks with European allies and voices support for Russia after populist party takes power|work=[[The Independent]]|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402021830/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/italy-prime-minister-giuseppe-conte-russia-sanctions-end-populist-five-star-vladimir-putin-crimea-a8385626.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe Senate approved the [[confidence vote]] with 171 votes in favor and 117 against, with 25 abstentions.<ref>{{cite news|work=[[National Post]]|url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/news-pmn/the-latest-tunisia-calls-italy-diplomat-over-salvini-remark|title=The Latest: Italy's populist govt wins 1st confidence vote|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> The cabinet was supported by M5S, Lega, two senators from [[Associative Movement Italians Abroad]] (MAIE) and two independents while the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] (PD), [[Forza Italia (2013)|Forza Italia]] (FI), [[Free and Equal (Italy)|Free and Equal]] (LeU) and other small leftist parties voted against it. The far-right [[Brothers of Italy]] (FdI) and other ten independent senators abstained.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-06-05/conte-via-discorso-programmatico-quale-conte-chiedera-fiducia--114755.shtml?uuid=AE51Te0E|title=Governo, 171 s\u00ec per la fiducia, Conte: euro non-in discussione. Salvini: no aumento Iva|work=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]|language=it|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014655/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-06-05/conte-via-discorso-programmatico-quale-conte-chiedera-fiducia--114755.shtml?uuid=AE51Te0E|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On the following day, he received 350 votes in favor out of 630 in the [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]], 236 votes against and 35 abstained.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/06/news/governo_conte_fiducia_camera-198287520/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|title=Camera, approvata la fiducia. Conte: \"Tratteremo con l'Ue sul nostro debito\". Delrio (Pd): \"Studi la Carta, non-sia un pupazzo|author=Alberto Custadero|work=[[la Repubblica]]|language=it|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014844/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/06/news/governo_conte_fiducia_camera-198287520/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> As in the Senate, PD, FI and LeU voted against the government while FdI abstained. Besides M5S and League, Conte received two votes from independent deputies and one vote from [[Vittorio Sgarbi]], a notable and controversial member of Forza Italia who has always heavily criticised the M5S, but decided to support the cabinet in respect of Salvini and with the hope that a M5S government could lead toward their failure.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/06/news/governo_conte_il_si_di_sgarbi_penso_malissimo_di_di_maio_ma_salvini_realizzera_il_programma_di_centrodestra_-198315097/|author=Concetto Vecchio|title=Governo, lo strappo di Sgarbi: \"Penso malissimo di Di Maio. Ma voto s\u00ec: Salvini realizzer\u00e0 il programma di centrodestra|work=la Repubblica|language=it|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224014/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/06/news/governo_conte_il_si_di_sgarbi_penso_malissimo_di_di_maio_ma_salvini_realizzera_il_programma_di_centrodestra_-198315097/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/06/06/governo-sgarbi-show-alla-camera-dove-ce-il-disordine-io-prospero-votero-la-fiducia-per-assistere-al-vostro-declino/4409507/|title=Governo, Sgarbi show alla Camera: \"Dove c'\u00e8 il disordine io prospero. Voter\u00f2 la fiducia per assistere al vostro decline|work=[[Il Fatto Quotidiano]]|language=it|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014712/https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/06/06/governo-sgarbi-show-alla-camera-dove-ce-il-disordine-io-prospero-votero-la-fiducia-per-assistere-al-vostro-declino/4409507/|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 February 2019, Conte became acting [[Italian Minister of European Affairs|Minister of European Affairs]] after the resignation of [[Paolo Savona]], who was elected President of the [[Commissione Nazionale per le Societ\u00e0 e la Borsa|Companies and Exchange Commission]] (CONSOB).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2019/02/05/news/la_lega_accordo_con_i_5stelle_savona_va_alla_consob-218335939/|title=Savona alla Consob, interim del ministero a Conte|trans-title=Savona joins CONSOB as an interim minister in Conte's cabinet|date=5 February 2019|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331004639/https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2019/02/05/news/la_lega_accordo_con_i_5stelle_savona_va_alla_consob-218335939/|archive-date=31 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://blendle.com/i/the-economist/wish-upon-five-stars/bnl-economist-20190208-bf5819cfa8c|title=Wish upon Five Stars|date=9 February 2019|work=[[The Economist]]|issue=9129|volume=430|page=28|access-date=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224016/https://blendle.com/i/the-economist/wish-upon-five-stars/bnl-economist-20190208-bf5819cfa8c|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> He held the ''ad interim'' office until 10 July 2019, when he appointed [[Lorenzo Fontana]]\u00a0as new minister.<ref>[https://www.ilpost.it/2019/07/10/conte-fontana-ministro/ Lorenzo Fontana sar\u00e0 il nuovo ministro degli Affari Europei], ''Il Post''</ref>\n\n===Resignation and reappointment===\n{{main|2019 Italian government crisis|Conte II Cabinet}}\n[[File:Sergio Mattarella and Giuseppe Conte 2019.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Conte announcing his resignation to President Mattarella]]\nIn August 2019, Deputy Prime Minister Salvini announced a motion of no confidence against Conte, after growing tensions within the majority.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Salvini-Subito-in-Aula-poi-le-elezioni-Conte-Dovra-spiegare-le-ragioni-della-crisi-648408f5-df6c-49f8-bf6d-a73532bd60ab.html|title=La Lega presenta al Senato una mozione di sfiducia a Conte. M5S attacca Salvini: \"Giullare\"|website=rainews|access-date=20 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190820183327/http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Salvini-Subito-in-Aula-poi-le-elezioni-Conte-Dovra-spiegare-le-ragioni-della-crisi-648408f5-df6c-49f8-bf6d-a73532bd60ab.html|archive-date=20 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Many political analysts believe the no confidence motion was an attempt to force early elections to improve Lega's standing in Parliament, ensuring Salvini could become the next Prime Minister.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/08/09/italys-league-files-no-confidence-motion-prime-minister-inbid/|title=Italy's League files no confidence motion in prime minister in bid to trigger election|first=Nick|last=Squires|date=9 August 2019|via=www.telegraph.co.uk|newspaper=The Telegraph|access-date=20 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190826042808/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/08/09/italys-league-files-no-confidence-motion-prime-minister-inbid/|archive-date=26 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 20 August, following the parliamentary debate at the Senate, in which Conte accused Salvini of being a political opportunist who \"had triggered the political crisis only to serve his personal interest\" and stated \"this government ends here\",<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=[[Financial Times]]|first=Ben|last=Hall|url=https://www.ft.com/content/2119e302-c32c-11e9-a8e9-296ca66511c9|date=20 August 2019|title=Conte resignation shows stakes are high in Italy's political crisis|access-date=28 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190821214903/https://www.ft.com/content/2119e302-c32c-11e9-a8e9-296ca66511c9|archive-date=21 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=guardian_resignation>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/20/italian-pm-expected-resign-giuseppe-conte|title=Italian PM resigns with attack on 'opportunist' Salvini|first=Angela|last=Giuffrida|date=20 August 2019|via=www.theguardian.com|newspaper=The Guardian|access-date=20 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190827235332/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/20/italian-pm-expected-resign-giuseppe-conte|archive-date=27 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> the Prime Minister resigned his post to [[Sergio Mattarella|President Mattarella]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/20/world/europe/italy-pm-giuseppe-conte-resign.html|title=Italy's Government Collapses, Turning Chaos into Crisis|first=Jason|last=Horowitz|date=20 August 2019|newspaper=The New York Times|access-date=20 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190826121315/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/20/world/europe/italy-pm-giuseppe-conte-resign.html|archive-date=26 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nHowever, during the round of the so-called consultations between Mattarella and the parliamentary groups, a possible new majority emerged, between the Five Star Movement and the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/topnews/2019/08/19/grasso-possibile-intesa-m5s-pd-leu_301fb033-f640-4d0f-bba3-ea37eb594c9b.html|title=Grasso, possibile intesa M5s-Pd-Leu - Ultima Ora|date=19 August 2019|website=Agenzia ANSA|access-date=28 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190819161904/http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/topnews/2019/08/19/grasso-possibile-intesa-m5s-pd-leu_301fb033-f640-4d0f-bba3-ea37eb594c9b.html|archive-date=19 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 28 August, PD's leader [[Nicola Zingaretti]] announced at the [[Quirinal Palace]] his favorable position on keeping Giuseppe Conte at the head of the new government,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/conte-wins-crucial-support-for-new-italian-govt-coalition/2019/08/28/a85203c4-c99c-11e9-9615-8f1a32962e04_story.html|title=Conte wins crucial support for new Italian govt coalition|website=Washington Post|access-date=28 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828200930/https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/conte-wins-crucial-support-for-new-italian-govt-coalition/2019/08/28/a85203c4-c99c-11e9-9615-8f1a32962e04_story.html|archive-date=28 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and on same day, Mattarella summoned Conte to the Quirinal Palace for 29 August to give him the task of forming a new cabinet.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agi.it/politica/governo_pd_m5s_consultazioni-6094223/news/2019-08-28/|title=C'\u00e8 l'accordo tra M5s e Pd. Governo giallorosso ai nastri di partenza|website=Agi|access-date=28 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828182811/https://www.agi.it/politica/governo_pd_m5s_consultazioni-6094223/news/2019-08-28/|archive-date=28 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 4 September, Conte announced the ministers of his new cabinet, which was sworn in at the Quirinal Palace on the following day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/05/news/governo_conte_accetta_l_incarico_oggi_il_giuramento_della_squadra_al_quirinale-235221666/|title=Governo, Conte e i ministri hanno giurato. Gentiloni in pole per successione a Moscovici|date=5 September 2019|website=Repubblica.it|access-date=5 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190905090044/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/05/news/governo_conte_accetta_l_incarico_oggi_il_giuramento_della_squadra_al_quirinale-235221666/|archive-date=5 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 9 September 2019 the Chamber of Deputies granted the confidence to the government with 343 votes in favour, 263 against and 3 abstentions.<ref>{{cite news |title=La Camera vota la fiducia con 343 s\u00ec, il premier replica alla Camera fra le proteste. Alzata anche una sedia |url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/09/news/governo_conte_fiducia_camera-235548089/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I235485988-C12-P1-S1.12-T1 |accessdate=9 September 2019 |work=Repubblica.it |date=9 September 2019 |language=it |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190910053844/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/09/news/governo_conte_fiducia_camera-235548089/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I235485988-C12-P1-S1.12-T1 |archive-date=10 September 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Resoconto stenografico dell'Assemblea Seduta n. 222 di luned\u00ec 9 settembre 2019 |url=https://www.camera.it/leg18/410?idSeduta=0222&tipo=stenografico#sed0222.stenografico.tit00070.sub00030 |website=camera.it |publisher=Camera dei Deputati |accessdate=10 September 2019}}</ref> On 10 September 2019, in the second vote of confidence in the Senate, 169 lawmakers voted in favour of his government and 133 against.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://thepublicsradio.org/article/italys-new-pro-europe-govt-wins-2nd-confidence-vote|title=Italy's new pro-EU govt wins vote, now faces 2020 budget|accessdate=10 September 2019|website=The Public's Radio|date=10 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191016205409/https://thepublicsradio.org/article/italys-new-pro-europe-govt-wins-2nd-confidence-vote|archive-date=16 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 September, after few days from the investiture vote, in an interview to ''[[la Repubblica]]'', former Prime Minister [[Matteo Renzi]] announced his intention to leave the PD, launching a new centrist and liberal party named [[Italia Viva]] (IV).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rep.repubblica.it/pwa/intervista/2019/09/16/news/pd_renzi_scissione-236190189/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I236210677-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|title=Renzi lascia il Pd: \"Uscire dal partito sar\u00e0 un bene per tutti. Anche per Conte\"|website=rep.repubblica.it}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/politica/19_settembre_17/renzi-il-nome-nuova-sfida-che-stiamo-lanciare-sara-italia-viva-8dbc9da4-d963-11e9-8812-2a1c8aa813a3.shtml|title=Renzi: \"Il nome della nuova sfida che stiamo per lanciare sar\u00e0 Italia viva\"|first=Redazione|last=Politica|date=17 September 2019|website=Corriere della Sera|access-date=2 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190924150038/https://www.corriere.it/politica/19_settembre_17/renzi-il-nome-nuova-sfida-che-stiamo-lanciare-sara-italia-viva-8dbc9da4-d963-11e9-8812-2a1c8aa813a3.shtml|archive-date=24 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In the interview he confirmed also the support to Conte's government.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/16/news/renzi_telefona_a_conte_e_annuncia_l_addio_al_pd-236192204/|title=Matteo Renzi lascia il Pd e fonda nuovo partito: telefona a Conte e annuncia l'addio al Pd, Le ragioni della svolta in una intervista a Repubblica|date=16 September 2019|website=Repubblica.it|access-date=2 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191002182626/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/16/news/renzi_telefona_a_conte_e_annuncia_l_addio_al_pd-236192204/|archive-date=2 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Two ministers and one undersecretary followed Renzi in his new movement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.avvenire.it/attualita/pagine/il-partito-di-renzi-italia-viva|title=L'iniziativa. Renzi saluta il Pd e lancia \"Italia viva\". \"Siamo 40 in Parlamento\"|date=17 September 2019|website=www.avvenire.it|access-date=2 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191002203847/https://www.avvenire.it/attualita/pagine/il-partito-di-renzi-italia-viva|archive-date=2 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019 the Minister of Education, University and Research [[Lorenzo Fioramonti]] resigned after disagreements with the rest of the cabinet regarding the recently approved 2020 budget bill. Fioramonti considered the share of funds dedicated to education and research to be insufficient.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jones |first1=Gavin |title=Italy education minister resigns over lack of funds for ministry |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-politics-minister-resignation/italy-education-minister-resigns-over-lack-of-funds-for-ministry-idUSKBN1YT0Q4 |accessdate=26 December 2019 |work=Reuters |date=25 December 2019 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191225225032/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-politics-minister-resignation/italy-education-minister-resigns-over-lack-of-funds-for-ministry-idUSKBN1YT0Q4 |archive-date=25 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Conte took the ministerial role ''ad interim'', and announced his decision to split the Ministry of Education, University and Research into two: a [[Italian Minister of Public Education|Ministry of Public Education]] led by former undersecretary [[Lucia Azzolina]] (M5S), and a [[Italian Minister of University and Research|Ministry of University and Research]] led by the dean of the [[University of Naples Federico II]] [[Gaetano Manfredi]] (Independent), who were sworn in on 10 January.<ref>{{cite news |title=Conte:: \"Separare la Scuola dall'Universit\u00e0. Azzolina ministro dell'Istruzione e Manfredi della Ricerca\" |url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/12/28/news/conte_prescrizione_governo_conferenza_stampa_fine_anno-244526130/ |accessdate=28 December 2019 |work=Repubblica.it |date=28 December 2019 |language=it |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191228120724/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/12/28/news/conte_prescrizione_governo_conferenza_stampa_fine_anno-244526130/ |archive-date=28 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2020/01/10/governo-giurano-azzolina-e-manfredi-e-diventano-ministri-_c59c8837-8569-4324-95da-025f184a9f82.html |title=Governo: Giurano Azzolina e Manfredi e diventano ministri |access-date=12 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112104102/http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2020/01/10/governo-giurano-azzolina-e-manfredi-e-diventano-ministri-_c59c8837-8569-4324-95da-025f184a9f82.html |archive-date=12 January 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Policies==\n===Economic policies===\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte Centro Italia 1.jpg|thumb|Conte among people affected by the [[August 2016 Central Italy earthquake|2016 Central Italy earthquakes]]]]\nOne of Conte's main proposals was the scheduled reform of the [[Taxation in Italy|Italian tax system]], mainly promoted by the League and characterized by the introduction of [[flat tax]]es for businesses and individuals, with a no-tax area for low-income households and some small corrections to keep some degree of [[Progressive tax|tax progression]] as required by the [[Constitution of Italy|Italian Constitution]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://economia.ilmessaggero.it/economia_e_finanza/flat_tax_cos_e_detrazioni_simulatore-3782544.html|title=Flat tax, cos'\u00e8 e come funziona: due aliquote al 15 e 20%, premiati i redditi pi\u00f9 alti|trans-title=Flat tax, what it is and how it works: Two rates at 15 and 20%, higher incomes awarded|work=[[Il Messaggero]]|language=it|date=7 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612181034/https://economia.ilmessaggero.it/economia_e_finanza/flat_tax_cos_e_detrazioni_simulatore-3782544.html|archive-date=12 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.guidafisco.it/flat-tax-cos-e-come-funziona-domanda-durata-opzione-1859|title=Flat tax: cos'\u00e8 come funziona per famiglie e imprese e quali vantaggi?|trans-title=Flat tax: What is it like for families and businesses and what are the advantages?|language=it|date=1 April 2019|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014740/https://www.guidafisco.it/flat-tax-cos-e-come-funziona-domanda-durata-opzione-1859|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The government stressed that they will find the funds to implement it through the so-called \"fiscal peace\", that is a [[condonation]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://notizie.tiscali.it/politica/articoli/pace-fiscale-condono-lega-m5s/|title=La pace fiscale pentaleghista conferma che l'Italia \u00e8 una repubblica fondata sul condono|trans-title=The pentalghistic fiscal peace confirms that Italy is a republic founded on amnesty|author=Michael Pontrelli|language=it|date=8 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224026/https://notizie.tiscali.it/politica/articoli/pace-fiscale-condono-lega-m5s/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> However, many important economists{{who|date=June 2018}} and newspapers like ''[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]'' denounced that the condonation could not finance all the new tax system based on flat tax.<ref>{{cite news|work=Il Sole 24 Ore|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/norme-e-tributi/2018-06-07/flat-tax-pace-fiscale-bonus-no-tax-area-perche-non-tornano-conti-222404.shtml?uuid=AEgXCE2E|title=Flat tax, dalla pace fiscale ai bonus alla no tax area: perch\u00e9 non-tornano i conti|author=Gianni Trovati|language=it|date=8 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014709/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/norme-e-tributi/2018-06-07/flat-tax-pace-fiscale-bonus-no-tax-area-perche-non-tornano-conti-222404.shtml?uuid=AEgXCE2E|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Conte's first government, introduced a flat tax with a 15% rate, applied to small entrepreneurs and self-employed with an amount of annual revenues inferior to \u20ac65,000. Despite the so-called \"flat regime\" was a proposal of the right-wing League, it was confirmed also by Conte's second government, with the centre-left.<ref>{{cite news |title=Manovra, Misiani: \"Per le partite Iva resta il regime forfettario fino a 65 mila euro\" |url=https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2019/10/22/news/partite_iva_misini_resta_il_regime_forfettario_fino_a_65_mila_euro_-239181146/ |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=Repubblica.it |date=22 October 2019 |language=it |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211013152/https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2019/10/22/news/partite_iva_misini_resta_il_regime_forfettario_fino_a_65_mila_euro_-239181146/ |archive-date=11 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nDuring his first cabinet, his government rolled out the so-called \"citizens' income\" ({{lang-it|reddito di cittadinanza}}), a system of [[social welfare provision]] that provides a basic income and assistance in finding a job in order to help poor people and families.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy's government launches 'citizens' income' website |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20190204/italys-government-launches-citizens-income-scheme-website |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=thelocal.it |date=4 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191031154935/https://www.thelocal.it/20190204/italys-government-launches-citizens-income-scheme-website |archive-date=31 October 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Giuffrida |first1=Angela |title=Italy rolls out 'citizens' income' for the poor amid criticisms |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/mar/06/italy-rolls-out-citizens-income-for-the-poor-amid-criticisms |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=6 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191130040914/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/mar/06/italy-rolls-out-citizens-income-for-the-poor-amid-criticisms |archive-date=30 November 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The income is set to a maximum of \u20ac780 per month, and in its first year the program has almost 2.7 million applications.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hurst |first1=Luke |title=What is Italy's new 'Citizens' Income' scheme? {{!}} Euronews Answers |url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/03/06/what-is-italy-s-new-citizens-income-scheme-euronews-answers |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=euronews |agency=Reuters |date=6 March 2019 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191016155451/https://www.euronews.com/2019/03/06/what-is-italy-s-new-citizens-income-scheme-euronews-answers |archive-date=16 October 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=2.7 million people apply for Italy's basic income scheme |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20190424/million-people-apply-for-italys-basic-income-scheme |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=thelocal.it |date=24 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925071154/https://www.thelocal.it/20190424/million-people-apply-for-italys-basic-income-scheme |archive-date=25 September 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The bill was later confirmed by Conte's second cabinet.<ref>{{cite news |title=Reddito di cittadinanza e Quota 100, il governo: \"Nessuna revisione all'ordine del giorno\" |url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2019/12/30/reddito-di-cittadinanza-e-quota-100-il-governo-nessuna-revisione-allordine-del-giorno/5642683/ |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=Il Fatto Quotidiano |date=30 December 2019 |language=it-IT |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191231143703/https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2019/12/30/reddito-di-cittadinanza-e-quota-100-il-governo-nessuna-revisione-allordine-del-giorno/5642683/ |archive-date=31 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nDuring Conte's governments, more severe punishments for [[Tax evasion|tax dodgers]], which are a major problem in Italy, had been approved.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ansa.it/english/news/2018/06/05/jail-for-tax-dodgers-bans-for-corrupt-conte-2_30f0ebbb-5757-4ced-bf9d-32b51c9a8ec3.html|title=Jail for tax dodgers, bans for corrupt - Conte|agency=Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014811/http://www.ansa.it/english/news/2018/06/05/jail-for-tax-dodgers-bans-for-corrupt-conte-2_30f0ebbb-5757-4ced-bf9d-32b51c9a8ec3.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> With the 2020 financial bill, the government introduced a bill which provided prison for \"great tax dodgers\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/10/22/news/manovra_accordo_vertice_maggioranza-239157635/|title=Manovra, accordo sul carcere agli evasori. A luglio la stretta sui contanti e le multe a chi non-usa il Pos|date=22 October 2019|website=Repubblica.it|access-date=24 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191024100151/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/10/22/news/manovra_accordo_vertice_maggioranza-239157635/|archive-date=24 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte @ the EP (46159375855).jpg|thumb|left|220px|Conte at the [[European Parliament]]]]\nIn September 2019, at the head of his second government, Conte launched the so-called \"Green New Deal\", named after the analogous [[Green New Deal|US proposed legislation]] that aimed to address [[Global warming|climate change]] and [[economic inequality]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/2193592-green-new-deal-proposal-includes-free-higher-education-and-fair-pay/|title=Green New Deal proposal includes free higher education and fair pay|last=Whyte|first=Chelsea|date=12 February 2019|work=NewScientist|access-date=4 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190306042902/https://www.newscientist.com/article/2193592-green-new-deal-proposal-includes-free-higher-education-and-fair-pay/|archive-date=6 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In the same period, he praised students who [[September 2019 climate strikes|protested against climate change]], stating: \"The images of the squares of the [[Fridays for Future]] are extraordinary, with so many young people participating with such passion. From the government there is the utmost commitment to translate this request for change into concrete solutions. We all have a great responsibility.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GiuseppeConteIT/status/1177562186144763904|title=Sono straordinarie le immagini delle piazze di #fridaysforfuture, con cos\u00ec tanti giovani che partecipano con tale passione. Da parte mia e del Governo c'\u00e8 il massimo impegno a tradurre questa richiesta di cambiamento in soluzioni concrete. Abbiamo tutti una grande responsabilit\u00e0pic.twitter.com/7RxMGzwcPz|first=Giuseppe|last=Conte|date=27 September 2019|access-date=2 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927125631/https://twitter.com/GiuseppeConteIT/status/1177562186144763904|archive-date=27 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2020, the cabinet increased to \u20ac100 per month the so-called \"Renzi bonus\", a monthly allowance introduced by [[Matteo Renzi]]'s government in 2014, recognized to holders of a total annual income not exceeding \u20ac24,600.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ipsoa.it/wkpedia/bonus-80-euro|title=Bonus Renzi (80 euro)|website=Ipsoa}}</ref> A total of 11.7 million people benefited of the bonus in 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/cuneo-fiscale-bonus-renzi-sale-100-euro-117-milioni-contribuenti-ACCT1ECB |title=Cuneo fiscale, il bonus Renzi sale a 100 euro per 11,7 milioni di contribuenti |access-date=20 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200118135105/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/cuneo-fiscale-bonus-renzi-sale-100-euro-117-milioni-contribuenti-ACCT1ECB |archive-date=18 January 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn April 2020, amid the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|coronavirus pandemic]] which severely affected Europe, Conte became the most vocal supporter of the [[Eurobond (eurozone)|eurobond]]s' issuance to face the crisis,<ref>[https://www.agi.it/politica/news/2020-04-07/coronavirus-conte-mes-fase-2-8259417/ L'Italia non vuole attivare il fondo Salva-Stati e insiste sugli eurobond], ''agi.it''</ref> describing the [[European Stability Mechanism]] (ESM) as \"completely inadequate\".<ref>[https://www.milanofinanza.it/news/conte-stronca-il-mes-inadeguato-202004062145468694 Conte stronca il Mes: inadeguato], ''Milano Finanza''</ref> Conte found key allies in [[France]], [[Spain]], [[Belgium]], [[Ireland]], [[Portugal]], [[Greece]], [[Slovenia]] and [[Luxembourg]], which demanded more to be done in relation to coronavirus pandemic;<ref>[https://www.agi.it/economia/news/2020-03-25/coronabond-ue-pressioni-italia-francia-spagna-7852247/ Italia, Francia e Spagna chiedono all'Ue di dare via libera ai coronabond], ''agi.it''</ref> while [[Germany]], the [[Netherlands]], [[Austria]], [[Finland]] and [[Estonia]], strongly opposed the eurobonds.<ref>[https://www.corriere.it/economia/finanza/20_aprile_08/perche-germania-olanda-sono-contro-coronabond-proviamo-capirlo-ricapitolare-tutto-03472d1e-7964-11ea-afb4-c5f49a569528_preview.shtml?reason=unauthenticated&cat=1&cid=Q4JDr2Aj&pids=FR&credits=1&origin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.corriere.it%2Feconomia%2Ffinanza%2F20_aprile_08%2Fperche-germania-olanda-sono-contro-coronabond-proviamo-capirlo-ricapitolare-tutto-03472d1e-7964-11ea-afb4-c5f49a569528.shtml Coronabond, perch\u00e9 Germania e Olanda sono contro?], ''Corriere della Sera''</ref> Conte, during an interview to German weekly ''[[Die Zeit]]'', questioned: \"What do we want to do in Europe? Does each member state want to go its own way?\",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronabonds-and-the-idea-of-european-financial-unity/a-52980433|title=Coronabonds and the idea of European financial unity|website=DW|date=1 April 2020}}</ref> he also added: \"If we are a union, now is the time to prove it.\"<ref>[https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/da-die-zeit-de-telegraaf-ora-conte-parla-direttamente-all-opinione-pubblica-europea-ADQIljH Da Die Zeit a De Telegraaf, ora Conte parla direttamente all\u2019opinione pubblica europea], ''Die Zeit''</ref> On 8 April, he stated \"we should loosened European fiscal rules, otherwise we would have to cancel Europe and everyone will do on their own.\"<ref>[https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2020/04/08/news/coronavirus_conte_allentare_regole_fiscali_o_fine_ue-253506669/ Coronavirus: Conte, allentare regole fiscali o fine Ue], la Repubblica</ref>\n\n===Immigration===\n[[File:-G7Biarritz (48632626161).jpg|thumb|right|220px|Conte with President [[Donald Trump]]. The [[U.S. President]] often praised Conte's immigration policies]]\nWhen Conte became Prime Minister in 2018, he acted quickly to deliver on promises to the government's anti-immigration base through strict controls on [[European migrant crisis|immigration to Italy]]. Since 2013, Italy had absorbed over 700,000 African migrants arriving by boat from [[Libya]].<ref>{{cite news|title=What will Italy's new government mean for migrants?|url=https://www.thelocal.it/20180521/what-will-italys-new-government-mean-for-migrants|publisher=The Local|agency=[[Agence France-Presse|AFP]]|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401231010/https://www.thelocal.it/20180521/what-will-italys-new-government-mean-for-migrants|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=African migrants fear for future as Italy struggles with surge in arrivals|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-migrants-africa/african-migrants-fear-for-future-as-italy-struggles-with-surge-in-arrivals-idUSKBN1A30QD|agency=Reuters|date=18 July 2017|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402002627/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-migrants-africa/african-migrants-fear-for-future-as-italy-struggles-with-surge-in-arrivals-idUSKBN1A30QD|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> During his premiership, Conte and his Interior Minister [[Matteo Salvini]] promoted stricter policies regarding immigration and public security.<ref>{{cite news|agency=Agenzia Giornalistica Italia|language=it|date=11 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|url=https://www.agi.it/breakingnews/migranti_conte_grazie_salvini_italia_non_piu_sola_il_premier_da_macron_e_merkel-4017213/news/2018-06-11/|title=Migranti: Conte, grazie Salvini, Italia non-piu' sola; il premier da Macron e Merkel|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402002624/https://www.agi.it/breakingnews/migranti_conte_grazie_salvini_italia_non_piu_sola_il_premier_da_macron_e_merkel-4017213/news/2018-06-11/|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAfter Conte's approval on 10 June 2018, Salvini announced the closure of Italian [[ports]], stating: \"Everyone in Europe is doing their own business, now Italy is also raising its head. Let's stop the business of illegal immigration\".<ref>{{cite news|work=[[La Stampa]]|url=https://www.lastampa.it/2018/06/11/italia/migranti-litalia-sfida-malta-salvini-chiudiamo-i-porti-bVoFCfoAr11187cT5qJ4rL/pagina.html|title=Migranti, l'Italia sfida Malta. Salvini: chiudiamo i porti|trans-title=Migrants, Italy challenges Malta. Salvini: We close the Ports|author=Fabio Albanese|language=it|date=11 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224015/https://www.lastampa.it/2018/06/11/italia/migranti-litalia-sfida-malta-salvini-chiudiamo-i-porti-bVoFCfoAr11187cT5qJ4rL/pagina.html|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The vessel ''Aquarius'', which is operated jointly by ''[[M\u00e9decins Sans Fronti\u00e8res]]'' and ''[[SOS M\u00e9diterran\u00e9e]]'' and carried more than 600 migrants, was refused a port of disembarkation by the Italian authorities despite having been told to rescue the migrants by the same co-ordination centre. The Italian authority told the vessel to ask [[Malta]] to provide a disembarkation port, but Malta also refused.<ref>{{cite news|author=Mark Stone|url=https://news.sky.com/story/italy-shuts-ports-to-rescue-ship-carrying-over-600-migrants-11401125|title=More than 600 migrants running out of food as Italy shuts port to rescue ship|date=11 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190723093832/https://news.sky.com/story/italy-shuts-ports-to-rescue-ship-carrying-over-600-migrants-11401125|archive-date=23 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On the following day, the new Spanish Prime Minister [[Pedro S\u00e1nchez (politician)|Pedro S\u00e1nchez]] accepted the disputed migrant ship.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-44441386|title=Spain to accept disputed migrant ship Aquarius|publisher=BBC News|date=12 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190111192818/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-44441386|archive-date=11 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Conte accused French President [[Emmanuel Macron]] of hypocrisy after Macron said Italy was acting \"irresponsibly\" by refusing entry to migrants and suggested it had violated international maritime law.<ref>{{cite news|title=Italian foreign ministry summons French ambassador as tensions mount over port closures to refugee rescue boats|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/italy-port-closures-refugees-mediterranean-matteo-salvini-aquarius-emmanuel-macron-a8396916.html|work=The Independent|date=13 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402021834/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/italy-port-closures-refugees-mediterranean-matteo-salvini-aquarius-emmanuel-macron-a8396916.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 September 2018, the Council of Ministers approved the so-called \"Salvini decree\", which contained a series of hardline measures that will see the [[Italian government]] abolish key forms of protection for migrants and make it easier for them to be deported. The decree will also suspend the refugee application process of those who are considered \"socially dangerous\" or who have been convicted of a crime.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/sep/24/italian-government-approves-bill-anti-migrant-measures-matteo-salvini|work=[[The Guardian]]|title=Italian government approves Salvini bill targeting migrants|author=Giuffrida, Angela|publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]]|date=24 September 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190826133405/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/sep/24/italian-government-approves-bill-anti-migrant-measures-matteo-salvini|archive-date=26 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 September 2019, Italy and other four European countries, Germany, France, Malta and Finland, agreed on a draft deal to present to other EU countries on how to manage the migrant crisis and distribute those saved from the Mediterranean.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/09/23/five-eu-interior-ministers-agree-on-draft-migration-deal|title=Five EU interior ministers agree on draft migration deal|date=23 September 2019|website=euronews|access-date=25 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925072612/https://www.euronews.com/2019/09/23/five-eu-interior-ministers-agree-on-draft-migration-deal|archive-date=25 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> This agreement was considered a win for Conte and his new interior minister, [[Luciana Lamorgese]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/english/news/politics/2019/09/24/migrant-agreement-is-turning-point-conte_dacde2b7-1806-4083-8142-a5a491b34fcf.html|title=Migrant agreement is turning point-Conte - English|date=24 September 2019|website=ANSA.it|access-date=25 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925072613/http://www.ansa.it/english/news/politics/2019/09/24/migrant-agreement-is-turning-point-conte_dacde2b7-1806-4083-8142-a5a491b34fcf.html|archive-date=25 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fanpage.it/politica/migranti-la-doppia-vittoria-di-lamorgese-salvini-disarmato-europa-resuscitata/|title=Migranti, la doppia vittoria di Lamorgese: Salvini disarmato, Europa resuscitata|website=Fanpage}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ilmattino.it/primopiano/politica/migranti_news_giuseppe_conte-4731793.html|title=Migranti, Conte: sar\u00e0 la Ue a gestire la redistribuzione|website=www.ilmattino.it|access-date=24 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191024095929/https://www.ilmattino.it/primopiano/politica/migranti_news_giuseppe_conte-4731793.html|archive-date=24 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 April 2020, amid the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|coronavirus pandemic]], the government closed all Italian ports until 31 July, stating that they do not ensure the necessary requirements for the classification and definition of \"safe place\", established by the [[Hamburg Rules]]\u00a0on maritime search and rescue.\"<ref>[https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/litalia-chiude-i-porti_it_5e8d89f2c5b6e1d10a6c2671?yhj&utm_hp_ref=it-homepage L'Italia chiude i porti], ''Huffington Post''</ref>\n\n===Ponte Morandi collapse===\n{{main|Ponte Morandi#Collapse}}\n[[File:Il Ponte Morandi dopo il crollo, visto da Est, dettaglio.jpg|thumb|220px|right|The collapsed section of [[Ponte Morandi]], [[Genoa]]]] \nOn 14 August 2018, during a torrential rainstorm over the city of [[Genoa]], a {{Convert|210|m|adj=on}} section of [[Ponte Morandi]] collapsed.<ref name=\"BBC-45183624\" /><ref name=\"BBC-45183624\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-45183624|title=Italy bridge: Dozens feared dead in Genoa as motorway collapses|work=BBC News|date=14 August 2018|accessdate=14 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814110230/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-45183624|archive-date=14 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Between 30 and 35 cars and three trucks were reported to have fallen from the bridge, killing 43 people.<ref name=\"BBC-45182675\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/live/world-europe-45182675|title=As it happened: Genoa motorway bridge disaster|first1=David|last1=Molloy|first2=Laurence|last2=Peter|first3=Ellis|last3=Palmer|work=BBC News|date=14 August 2018|access-date=14 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180815152610/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/live/world-europe-45182675|archive-date=15 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/liguria/crollo-ponte-morandi-una-testimone-tiranti-spezzati-insieme_3158532-201802a.shtml|title=Crollo ponte Morandi, una testimone: tiranti spezzati insieme|work=Tgcom24|access-date=18 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180817205239/http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/liguria/crollo-ponte-morandi-una-testimone-tiranti-spezzati-insieme_3158532-201802a.shtml|archive-date=17 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe day after the collapse, Conte declared a state of emergency for the [[Liguria]] region, which would last for a year.<ref name=\"BBC45193614\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-45193614 |title=Italy bridge: State of emergency follows Genoa disaster |work=BBC News |accessdate=15 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180815093914/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-45193614 |archive-date=15 August 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> The government put pressure on the managers of the road, Autostrade per l\u2019Italia, which is part of the [[Benetton family]] owned [[Atlantia (company)|Atlantia]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/economia/18_agosto_17/choc-benetton-genova-3911bea8-a25d-11e8-b2f9-d4ce42b355f4.shtml|title=Lo choc dei Benetton. A Genova i manager chiederanno scusa|last=Pica|first=Paola|work=Corriere della Sera|access-date=18 August 2018|language=it-IT}}</ref> The M5S asked the revocation of license to Benetton family and the [[nationalization]] of Autostrade per l'Italia.<ref>[https://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2020/01/01/autostrade-via-alla-revoca-delle-concessioni.-di-maio-benetton-perderanno-profitti_d451b32a-ee93-46f5-941c-7036219ec477.html Autostrade, via alla revoca delle concessioni. Di Maio: 'Benetton perderanno profitti'] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200107152119/http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2020/01/01/autostrade-via-alla-revoca-delle-concessioni.-di-maio-benetton-perderanno-profitti_d451b32a-ee93-46f5-941c-7036219ec477.html |date=7 January 2020 }}, ANSA</ref> However, despite bitter controversies, the revocation has not yet been implemented.\n\nThe last two cable-stayed pillars of the bridge were demolished [[explosive demolition|using a tonne of explosives]] on 28 June 2019. The complete bridge was planned to be removed, along with multiple damaged houses in the surrounding area.<ref name=bbc-20190628>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/av/world-europe-48797883/morandi-bridge-towers-demolished-in-genoa |title=Morandi bridge towers demolished in Genoa |work=BBC News |date=28 June 2019 |accessdate=28 June 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190628113346/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/av/world-europe-48797883/morandi-bridge-towers-demolished-in-genoa |archive-date=28 June 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> A replacement bridge, designed by Italian architect [[Renzo Piano]], has been under construction since 25 June 2019, and is set to be opened in the first half of 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.engineering.com/BIM/ArticleID/18231/After-Bridge-Tragedy-Genoa-Selects-a-New-Design.aspx|title=After Bridge Tragedy, Genoa Selects a New Design|date=2019-01-10|website=www.engineering.com|language=en-US|access-date=3 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825091927/https://www.engineering.com/BIM/ArticleID/18231/After-Bridge-Tragedy-Genoa-Selects-a-New-Design.aspx|archive-date=25 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Constitutional reform===\nUnder Conte's governments, the [[Italian Parliament]] approved the so-called \"[[Riccardo Fraccaro|Fraccaro]] Reform\", from the name of the M5S deputy who was the bill's first signatory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rainews.it/tgr/trento/articoli/2019/10/tnt-camera-dei-deputati-riforma-fraccaro-taglio-parlamentari-trentino-alto-adige-dbb4795d-063b-47be-a171-d467a65ee157.html|title=La Camera approva la riforma Fraccaro. Via al taglio dei parlamentari - TGR Trento|website=TGR|access-date=24 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191024095931/https://www.rainews.it/tgr/trento/articoli/2019/10/tnt-camera-dei-deputati-riforma-fraccaro-taglio-parlamentari-trentino-alto-adige-dbb4795d-063b-47be-a171-d467a65ee157.html|archive-date=24 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The reform was finally approved by the Parliament, with the fourth and final vote in the Chamber of Deputies on 8 October with 553 votes in favor and 14 against. In the final vote, the bill was supported both by the majority and the opposition;<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sciorilli Borrelli |first1=Silvia |title=Italian lawmakers want fewer Italian lawmakers |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/italian-lawmakers-want-fewer-seats-in-parliament-vote-referendum/ |accessdate=24 October 2019 |work=POLITICO |date=8 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009141725/https://www.politico.eu/article/italian-lawmakers-want-fewer-seats-in-parliament-vote-referendum/ |archive-date=9 October 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> only the liberal party [[More Europe]] (+Eu) and other small groups voted against.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://it.notizie.yahoo.com/taglio-dei-parlamentari-orfini-la-riforma-fa-schifo-chi-sono-i-contrari-080204412.html|title=Taglio dei parlamentari, Orfini: \"La riforma fa schifo\". Chi sono i contrari|website=it.notizie.yahoo.com|access-date=24 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009115403/https://it.notizie.yahoo.com/taglio-dei-parlamentari-orfini-la-riforma-fa-schifo-chi-sono-i-contrari-080204412.html|archive-date=9 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The reform provided a cut in the number of MPs, which would shrink from 630 to 400 deputies and from 315 to 200 senators.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy shrinks parliament 'to save \u20ac1bn' |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-49979103 |accessdate=24 October 2019 |work=BBC News |date=8 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009093221/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-49979103 |archive-date=9 October 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAfter the approval, Conte stated: \"The cut to the parliamentarians is a reform that will bring to a greater efficiency of the parliamentary jobs. Now, citizens to be closer to the institutions. It is a historical passage that, together with other projected reform, will be a prelude to greater efficiency of our parliamentary system.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2019/10/08/taglio-parlamentari-e-legge-montecitorio-approva-con-553-si-di-maio-fatto-storico-saremo-leali-su-contrappesi-conte-riforme-riduce-i-costi-e-dara-piu-efficienza/5504346/|title=Taglio parlamentari \u00e8 legge: Montecitorio approva con 553 S\u00ec. Di Maio: \"Fatto storico, saremo leali su contrappesi\". Conte: \"Riforma riduce i costi e dar\u00e0 pi\u00f9 efficienza\"|date=8 October 2019|website=Il Fatto Quotidiano|access-date=24 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191011174152/https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2019/10/08/taglio-parlamentari-e-legge-montecitorio-approva-con-553-si-di-maio-fatto-storico-saremo-leali-su-contrappesi-conte-riforme-riduce-i-costi-e-dara-piu-efficienza/5504346/|archive-date=11 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[2020 Italian constitutional referendum|referendum]] to approve the reform was scheduled on 29 March, however it was postponed due to the [[2020 coronavirus outbreak in Italy|coronavirus pandemic]] which severely affected Italy.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.interno.gov.it/it/notizie/rinviato-referendum-29-marzo-sul-taglio-dei-parlamentari |title=inviato il referendum del 29 marzo sul taglio dei parlamentari |access-date=10 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314100154/https://www.interno.gov.it/it/notizie/rinviato-referendum-29-marzo-sul-taglio-dei-parlamentari |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Coronavirus pandemic===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy}}\nIn February 2020, Italy became one of the world's main centres for confirmed cases of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]], a respiratory disease caused by the [[SARS-CoV-2]] virus that originated in [[China]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/salute/ricerca/coronavirus_italia_prima_contagi_europa-5068457.html |title=Coronavirus, Italia prima in Europa per numero di contagi: \u00e8 caccia ai focolai |access-date=23 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223000631/https://www.ilmessaggero.it/salute/ricerca/coronavirus_italia_prima_contagi_europa-5068457.html |archive-date=23 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> As of April 2020, over 170,000 coronavirus cases were confirmed, affecting mainly [[Lombardy]], [[Emilia-Romagna]], [[Veneto]] and [[Piedmont]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-italia-nuovi-contagi-lombardia-veneto-245e72d4-5540-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml|title=Coronavirus, due casi a Milano|last=online|first=Simona Ravizza e redazione|date=2020-02-22|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222225105/https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-italia-nuovi-contagi-lombardia-veneto-245e72d4-5540-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml|archive-date=22 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:2020 coronavirus task force.jpg|thumb|220px|left|Italian [[Conte II Cabinet|government]] task force to face the coronavirus pandemic]]\nIn late January, the government banned all flights from and to China, becoming the first European country to adopt this measure.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://roma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/01/30/news/coronavirus_turisti_cinesi-247194041/ |title=Coronavirus, primi due casi confermati in Italia: sono turisti cinesi a Roma. Chiuso il traffico aereo con la Cina |access-date=23 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225152158/https://roma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/01/30/news/coronavirus_turisti_cinesi-247194041/ |archive-date=25 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 22 February, the [[Council of Ministers of Italy|Council of Ministers]] announced a bill to contain the COVID-19 outbreak, quarantining more than 50,000 people from 11 different municipalities in [[Northern Italy]]. Prime Minister Conte stated: \"In the outbreak areas, entry and exit will not be provided. Suspension of work activities and sport events has already been ordered in those areas.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/decreto_governo_contro_coronavirus-249308355/|title=Coronavirus, decreto del governo: nei comuni focolaio stop ad ingressi ed uscite. Conte: \"Non trasformeremo l'Italia in un lazzaretto\"|date=2020-02-22|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-22}}</ref>\n\nSchools were closed in 10 municipalities in Lombardy, one in Veneto and in Emilia-Romagna. In some areas, all public events were cancelled and commercial activities were halted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_21/scuole-chiuse-il-coronavirus-lombardia-lodi-piacenza-codogno-a190ccee-54bd-11ea-9196-da7d305401b7.shtml|title=Quali sono i Comuni che hanno chiuso le scuole per il Coronavirus|last=online|first=Redazione|date=2020-02-21|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref> Regional train services suspended the stops in the most affected areas \u2013 with trains not stopping at Codogno, Maleo and Casalpusterlengo stations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-treni-fermi-ore-lecce-milano-nessuno-stop-comuni-rischio-lodigiano-431e997c-553d-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml|title=Coronavirus, treni fermi per ore a Lecce e Milano. I convogli non-fermano nei Comuni a rischio del Lodigiano|last=online|first=Redazione|date=2020-02-22|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/coronavirus_il_comune_di_milano_sospende_dal_lavoro_i_dipendenti_che_abitano_delle_zone_coinvolte-249252812/|title=Coronavirus, per una settimana didattica sospesa nelle universit\u00e0 lombarde. Comune di Milano e grandi aziende: i lavoratori a rischio restano a casa|date=2020-02-22|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222165821/https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/coronavirus_il_comune_di_milano_sospende_dal_lavoro_i_dipendenti_che_abitano_delle_zone_coinvolte-249252812/|archive-date=22 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Universities in Lombardy suspended all activities from 23 February.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.unipv.it/?p=46130|title=news.unipv \u2013 Coronavirus: Sospensione delle attivit\u00e0 didattiche dal 24/2 all\u20191/03|website=news.unipv|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unimi.it/it/coronavirus-misure-urgenti-la-comunita-universitaria|title=Coronavirus: misure urgenti per la comunit\u00e0 universitaria {{!}} Universit\u00e0 degli Studi di Milano Statale|website=www.unimi.it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unibg.it/node/9238|title=Sospensione precauzionale delle attivit\u00e0 didattiche {{!}} Universit\u00e0 degli studi di Bergamo|website=www.unibg.it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 March 2020, Prime Minister Conte extended the quarantine to all of [[Lombardy]] and 14 other northern provinces, [[2020 Italy coronavirus lockdown|putting more than a quarter of the national population under lockdown]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Northern Italy quarantines 16 million people |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51787238 |website=BBC |accessdate=8 March 2020 |date=8 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308000026/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51787238 |archive-date=8 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On the following day, he announced in a press conference that all measures previously applied only in the so-called \"red zones\" had been extended to the whole country, putting ''de facto'' 60 million people in lockdown. He later proceeded to officially sign the executive decree.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/09/europe/coronavirus-italy-lockdown-intl/index.html |title=All of Italy is in lockdown as coronavirus cases rise |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309190226/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/09/europe/coronavirus-italy-lockdown-intl/index.html |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/09/coronavirus-italy-prime-minister-country-lockdown?utm_term=Autofeed&CMP=twt_gu&utm_medium&utm_source=Twitter#Echobox=1583793579 |title=Coronavirus: Italian PM extends lockdown to entire country |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323165905/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/09/coronavirus-italy-prime-minister-country-lockdown?utm_term=Autofeed&CMP=twt_gu&utm_medium&utm_source=Twitter#Echobox=1583793579 |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> This measure was described as the largest lockdown in human history.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/08/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-quarantine.html |title=On Day 1 of Broad Lockdown, a Debate Arises: Can Italians Follow the Rules? |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309095039/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/08/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-quarantine.html |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2020/3/7/21169637/italy-lockdown-lombardy-coronavirus-outbreak|title=Italy locks down northern region in response to coronavirus outbreak|first=Kim|last=Lyons|date=7 March 2020|website=The Verge|accessdate=8 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308071135/https://www.theverge.com/2020/3/7/21169637/italy-lockdown-lombardy-coronavirus-outbreak|archive-date=8 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Horowitz |first1=Jason |title=Italy Locks Down Much of the Country\u2019s North Over the Coronavirus |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/07/world/europe/coronavirus-italy.html |accessdate=8 March 2020 |work=The New York Times |date=7 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308002308/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/07/world/europe/coronavirus-italy.html |archive-date=8 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=Italia>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-milan-lombardy-lockdowns/2020/03/07/403fcea2-60b3-11ea-ac50-18701e14e06d_story.html To contain coronavirus, Italy will restrict movement across much of its northern region, including the city of Milan] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309111222/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-milan-lombardy-lockdowns/2020/03/07/403fcea2-60b3-11ea-ac50-18701e14e06d_story.html |date=9 March 2020 }}, ''[[Washington Post]]'', Chico Harlan and Stefano Pitrelli, 7 March 2020. Retrieved 8 March 2020.</ref>\n\nThe lockdown measures, despite being widely approved by [[public opinion]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=De Feo |first1=Gianluca |title=Sondaggio Demos: gradimento per Conte alle stelle |url=https://www.youtrend.it/2020/03/20/sondaggio-demos-gradimento-per-conte-alle-stelle/ |website=YouTrend |accessdate=22 March 2020 |language=it-IT |date=20 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322105609/https://www.youtrend.it/2020/03/20/sondaggio-demos-gradimento-per-conte-alle-stelle/ |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> were also described as the largest suppression of [[constitutional right]]s in the history of the republic.<ref>{{cite news |title=Blog {{!}} Coronavirus, la sospensione delle libert\u00e0 costituzionali \u00e8 realt\u00e0. Ma per me ce la stiamo cavando bene |url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/18/coronavirus-la-sospensione-delle-liberta-costituzionali-e-realta-ma-per-me-ce-la-stiamo-cavando-bene/5739296/ |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Il Fatto Quotidiano |date=18 March 2020 |language=it-IT |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322105608/https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/18/coronavirus-la-sospensione-delle-liberta-costituzionali-e-realta-ma-per-me-ce-la-stiamo-cavando-bene/5739296/ |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Un uomo solo \u00e8 al comando dell\u2019Italia, e nessuno ha niente da ridire |url=https://www.linkiesta.it/2020/03/italia-coronavirus-conte-uomo-solo-al-comando/ |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=Linkiesta |date=24 March 2020 |language=it-IT |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324114753/https://www.linkiesta.it/2020/03/italia-coronavirus-conte-uomo-solo-al-comando/ |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, the [[Ministry of Health (Italy)|Ministry of Health]] ordered tighter regulations on free movement. The new measures banned open-air sports and running, except individually and in close proximity of one's residence.  Parks, playgrounds and public green were closed down. Furthermore, movement across the country was further restricted, by banning \"any movement towards a residence different from the main one\", including holiday homes, during weekends and holidays.<ref>{{cite news |title=Le nuove restrizioni decise dal governo |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/20/ordinanza-coronavirus-attivita-sportiva-correre/ |accessdate=21 March 2020 |work=Il Post |date=20 March 2020 |language=it-IT |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321084610/https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/20/ordinanza-coronavirus-attivita-sportiva-correre/ |archive-date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> While on the following day, Conte announced further restrictions within the nationwide lockdown, by halting all non-essential production, industries and businesses in Italy,<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, Milano trema: 634 casi in un giorno. Fontana chiama Conte: chiudere tutto, Esercito per strada |url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_milano_casi_contagi_lombardia_ultime_notizie-5121166.html |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=ilmessaggero.it |language=it |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320134113/https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_milano_casi_contagi_lombardia_ultime_notizie-5121166.html |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> following the rise in the number of new cases and deaths in the previous days.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Farrer |first1=Martin |title=Italy: PM warns of worst crisis since WW2 as coronavirus deaths leap by almost 800 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/22/italian-pm-warns-of-worst-crisis-since-ww2-as-coronavirus-deaths-leap-by-almost-800 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=22 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322101342/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/22/italian-pm-warns-of-worst-crisis-since-ww2-as-coronavirus-deaths-leap-by-almost-800 |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=De Angelis |first1=Alessandro |title=\"Chiudete tutto, anche le fabbriche\" (di A. De Angelis) |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/giorgio-gori-chiudete-tutto-anche-le-fabbriche_it_5e74ad81c5b63c3b648e6263 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=L'HuffPost |date=20 March 2020 |language=it |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321172447/https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/giorgio-gori-chiudete-tutto-anche-le-fabbriche_it_5e74ad81c5b63c3b648e6263 |archive-date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, in a live-streamed press conference, Conte announced a new decree approved by the Council of Ministers. The decree imposed higher fines for the violation of the restrictive measures, and a regulation of the relationship between government and Parliament during the emergency. It included also the possibility of reducing or suspending public and private transport, and gave the regional governments power to impose additional restrictive regulations in their Regions for a maximum of seven days before being confirmed by national decree.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy announces fines of up to \u20ac3,000 for breaking quarantine rules |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20200324/italy-announces-fines-of-up-to-3000-for-breaking-quarantine-rules |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=thelocal.it |date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325091256/https://www.thelocal.it/20200324/italy-announces-fines-of-up-to-3000-for-breaking-quarantine-rules |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Cosa ha detto Giuseppe Conte |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/24/decreto-restrizioni-sanzioni-coronavirus/ |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=Il Post |date=24 March 2020 |language=it-IT |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325091256/https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/24/decreto-restrizioni-sanzioni-coronavirus/ |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 1 April, Conte's government extended the period of lockdown until 13 April.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Henley |first1=Jon |title=Italy extends lockdown amid signs coronavirus infection rate is easing |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/01/italy-extends-lockdown-amid-signs-coronavirus-infection-rate-is-easing |accessdate=1 April 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=1 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401135230/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/01/italy-extends-lockdown-amid-signs-coronavirus-infection-rate-is-easing |archive-date=1 April 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> While on 6 April, Conte announced a new economic stimulus plan, consisting of \u20ac200 billion of state-guaranteed loans to companies and additional \u20ac200 billion of guarantees to support exports.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Leali |first1=Giorgio |title=Italy adopts \u20ac400B liquidity plan amid coronavirus crisis |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/italy-adopts-e400b-liquidity-plan-amid-coronavirus-crisis/ |accessdate=7 April 2020 |work=POLITICO |date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 April, Conte made further announcements extending the lockdown until the 3rd of May, allowing some specific businesses, like [[bookstore]]s\u00a0and [[silviculture]] activities, to reopen under specific safe measures.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/04/10/news/coronavirus_giuseppe_conte_riaperture-253677426/|title=Coronavirus, il premier Conte: \"Chiusura fino al 3 maggio, non possiamo cedere adesso\"|date=10 April 2020|website=la Repubblica}}</ref> On the same day, he appointed a [[task force]] to relaunch Italy after the crisis; the team was led by [[Vittorio Colao]] and composed by a total of nineteen members, chosen among university professors, managers and public administration officers, which notably included [[Mariana Mazzucato]] and [[Enrico Giovannini]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/politica/2020/04/10/coronavirus-ecco-task-force-per-fase_pxW186qVm9sQHlupjz2wGN.html|title=Coronavirus, ecco la task force per la Fase 2|website=Adnkronos}}</ref>\n\n===Foreign policy===\n{{See also|List of official trips made by Giuseppe Conte}}\n[[File:President Trump Meets with the Prime Minister of the Italian Republic (49173499077).jpg|thumb|Conte with U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] in December 2019]]\nSince the beginning of his term as prime minister, Conte's [[foreign policy]] has been characterized by a lenient approach to Russia. For example, he advocated the repeal of international sanctions against Russia, which according to him damage the [[Italian economy]].<ref>[https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/mondo/putin-a-roma-conte-contro-le-sanzioni-a-mosca-sono-un-danno-per-tutti-_3218344-201902a.shtml Putin a Roma, Conte contro le sanzioni a Mosca: \"Sono un danno per tutti\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190704215947/https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/mondo/putin-a-roma-conte-contro-le-sanzioni-a-mosca-sono-un-danno-per-tutti-_3218344-201902a.shtml |date=4 July 2019 }}, TgCom24</ref> He also considered Russia a strategic partner in the [[War on Terror|fight]] against [[Islamic terrorism]].<ref>{{cite news|language=it|url=http://www.askanews.it/video/2018/06/05/conte-appartenenza-alla-nato-ma-apriremo-alla-russia-20180605_video_16453330/|title=Conte: appartenenza alla Nato ma apriremo alla Russia|agency=[[ASCA (news agency)|ASCA]]|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401180005/http://www.askanews.it/video/2018/06/05/conte-appartenenza-alla-nato-ma-apriremo-alla-russia-20180605_video_16453330/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> However, Conte stressed that under his leadership Italy will remain an active member of [[NATO]] and a close ally of the [[United States]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/conte-restiamo-nella-nato-e-con-usa-ma-via-sanzioni-alla-russia_3144252-201802a.shtml|title=Conte: restiamo nella Nato e con Usa ma via sanzioni alla Russia|language=it|date=5 July 2018|trans-title=Conte: We remain in NATO and with the USA but via sanctions against Russia|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401192645/https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/conte-restiamo-nella-nato-e-con-usa-ma-via-sanzioni-alla-russia_3144252-201802a.shtml|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The good relations between the two administration became evident in March 2020, during the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]]. After a phone call with Conte, Russian president [[Vladimir Putin]] arranged the [[Russian Armed Forces|Russian army]] to send military medics, special disinfection vehicles and other medical equipment to Italy, which was the European country hardest hit by coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian army to send coronavirus help to Italy after Putin phone call |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-russia-italy/russian-army-to-send-coronavirus-help-to-italy-after-putin-phone-call-idUSKBN219081 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Reuters |date=22 March 2020 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322092901/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-russia-italy/russian-army-to-send-coronavirus-help-to-italy-after-putin-phone-call-idUSKBN219081 |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nDuring his premiership, Conte built a close relationship with [[U.S. President]] [[Donald Trump]]. Since the beginning of Conte's government, Trump considered him a key ally during international meetings.<ref>[https://www.thelocal.it/20180615/trump-praises-conte-as-very-strong-on-immigration Trump praises Conte as 'very strong' on immigration], ''The Local''</ref>  On 8 and 9 June, Conte participated in his first [[44th G7 summit|G7 summit]], hosted by Prime Minister [[Justin Trudeau]] in [[Canada]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tg24.sky.it/mondo/photogallery/2018/06/08/g7-conte-incontro-leader.html|title=G7, il primo incontro del premier Conte con gli altri leader. FOTO - Sky TG24|date=8 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233435/https://tg24.sky.it/mondo/photogallery/2018/06/08/g7-conte-incontro-leader.html|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> During the summit, he was the only leader to back President Trump and his proposal to readmit Russia into the G7.<ref>{{cite news|agency=Reuters|date=8 June 2018|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/g7-summit-italy-russia/italys-new-pm-backs-trump-on-re-admitting-russia-into-the-g7-idUSR1N1SZ002|title=Italy's new PM backs Trump on re-admitting Russia into the G7|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331004627/https://www.reuters.com/article/g7-summit-italy-russia/italys-new-pm-backs-trump-on-re-admitting-russia-into-the-g7-idUSR1N1SZ002|archive-date=31 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> However, he later assumed a more [[pro-Europe]]an view, shared by the other five leaders, condemning [[Trump tariffs]] on [[steel]] and [[aluminium]] exported by the [[European Union]].<ref>{{cite news|date=9 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|url=https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2018/06/09/news/conte_vede_macron_al_g7_e_non_rompe_con_l_ue_il_tweet_di_macron_condividiamo_l_europa_-198544751/|title=G7, Trudeau: \"Documento finale firmato da tutti\". Trump va via e chiede riammissione Russia|work=la Repubblica|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331004636/https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2018/06/09/news/conte_vede_macron_al_g7_e_non_rompe_con_l_ue_il_tweet_di_macron_condividiamo_l_europa_-198544751/|archive-date=31 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On the following day, Conte was thanked for his positions on Russia and his populist stance by President Trump, who invited him to the [[White House]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2018/06/09/trump-italy-prime-minister-white-house-giuseppe-conte-635009|title=Trump: Italy's populist prime minister to visit White House|author=Brent D. Griffiths|website=[[Politico]]|date=9 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233237/https://www.politico.com/story/2018/06/09/trump-italy-prime-minister-white-house-giuseppe-conte-635009|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 28 June, Conte participated in his first [[European Council]] meeting and blocked a joint EU trade and defense statement criticizing Trump's tariff policy.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-eu-summit-conte-idUSKBN1JO2UF|title=Italy blocks joint text on trade, defense at EU summit|date=28 June 2018|agency=[[Reuters]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233208/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-eu-summit-conte-idUSKBN1JO2UF|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2018, Trump praised Conte, describing him as a \"really great leader\" and \"very strong on immigration\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://video.corriere.it/trump-il-primo-ministro-italiano-conte-fantastico-severo-sull-immigrazione-questo-momento-paga/d065ab42-70a9-11e8-8f08-e72858c58491|title=Trump: \"Il primo ministro italiano Conte \u00e8 fantastico. \u00c8 severo sull'immigrazione e in questo momento paga\"|date=15 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233402/https://video.corriere.it/trump-il-primo-ministro-italiano-conte-fantastico-severo-sull-immigrazione-questo-momento-paga/d065ab42-70a9-11e8-8f08-e72858c58491|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Trump also endorsed Conte during the [[2019 Italian government formation#Political crisis|2019 Italian political crisis]], hoping that he could remain Prime Minister.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agi.it/politica/trump_endorsement_conte-6090415/news/2019-08-27/|title=L'endorsement di Trump per il Conte-bis|website=Agi|access-date=30 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830123932/https://www.agi.it/politica/trump_endorsement_conte-6090415/news/2019-08-27/|archive-date=30 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 31 March 2020, President Trump announced that the [[United States]] would send 100 million dollars of medical aids to Italy.<ref>[https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/31/coronavirus-trump-annuncia-100-milioni-di-dollari-di-aiuti-allitalia-giuseppi-era-molto-contento-poi-mostra-macchina-per-test-rapido/5754858/ Trump annuncia: \"Aiuti sanitari all'Italia per 100 milioni di dollari\", compresi kit per i test veloci], ''Huffington Post''</ref> After few days, during an interview at the [[NBC]], Conte described Trump as \"Italy's most true and loyal friend\".<ref>[https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/news/italian-prime-minister-thanks-trump-for-being-countrys-true-and-loyal-friend-through-pandemic Italian prime minister thanks Trump for being country's 'true and loyal friend' through pandemic], ''Washington Examiner''</ref> On 11 Apri, Trump issued an [[executive order]] in which he allowed U.S. militaries deployed in Italy to assist Italian law enforcement in facing the crisis.<ref>[https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2020/04/11/news/l_ordine_esecutivo_di_trump_per_l_italia_contro_il_coronavirus_mobilitiamo_anche_i_nosri_30_mila_soldati_-253733750/ 'ordine esecutivo di Trump: \"Per l'Italia contro il coronavirus mobilitiamo anche i nostri 30 mila soldati\"], ''la Repubblica''</ref>\n\n[[File:-G7Biarritz (48616362963).jpg|thumb|left|Conte and other leaders at the [[45th G7 summit]] in Biarritz, France]]\nAt the beginning of his political career, Conte was described as a [[populist]]\u00a0and [[Eurosceptic]] politician, openly critic towards the EU, whose economic and financial rules were described as \"old and outdated\".<ref>[https://www.politico.eu/article/giuseppe-conte-interview-shake-up-europe-italy/ Italian PM: We want to shake things up in Europe], ''Politico''</ref> However, he later toned down his Eurosceptic rhetoric, thus still remaining a vocal [[anti-austerity]] leader, as it became evidence during the 2020 coronavirus pandemic, which severely affected Europe.<ref>[https://www.ilgazzettino.it/italia/primopiano/conte_sente_von_der_leyen_italia_non_accettera_compromessi_al_ribasso_italia_europa_eurobond_si_mes_no-5158555.html Conte sente Von Der Leyen: \u00abL'Italia non accetter\u00e0 compromessi al ribasso\u00bb. L'Italia all'Europa: \u00abEurobond s\u00ec, Mes no\u00bb] ''Il Gazzettino''</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, Conte and the Chinese President [[Xi Jinping]] [[2019 Xi Jinping Italy and France visit|signed in Rome]] 29 economic and institutional agreements amounting to 2.5 billion [[euro]]s, including a [[memorandum of understanding]] vis-\u00e0-vis the [[Belt and Road Initiative]] investments program.<ref>{{cite news|date=23 March 2019|accessdate=1 April 2019|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/03/23/news/xi_jinping_cina_italia_villa_madama_accordi_commerciali_conte_mattarella_di_maio-222293765/|title=Cina-Italia, firmati gli accordi. Di Maio: \"Valgono 2,5 miliardi ma con un potenziale di 20\". Gelo con Salvini|work=la Repubblica|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233258/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/03/23/news/xi_jinping_cina_italia_villa_madama_accordi_commerciali_conte_mattarella_di_maio-222293765/|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.quotidiano.net/politica/xi-jinping-in-italia-1.4504422|title=Xi Jinping a Roma, firmato il Memorandum su Via della Seta. \"Grazie Italia, un successo\"|publisher=QuotidianoNet|date=23 March 2019|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233249/https://www.quotidiano.net/politica/xi-jinping-in-italia-1.4504422|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In August 2019, he took part, as caretaker Prime Minister, in the [[45th G7 summit]] in [[Biarritz]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/conte-resiste-nel-fortino-dorato-di-biarritz_it_5d62a7c1e4b0b59d2576492f|title=Conte resiste nel 'fortino dorato' di Biarritz (da Biarritz A. Mauro)|date=25 August 2019|website=L'HuffPost|access-date=27 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190827205147/https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/conte-resiste-nel-fortino-dorato-di-biarritz_it_5d62a7c1e4b0b59d2576492f|archive-date=27 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The main topics of the summit included [[global trade]], [[climate change]], taxing technology companies,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2019/08/24/world/24reuters-g7-summit-trump.html |title=Trump Arrives in Biarritz for Testing G7 Summit |date=24 August 2019 |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=27 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825014058/https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2019/08/24/world/24reuters-g7-summit-trump.html |archive-date=25 August 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> but also [[Iran nuclear deal]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2019/08/24/world/24reuters-g7-summit-tusk.html |title=G7 Summit to Be 'a Difficult Test of Unity': EU's Tusk |date=24 August 2019 |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=27 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825014152/https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2019/08/24/world/24reuters-g7-summit-tusk.html |archive-date=25 August 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> and [[2019 Amazon wildfires]].<ref name=\"theguardian_Phillips_20190822\">{{Cite news| issn = 0261-3077| last1 = Phillips| first1 = Tom| last2 = correspondent| first2 = Latin America| title = Amazon rainforest fires: Macron calls for 'international crisis' to lead G7 discussions| work = The Guardian| access-date = 23 August 2019| date = 23 August 2019| url = https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/23/amazon-rainforest-fires-macron-calls-for-international-crisis-to-lead-g7-discussions| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190914153151/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/23/amazon-rainforest-fires-macron-calls-for-international-crisis-to-lead-g7-discussions| archive-date = 14 September 2019| url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nConte criticized the [[2019 Turkish offensive into north-eastern Syria]]. He stated that the offensive puts the region's civilians and stability in jeopardy.<ref>[https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/10/world-reacts-turkey-military-operation-northeast-syria-191009181335266.html \"World reacts to Turkey's military operation in northeast Syria\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191013104614/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/10/world-reacts-turkey-military-operation-northeast-syria-191009181335266.html |date=13 October 2019 }}. Al Jazeera. 10 October 2019.</ref>\n\nIn January 2020, the situation of the [[Libyan Civil War (2014\u2013present)|Libyan Civil War]] became increasingly worrying, with the troops of field marshal [[Khalifa Haftar]] approaching [[Tripoli]]. During the crisis, Prime Minister Conte had a series of bilateral meetings in Rome both with Haftar and [[Fayez al-Sarraj]], the Chairman of the [[Presidential Council (Libya)|Presidential Council of Libya]], who are considered two of the main contenders in the civil war.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/libia-sarraj-palazzo-chigi-incontrare-conte-ACnuMOBB |title=Libia, Haftar annuncia il cessate il fuoco. L\u2019incontro Conte-Sarraj |access-date=12 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112102519/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/libia-sarraj-palazzo-chigi-incontrare-conte-ACnuMOBB |archive-date=12 January 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> After pressures from the international community, on 12 January Haftar announced a [[ceasefire]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/libyan-forces-loyal-haftar-announce-conditional-ceasefire-200112004206081.html |title=Libyan forces loyal to Haftar announce conditional ceasefire |access-date=12 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112102519/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/libyan-forces-loyal-haftar-announce-conditional-ceasefire-200112004206081.html |archive-date=12 January 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Political views and public image==\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte EC.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Conte at the [[European Council]]]]\nDuring his first cabinet, Conte has often been considered a [[Neo-nationalism|neo-nationalist]] politician,<ref>{{cite news|work=[[Financial Times]]|date=25 May 2018|title=Market turmoil hits Conte's road to Rome|url=https://www.ft.com/content/7ad0ff6a-6028-11e8-9334-2218e7146b04}}</ref> however, since September 2019, when he became the head of a [[centre-left]] coalition government, he toned down his nationalist rhetoric.<ref>[https://www.lastampa.it/topnews/primo-piano/2019/08/30/news/juncker-loda-la-metamorfosi-di-conte-e-la-rivendica-e-come-con-tsipras-1.37394484 Juncker loda la metamorfosi di Conte e la rivendica: \u201c\u00c8 come con Tsipras\u201d], ''La Stampa''</ref> Despite being labeled as a post-ideological leader,<ref>[https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/in-edicola/articoli/2019/09/20/dalema-benedice-il-nuovo-conte-post-ideologico-tra-selfie-e-salsicce/5465121/ D\u2019Alema benedice il nuovo Conte post-ideologico, tra selfie e salsicce], ''Il Fatto Quotidiano''</ref> Conte described his political ideal as \"new [[Renaissance humanism|humanism]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/esteri/2019/05/09/conte-mondo-non-piu-eurocentrico-italia-per-nuovo-umanesimo_lnB5GN6crUz1kLLJzdScaI.html|title=Conte: \"Mondo non-pi\u00f9 eurocentrico, Italia per nuovo umanesimo\"|website=Adnkronos|access-date=29 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190829090056/https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/esteri/2019/05/09/conte-mondo-non-piu-eurocentrico-italia-per-nuovo-umanesimo_lnB5GN6crUz1kLLJzdScaI.html|archive-date=29 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fanpage.it/politica/il-testo-completo-del-discorso-di-giuseppe-conte-al-senato/|title=Il testo completo del discorso di Giuseppe Conte al Senato|website=Fanpage|access-date=29 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831215502/https://www.fanpage.it/politica/il-testo-completo-del-discorso-di-giuseppe-conte-al-senato/|archive-date=31 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nDuring an interview in 2018, Conte said he used to vote for the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] before approaching the M5S during the late 2010s.<ref>[https://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/non-sono-dei-5-stelle-spunta-video-che-sbugiarda-conte-1746983.html \"Non sono dei 5 Stelle\", ma spunta un video \u200bche sbugiarda Conte], ''Il Giornale''</ref> He also added that today \"the ideological schemes of the 20th century are no longer adequate to represent the current [[political system]]\" and it should be \"more important and correct to evaluate the work of a political force on how it is positioned on the respect of fundamental [[Human rights|rights]] and freedoms\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-ecco-chi-e-il-nome-piu-quotato-per-guidare-il-governo-lega-m5s/4369287/|title=Giuseppe Conte, ecco chi \u00e8 il presidente del consiglio del governo Lega-M5s|date=31 May 2018|work=Il Fatto Quotidiano|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180527064732/https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-ecco-chi-e-il-nome-piu-quotato-per-guidare-il-governo-lega-m5s/4369287/|archive-date=27 May 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn his inaugural speech at the Senate on 5 June 2018,<ref name=\"rep_050618\">{{cite web|title=Il discorso di Conte in Senato, la versione integrale|url=http://download.repubblica.it/pdf/2018/politica/presidente05062018.pdf|work=[[la Repubblica]]|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191215113342/http://download.repubblica.it/pdf/2018/politica/presidente05062018.pdf|archive-date=15 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media|date=5 June 2018|title=Dichiarazioni programmatiche - L'intervento del Presidente Conte al Senato|medium=official video|language=it|url=http://www.governo.it/media/dichiarazioni-programmatiche/9515|accessdate=1 April 2019|location=Italy|publisher=Governo Italiano - Presidenza del Consiglio dei Ministri|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014835/http://www.governo.it/media/dichiarazioni-programmatiche/9515|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> in response to attacks on government political forces accused of being populist and [[anti-establishment]], Conte replied that \"if populism is the attitude of the ruling class to listen to the people's needs [...] and if anti-establishment means aiming at introducing a new system able to remove old privileges and encrusted power, well, these political forces deserve both these epithets\".<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2018/06/05/world/europe/italy-government-giuseppe-conte.html \"Italy's New Populist Government Articulates Vision, but Few Specifics\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180611190303/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/06/05/world/europe/italy-government-giuseppe-conte.html |date=11 June 2018 }}.</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Highlights: Italian Prime Minister Giuseppe Conte's inaugural speech|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-politics-speech-highlights/highlights-italian-prime-minister-giuseppe-contes-inaugural-speech-idUSKCN1J118M|agency=[[Reuters]]|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402002640/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-politics-speech-highlights/highlights-italian-prime-minister-giuseppe-contes-inaugural-speech-idUSKCN1J118M|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media|date=5 June 2018|title=Conte: \"Noi populisti? Ascoltiamo la gente|medium=video|language=Italian|url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/video/politica/conte-noi-populisti-ascoltiamo-gente-1536881.html|accessdate=1 April 2019|location=Italy|work=[[il Giornale]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014704/http://www.ilgiornale.it/video/politica/conte-noi-populisti-ascoltiamo-gente-1536881.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nHe also opposed the \"hypertrophy of Italian laws\", advocating the repeal of useless laws and supported a simplification of [[bureaucracy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/primopiano/politica/conte_premier_governo_m5s_lega-3744907.html|date=21 May 2018|author=Diodato Pirone|title=Conte, giurista anti-burocrazia con un passato a sinistra|trans-title=Conte, former anti-bureaucracy lawyer joins the left|work=[[Il Messaggero]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014743/https://www.ilmessaggero.it/primopiano/politica/conte_premier_governo_m5s_lega-3744907.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> As a professor, Conte strongly opposed the [[school reform]] legislation promoted by [[Matteo Renzi]]'s government in 2015, known as \"The Good School\", which, according to him, must be completely revised.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.orizzontescuola.it/giuseppe-conte-rivedere-pressoche-integralmente-la-riforma-della-cattiva-scuola/|title=Giuseppe Conte: rivedere, pressoch\u00e9 integralmente, la riforma della cattiva scuola|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014725/https://www.orizzontescuola.it/giuseppe-conte-rivedere-pressoche-integralmente-la-riforma-della-cattiva-scuola/|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAccording to public opinion surveys, Conte's approval rating was always above 50% during all his first cabinet, then dropping to 40% in the early months of his second government.<ref>[https://www.youtrend.it/2020/03/20/sondaggio-demos-gradimento-per-conte-alle-stelle/ Sondaggio Demos: gradimento per Conte alle stelle], ''YouTrend''</ref> However, in March 2020, amid the coronavirus crisis, his approval rating rose to 71%, one of the highest rating ever for an Italian Prime Minister.<ref>[https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/19/coronavirus-fiducia-record-per-conte-e-il-governo-hanno-il-sostegno-di-7-italiani-su-10-tra-i-leader-zaia-piace-piu-di-salvini/5741739/ Coronavirus, fiducia record per Conte e il governo: hanno il sostegno di 7 italiani su 10. Tra i leader Zaia piace pi\u00f9 di Salvini], ''Il Fatto Quotidiano''</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nGiuseppe Conte married Valentina Fico, a lawyer from [[Rome]] and daughter of a former director of the Santa Cecilia [[music school|conservatory]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.donnemagazine.it/giuseppe-conte-moglie/|title=Valentina Fico, chi \u00e8 l'ex moglie di Giuseppe Conte|first=Olga|last=Luce|date=29 August 2019|website=Donne Magazine|access-date=10 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324011119/https://www.donnemagazine.it/giuseppe-conte-moglie/|archive-date=24 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> They have a child, Niccol\u00f2, born in 2007.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.it/news/politica/2018/05/21/giuseppe-conte-chi-e-il-professore-di-sinistra-chiamato-a-fare-il-premier|title=Giuseppe Conte, chi \u00e8 il professore (di sinistra) che potrebbe diventare premier|date=21 May 2018|access-date=10 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724085132/https://www.vanityfair.it/news/politica/2018/05/21/giuseppe-conte-chi-e-il-professore-di-sinistra-chiamato-a-fare-il-premier|archive-date=24 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> However, they divorced after a few years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://social.excite.it/Attualita/Politica/Ecco-chi-e-l-ex-moglie-di-Giuseppe-Conte|title=Ecco chi \u00e8 l'ex moglie di Giuseppe Conte|website=Excite}}</ref> Conte is currently engaged with Olivia Paladino (born 1979),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://social.excite.it/Attualita/Politica/Ecco-chi-e-Olivia-Paladino-l-affascinante-fidanzata-del-premier-Conte|title=Ecco chi \u00e8 Olivia Paladino, l'affascinante fidanzata del premier Conte|website=Excite}}</ref> daughter of the Roman entrepreneur Cesare Paladino and the [[Sweden|Swedish]] actress [[Ewa Aulin]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.letteradonna.it/it/articoli/ritratti/2018/06/04/giuseppe-conte-compagna-olivia-paladino/26009/|title=Chi \u00e8 Olivia Paladino, la compagna del premier Giuseppe Conte - LetteraDonna|access-date=10 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612144331/https://www.letteradonna.it/it/articoli/ritratti/2018/06/04/giuseppe-conte-compagna-olivia-paladino/26009/|archive-date=12 June 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nConte is an avid supporter of [[A.S. Roma]], a passion that arose when he studied in [[Rome]] at the Sapienza University.<ref>[https://www.tpi.it/news/giuseppe-conte-squadra-calcio-20180606128675/ Quali sono le squadre del cuore di Giuseppe Conte e degli ex premier italiani], TPI</ref>\n\nHe is a [[Roman Catholic]] and a devout votary to [[Padre Pio|Padre Pio of Pietrelcina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/devoto-padre-pio-secchione-e-sinistra-financial-times-1530345.html|title=Devoto di Padre Pio, secchione e di sinistra. Il \"Financial Times\" lo stronca: un novellino|work=il Giornale|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014716/http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/devoto-padre-pio-secchione-e-sinistra-financial-times-1530345.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte Quirinale 2019.jpg|thumb|220px|Giuseppe Conte in August 2019]]\nOn 21 May 2018, when Conte was proposed to President Mattarella as candidate for prime minister,<ref name=bbc/> ''[[The New York Times]]'' questioned his summer stays at [[New York University]] (NYU) listed in his official [[curriculum vitae]]<ref name=cv/> in an article asserting that a NYU spokeswoman could not find Conte in university \"records as either a student or faculty member\".<ref name=nyt/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/22/giuseppe-conte-nyt-nel-cv-studi-alla-new-york-university-non-risultano-allateneo-accademici-visiting-scholar-non-sono-registrati/4372768/|title=Giuseppe Conte, Nyt: \"Nel cv studi alla New York University che non-risultano all'ateneo\". Accademici: \"Visiting scholar non-sono registrati\"|work=Il Fatto Quotidiano|date=22 May 2018|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233208/https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/22/giuseppe-conte-nyt-nel-cv-studi-alla-new-york-university-non-risultano-allateneo-accademici-visiting-scholar-non-sono-registrati/4372768/|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Similar doubts arose concerning his study period in France at the [[Sorbonne University]].<ref name=theguardian>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/may/22/italy-giuseppe-conte-cv-new-york-university|title=Doubts raised over academic credentials of proposed Italian PM|author=Kirchgaessner, Stephanie|author2=Giuffrida, Angela|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328231104/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/may/22/italy-giuseppe-conte-cv-new-york-university|archive-date=28 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe following day, the [[Associated Press]] reported in an article published also by ''The New York Times'' that the NYU spokeswoman added that \"while Mr. Conte had no official status at NYU, he was granted permission to conduct research in the NYU law library\" during the period listed in his official curriculum vitae.<ref name=cv/><ref>{{cite news|title=The Latest: Italy PM pick had 'no official status' at NYU|url=https://www.apnews.com/d7e4f88200524150806030baec55b919|agency=Associated Press|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328231037/https://www.apnews.com/d7e4f88200524150806030baec55b919|archive-date=28 March 2019|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite news|title=The Latest: Italy PM pick had 'no official status' at NYU|url=https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2018/05/22/world/europe/ap-eu-italy-politics-the-latest.html|work=The New York Times|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Similarly, the [[Duquesne University]] of [[Pittsburgh]] and the [[University of Malta]] found no record of him in their archives,<ref>{{cite news|author1=Lorenzo De Cicco|author2=Francesca Pierantozzi|author3=Flavio Pompetti|date=22 May 2018|title=Conte, dopo New York anche le universit\u00e0 di Malta e Pittsburgh: \"Non ha mai studiato o insegnato ufficialmente qui\"|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/primopiano/politica/giuseppe_conte_curriculum_universita_pittsburgh-3748598.html|work=Il Messaggero|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329025146/https://www.ilmessaggero.it/primopiano/politica/giuseppe_conte_curriculum_universita_pittsburgh-3748598.html|archive-date=29 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> although it was confirmed that Conte held lectures at the old university building in [[Valletta]], Malta, for the Foundation for International Studies.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20180522/local/did-italys-prime-minister-candidate-lecture-in-Malta.679733|title=Italian prime minister candidate says he lectured in Malta - but the University has no record of him|newspaper=Times of Malta|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329002409/https://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20180522/local/did-italys-prime-minister-candidate-lecture-in-Malta.679733|archive-date=29 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Yale University]], contacted by another newspaper, confirmed that he was a visiting scholar there for three months.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_25/conte-curriculum-yale-conferma-visiting-scholar-tre-mesi-eabf3c82-5fa7-11e8-989a-8761ed483ece.shtml|title=Conte e il curriculum, Yale conferma: \"Visiting scholar per tre mesi\"|author=Sarcina, Giuseppe|work=Corriere della Sera|date=25 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612140217/https://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_25/conte-curriculum-yale-conferma-visiting-scholar-tre-mesi-eabf3c82-5fa7-11e8-989a-8761ed483ece.shtml|archive-date=12 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nMoreover, Conte stated in his CV that he had worked for his legal studies at the Kulturinstitut in [[Vienna]], Austria, but this is a language school, not a law school.<ref name=theguardian/>\n\n==Authored books==\n*{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gpBBDwAAQBAJ|title=Il volontariato. Libert\u00e0 dei privati e mediazione giuridica dello Stato|last=Conte|first=Giuseppe|last2=Landini|first2=Sara|year=1996|isbn=9788899459772|publisher=Pioda|location=[[Rome]]|author-mask=with}}\n*{{cite book|title=Matrimonio civile e teoria della simulazione|year=1996|publisher=Pioda|location=[[Rome]]|oclc=1088868085}}\n*{{cite book|title=La simulazione del matrimonio nella teoria del negozio giuridico|year=1999|isbn=9788813220068|publisher=CEDAM|location=[[Padua]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=Le regole della solidarit\u00e0. Iniziative non-profit dei privati e mediazione dei pubblici poteri|year=2001|publisher=Pioda|location=[[Rome]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=Il danno non-patrimoniale|year=2018|publisher=Giuffr\u00e8|location=[[Milan]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=La formazione del contratto|year=2018|isbn=9788814203770|publisher=Giuffr\u00e8|location=[[Milan]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=L'impresa responsabile|year=2018|isbn=9788814227035|publisher=Giuffr\u00e8|location=[[Milan]]}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Commons category}}\n*University of Florence [https://www.unifi.it/p-doc2-2016-0-A-2b333b2d322c-1.html personal page] (including CV and publication list in English)\n*{{Scopus id}}\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Paolo Gentiloni]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Prime Minister of Italy]]|years=2018\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-prec|italy}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Roberto Fico]]|as=[[List of Presidents of the Italian Chamber of Deputies|President of the Chamber of Deputies]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Italian order of precedence|Order of precedence of Italy]]<br />''{{small|as Prime Minister}}''|years=}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Marta Cartabia]]<br />''{{small|{{nowrap|as [[Constitutional Court of Italy|President of the Constitutional Court]]}}}}''}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Prime Ministers of Italy}}\n{{Offices of italy}}\n{{European Council}}\n{{Current NATO leaders}}\n{{Current G8 Leaders}}\n{{Current G20 Leaders}}\n{{Conte I Cabinet}}\n{{Conte II Cabinet}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Conte, Giuseppe}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:Conte I Cabinet]]\n[[Category:Conte II Cabinet]]\n[[Category:Italian jurists]]\n[[Category:Italian Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Foggia]]\n[[Category:Prime Ministers of Italy]]\n[[Category:Roma Tre University faculty]]\n[[Category:Sapienza University of Rome alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Florence faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Malta faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Sassari faculty]]\n[[Category:Yale Law School alumni]]\n[[Category:Independent politicians in Italy]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-blp|small=yes}}\n{{short description|58th Prime Minister of Italy}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name                = Giuseppe Conte\n| image               = Giuseppe Conte Official.jpg\n| office              = 58th [[Prime Minister of Italy]]\n| president           = [[Sergio Mattarella]]\n| deputy              = [[Luigi Di Maio]] {{small|(2018\u201319)}}<br/>[[Matteo Salvini]] {{small|(2018\u201319)}}\n| term_start          = 1 June 2018\n| term_end            = \n| predecessor         = [[Paolo Gentiloni]]\n| successor           = \n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1964|8|8|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Volturara Appula]], [[Apulia]], Italy\n| death_date          = \n| death_place         = \n| party               = [[Independent politician|Independent]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.agi.it/politica/giuseppe_conte_rassegna_stampa-3931524/news/2018-05-22/ |title=Il premier tecnico di un governo politico\". Cosa dicono i giornali |publisher=AGI \u2013 Agenzia Giornalistica Italia |date=22 May 2018 |accessdate=1 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180913144204/https://www.agi.it/politica/giuseppe_conte_rassegna_stampa-3931524/news/2018-05-22/ |archive-date=13 September 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| spouse              = Valentina Fico ({{abbr|div.|divorced}})<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.today.it/donna/trend/giuseppe-conte-ex-moglie-chi-e-valentina.html |author=Donatella Polito |title=Valentina, chi \u00e8 l'ex moglie di Giuseppe Conte |trans-title=Valentina, who is the former wife of Giuseppe Conte |date=24 May 2018 |accessdate=1 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180712111930/http://www.today.it/donna/trend/giuseppe-conte-ex-moglie-chi-e-valentina.html |archive-date=12 July 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| partner             = Olivia Paladino<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/sfoglio/13343184/giuseppe-conte-olivia-paladino-giovane-fidanzata-bellissima-figlia-padrone-hotel-plaza.html |title=Giuseppe Conte, la sua fidanzata? Olivia Paladino: bellissima e biondissima, \u00e8 la figlia del proprietario dell'Hotel Plaza |trans-title=Who is Giuseppe Conte's girlfriend? Olivia Paladino: Beautiful and very blond, she is the daughter of the owner of the Hotel Plaza |work=[[Libero (newspaper)|Libero]] |date=25 May 2018 |accessdate=1 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224016/https://www.liberoquotidiano.it/news/sfoglio/13343184/giuseppe-conte-olivia-paladino-giovane-fidanzata-bellissima-figlia-padrone-hotel-plaza.html |archive-date=1 April 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n| children            = 1\n| residence           = [[Chigi Palace]]\n| education           = [[Sapienza University of Rome|Sapienza University]]\n| website             = {{url|governo.it/il-presidente|Official website}}\n| signature           = Giuseppe Conte signature 2.svg\n}}\n{{Giuseppe Conte sidebar}}\n\n'''Giuseppe Conte''' ({{IPA-it|d\u0292u\u02c8z\u025bppe \u02c8konte}}; born 8 August 1964) is an Italian [[jurist]] and [[politician]] who has served as the [[List of Prime Ministers of Italy|58th]] [[Prime Minister of Italy]] since June 2018.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/31/ci-sono-tutte-le-condizioni-per-un-governo-m5s-lega_a_23448003/|title=Raggiunto l'accordo per un governo M5S-Lega con Conte premier|trans-title=Agreement is reached for an M5S-Lega government with premier Conte|language=it|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014829/https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/31/ci-sono-tutte-le-condizioni-per-un-governo-m5s-lega_a_23448003/|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nConte spent the majority of his career as a [[private law|law]] [[professor]] and was also a member of the Italian Bureau of Administrative Justice. Following the inconclusive [[Italian general election, 2018|2018 general election]], Conte was proposed as the potential independent leader of a coalition government between the [[Five Star Movement]] (M5S) and the [[Lega Nord|League]], despite his very low public profile nationally.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-44223034|title=Novice to lead Italian populist cabinet|date=23 May 2018|publisher=[[BBC News]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401112700/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-44223034|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> After both parties agreed to a [[Conte I Cabinet|programme for government]], Conte was sworn in as Prime Minister on 1 June by [[President of Italy|President]] [[Sergio Mattarella]], immediately appointing the M5S and League leaders as his deputies.<ref>{{cite news |title=M5S and League agree contract for Italy's 'government of change' |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20180517/m5s-league-contract-italy-government-of-change |accessdate=5 September 2019 |work=thelocal.it |date=17 May 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190905092124/https://www.thelocal.it/20180517/m5s-league-contract-italy-government-of-change |archive-date=5 September 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-31/governo-contatti-maio-salvini-ipotesi-ciocca-all-economia-e-savona-esteri-083656.shtml?uuid=AEnWsmxE|title=Giuramento governo: alle 16 Conte e i ministri al Quirinale|work=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401070024/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-31/governo-contatti-maio-salvini-ipotesi-ciocca-all-economia-e-savona-esteri-083656.shtml?uuid=AEnWsmxE|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nHe became the first Italian Prime Minister without prior political office since [[Silvio Berlusconi]] in 1994, as well as the first from [[Southern Italy]] since [[Ciriaco De Mita]] in 1989.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tpi.it/2018/05/25/conte-premier-non-eletto/|title=Da Renzi a Conte: ecco chi sono i presidenti del Consiglio non-eletti in parlamento|author=Luca Serafini|date=25 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401070054/https://www.tpi.it/2018/05/25/conte-premier-non-eletto/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-23/l-incarico-torna-sud-roma-trent-anni-132910.shtml?uuid=AEToqGtE|title=Da De Mita a Conte, l'incarico torna a sud di Roma dopo trent'anni|work=Il Sole 24 Ore|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401070020/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-23/l-incarico-torna-sud-roma-trent-anni-132910.shtml?uuid=AEToqGtE|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The first Conte Cabinet was described by many publications, such as ''[[The New York Times]]'' and ''[[la Repubblica]]'', as the \"first modern populist government in [[Western Europe]]\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/politica/2018/05/11/italia-primo-regime-populista-europa-occidentale_ACfIrXYfVRuN9kbkERbm1L.html|title=Italia primo governo populista in Europa occidentale|agency=[[Adnkronos]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401043020/https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/politica/2018/05/11/italia-primo-regime-populista-europa-occidentale_ACfIrXYfVRuN9kbkERbm1L.html|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://eu.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2018/05/22/giuseppe-conte-italy-prime-minister/632744002/|author=Eric J. Lyman|title=Giuseppe Conte: Italy's next PM to form western Europe's first populist government|work=[[USA Today]]|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724043047/https://eu.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2018/05/22/giuseppe-conte-italy-prime-minister/632744002/|archive-date=24 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/24/opinion/populists-rome-five-star-movement.html|title=Opinion \u2013 The Populists Take Rome|date=24 May 2018|work=[[The New York Times]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|via=NYTimes.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401070043/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/24/opinion/populists-rome-five-star-movement.html|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 20 August 2019, Conte offered to resign as Prime Minister when the League filed a motion of no confidence in the coalition government.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Borrelli |first1=Silvia Sciorilli |title=Matteo Salvini calls confidence vote in Italian PM |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/italy-salvini-calls-confidence-vote-in-pm-conte/ |accessdate=5 September 2019 |work=POLITICO |date=9 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816182951/https://www.politico.eu/article/italy-salvini-calls-confidence-vote-in-pm-conte/ |archive-date=16 August 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=guardian_resignation /> Subsequently, the M5S and the centre-left [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] agreed to form a [[Conte II Cabinet|new government]], with Conte remaining as Prime Minister.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/notizia_3228466201902a.shtml|title=Consultazioni, Mattarella convoca Conte per gioved\u00ec mattina: il premier al Colle alle 09:30|website=Tgcom24|access-date=29 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828181939/https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/notizia_3228466201902a.shtml|archive-date=28 August 2019|url-status=dead}}</ref> In the process, Conte became the first Italian Prime Minister to lead separate governments with both right-wing and left-wing coalition partners.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://formiche.net/2019/09/conte-sinistra-destra-presidentissimo-antonucci/|title=Da sinistra a destra, Conte fa (bene) il presidentissimo. Analisi di Antonucci|first=Maria Cristina|last=Antonucci|date=21 September 2019|website=Formiche.net|access-date=24 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191028052442/https://formiche.net/2019/09/conte-sinistra-destra-presidentissimo-antonucci/|archive-date=28 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.iltempo.it/politica/2019/09/18/news/governo-giallorosso-conte-renzi-news-m5s-pd-mastella-trasformismo-1210557/|title=Conte? Campione di trasformismo|website=www.iltempo.it|access-date=24 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191024101345/https://www.iltempo.it/politica/2019/09/18/news/governo-giallorosso-conte-renzi-news-m5s-pd-mastella-trasformismo-1210557/|archive-date=24 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nConte has often been nicknamed \"the lawyer of the people\" (''l'avvocato del popolo''), as he also defined himself during his first speech as prime minister.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/un-anno-e-mezzo-conte-avvocato-popolo-garante-contratto-gialloverde-leader-ACBFGTg|title=Conte bis? I 15 mesi a palazzo Chigi dell' \"avvocato del popolo\" diventato leader politico|website=Il Sole 24 ORE|access-date=28 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828073111/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/un-anno-e-mezzo-conte-avvocato-popolo-garante-contratto-gialloverde-leader-ACBFGTg|archive-date=28 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/photogallery/primopiano/2019/08/20/giuseppe-conte-lavvocato-degli-italiani-_80d2deb1-d864-4c8b-a0bc-29a34a543218.html|title=Conte, l'avvocato del popolo strapazza il capitano - Primopiano|date=20 August 2019|website=ANSA.it|access-date=28 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825073909/http://www.ansa.it/sito/photogallery/primopiano/2019/08/20/giuseppe-conte-lavvocato-degli-italiani-_80d2deb1-d864-4c8b-a0bc-29a34a543218.html|archive-date=25 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and career==\nConte was born on 8 August 1964 into a [[middle class]] family at [[Volturara Appula]], near [[Foggia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-prof-anti-burocrazia-con-un-passato-a-sinistra_32a616ac-8e32-4b2f-8788-5e63912bbca3.html|title=Giuseppe Conte, legalit\u00e0 e semplificazione le sue parole d'ordine \u2013 Politica|date=20 May 2018|agency=[[Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401054423/http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-prof-anti-burocrazia-con-un-passato-a-sinistra_32a616ac-8e32-4b2f-8788-5e63912bbca3.html|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/puglia/notizie/2018/05/21/governo-conte-il-bambino-prodigio-legatissimo-a-volturara_03b14393-6ff3-451d-8ed7-8163ac6f0135.html|title=Governo: Conte, il 'bambino prodigio' legatissimo a Volturara \u2013 Puglia|date=21 May 2018|agency=Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233048/http://www.ansa.it/puglia/notizie/2018/05/21/governo-conte-il-bambino-prodigio-legatissimo-a-volturara_03b14393-6ff3-451d-8ed7-8163ac6f0135.html|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> His father Nicola was a public employee in the local [[municipality]], while his mother Lillina Roberti was an [[elementary school]] teacher.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_21/chi-giuseppe-conte-premier-che-viene-periferia-2d4fe228-5d18-11e8-9df6-a1f7c25f6df9_preview.shtml?reason=unauthenticated&cat=1&cid=Lalukfqy&pids=FR&origin=http://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_21/chi-giuseppe-conte-premier-che-viene-periferia-2d4fe228-5d18-11e8-9df6-a1f7c25f6df9.shtml|title=Chi \u00e8 Giuseppe Conte, il premier che \"viene dalla periferia\" \u2013 Video|author=Borrillo, Michelangelo|work=[[Corriere della Sera]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401070111/https://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_21/chi-giuseppe-conte-premier-che-viene-periferia-2d4fe228-5d18-11e8-9df6-a1f7c25f6df9_preview.shtml?reason=unauthenticated&cat=1&cid=Lalukfqy&pids=FR&origin=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.corriere.it%2Fpolitica%2F18_maggio_21%2Fchi-giuseppe-conte-premier-che-viene-periferia-2d4fe228-5d18-11e8-9df6-a1f7c25f6df9.shtml|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/21/studioso-e-riservato-e-molto-devoto-a-padre-pio-il-racconto-del-miglior-amico-del-premier-conte_a_23440002/|title=Studioso e riservato, e molto devoto a Padre Pio\". Il racconto del miglior amico del \"premier\" Conte|date=21 May 2018|work=[[HuffPost]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330221438/https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/21/studioso-e-riservato-e-molto-devoto-a-padre-pio-il-racconto-del-miglior-amico-del-premier-conte_a_23440002/|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAfter his family moved to [[San Giovanni Rotondo]], Conte attended the [[Liceo classico|Classical Lyceum]] \"[[Pietro Giannone]]\" near [[San Marco in Lamis]] and then studied law at the [[Sapienza University of Rome]], where he graduated in 1988 with honors.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://bari.repubblica.it/cronaca/2018/05/21/news/palazzo_chigi_a_volturara_e_a_san_giovanni_rotondo_fanno_il_tifo_per_il_nuovo_premier_conte-197020155/|title=Governo, a Volturara e a San Giovanni Rotondo nelle citt\u00e0 che fanno il tifo per Conte|date=21 May 2018|work=[[la Repubblica]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401043017/https://bari.repubblica.it/cronaca/2018/05/21/news/palazzo_chigi_a_volturara_e_a_san_giovanni_rotondo_fanno_il_tifo_per_il_nuovo_premier_conte-197020155/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=civilisti/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sanmarcoinlamis.org/sito/gargano/4137-il-candidato-alla-presidenza-del-governo-e-uno-di-noi-sul-gargano|title=Il candidato alla Presidenza del Governo \u00e8 uno di noi...|date=23 May 2018|website=SanMarcoinLamis.eu|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401043020/https://www.sanmarcoinlamis.org/sito/gargano/4137-il-candidato-alla-presidenza-del-governo-e-uno-di-noi-sul-gargano|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> For a short terms, Conte studied abroad. In 1992, he moved to the [[United States]] to study at [[Yale Law School]] and [[Duquesne University]] and at the [[Internationales Kulturinstitut|International Culture Institute]] in [[Vienna]] in 1993. He later researched or lectured at [[Sorbonne University]] in 2000, [[Girton College, Cambridge]] in 2001 and [[New York University]] in 2008.<ref name=cv>{{cite web|url=http://www.camera.it/application/xmanager/projects/leg17/file/ufficio_stampa/Tutti_i_Curricula.pdf|date=17 September 2013|title=Curricula dei candidati alle elezioni a componente del Consiglio di Presidenza della Giustizia Amministrativa|website=Camera dei deputati|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181208001035/http://www.camera.it/application/xmanager/projects/leg17/file/ufficio_stampa/Tutti_i_Curricula.pdf|archive-date=8 December 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-chi-e-il-favorito-per-la-premiership-nel-governo-m5s-lega_a_23439294/|title=Giuseppe Conte, avvocato civilista e \"sburocratizzatore\". Ecco chi \u00e8 il premier indicato da M5S e Lega a Mattarella|date=20 May 2018|work=HuffPost|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401093507/https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-chi-e-il-favorito-per-la-premiership-nel-governo-m5s-lega_a_23439294/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nHe started his academic career during the 1990s, when he taught at [[Roma Tre University]], at [[Libera Universit\u00e0 Maria SS. Assunta|LUMSA University]] in Rome, at the [[University of Malta]] and at the [[University of Sassari]].<ref name=\"civilisti\">{{cite web|url=https://www.civilistiitaliani.eu/soci/soci-effettivi/200-conte-giuseppe|title=Conte Giuseppe|author=Carlo Michele Cortellessa|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014929/https://www.civilistiitaliani.eu/soci/soci-effettivi/200-conte-giuseppe|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Conte is currently professor of [[private law]] at the [[University of Florence]] and at [[Libera Universit\u00e0 Internazionale degli Studi Sociali Guido Carli|LUISS]] of Rome.<ref>[https://www.unifi.it/p-doc2-2016-0-A-2b333b2d322c-1.html \"Giuseppe Conte\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180522070647/https://www.unifi.it/p-doc2-2016-0-A-2b333b2d322c-1.html |date=22 May 2018 }}.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://docenti.luiss.it/diritto-privato-conte/|title=Diritto Privato \u2013 LUISS Guido Carli|website=docenti.luiss.it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014838/http://docenti.luiss.it/diritto-privato-conte/|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> He sits on the [[board of trustees]] of [[John Cabot University]] in Rome.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://news.johncabot.edu/2018/05/jcu-trustee-giuseppe-conte-italian-prime-minister/|title=John Cabot Trustee Giuseppe Conte Named New Italian Prime Minister|date=24 May 2018|publisher=John Cabot University|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014649/https://news.johncabot.edu/2018/05/jcu-trustee-giuseppe-conte-italian-prime-minister/|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2010 and 2011, Conte served on the [[board of directors]] of the [[Italian Space Agency]] (ASI) and in 2012 he was appointed by the [[Bank of Italy]] as a member of the \"Banking and Financial [[Arbitrage]]\" commission.<ref>[http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/giuseppe-conte/ Giuseppe Conte] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190919172354/http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/giuseppe-conte/ |date=19 September 2019 }}, Enciclopedia Treccani</ref> He served also in scientific committee of the Italian Foundation of [[Notaries]].<ref>[https://www.fondazionenotariato.it/progetti.html Progetti] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191001183935/http://www.fondazionenotariato.it/progetti.html |date=1 October 2019 }}, ''Fondazione Italiana del Notariato''</ref>\n\nOn 18 September 2013, he was elected by the [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]] as a member of the Bureau of Administrative Justice, the self-governing body of administrative magistrates, of which he served also as vice president.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.camera.it/leg17/1132?shadow_primapagina=3150|title=Eletti i componenti dei Consigli di presidenza della Giustizia amministrativa, della Corte dei conti, della Giustizia tributaria|website=Camera dei deputati|date=18 September 2013|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402051232/http://www.camera.it/leg17/1132?shadow_primapagina=3150|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Prime Minister of Italy==\n=== 2018 government formation===\n{{Main|2018 Italian government formation}}\n[[File:Sergio Mattarella and Giuseppe Conte.jpg|thumb|left|220px|Conte with [[President of the Italian Republic|President]] [[Sergio Mattarella]] at the [[Quirinal Palace]] ]]\nIn February 2018, Conte was selected by [[Luigi Di Maio]], leader of the [[Five Star Movement]] (M5S), as the future possible Minister of Public Administration in his cabinet following the [[2018 Italian general election|2018 general election]].<ref>{{cite news|work=[[Il Giornale]]|url=https://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/ecco-tutti-i-ministri-governo-movimento-5-stelle-1500068.html|title=Ecco tutti i \"ministri\" del governo del Movimento 5 Stelle|author=Chiara Sarra|date=1 March 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612235128/http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/ecco-tutti-i-ministri-governo-movimento-5-stelle-1500068.html|archive-date=12 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> However, the election resulted in a [[hung parliament]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/elezioni-2018/notizie/elezioni-2018-exit-poll-risultati-proiezioni-spoglio-eb21387e-1ff1-11e8-a09a-92b478235f6f.shtml|title=Elezioni 2018: M5S primo partito, nel centrodestra la Lega supera FI|author=Alessandro Sala|work=[[Corriere della Sera]]|date=4 March 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328131021/https://www.corriere.it/elezioni-2018/notizie/elezioni-2018-exit-poll-risultati-proiezioni-spoglio-eb21387e-1ff1-11e8-a09a-92b478235f6f.shtml|archive-date=28 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> with the M5S that became the party with the largest number of votes and of parliamentary seats while the [[centre-right coalition]], led by [[Matteo Salvini]]'s [[Lega Nord|League]] and other right-wing parties, emerged with a [[Plurality (voting)|plurality]] of seats in the Chamber of Deputies and in the Senate. The centre-left coalition led by former [[Prime Minister of Italy|Prime Minister]] [[Matteo Renzi]] came in third.<ref>{{cite news|author=Piera Matteucchi|url=https://www.repubblica.it/speciali/politica/elezioni2018/2018/03/04/news/risultati_elezioni_politiche_pd_centrodestra_m5s_fi_lega-190424815/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I0-C12-P1-S1.12-T1|title=Elezioni politiche: vincono M5s e Lega. Crollo del Partito democratico. Centrodestra prima coalizione. Il Carroccio sorpassa Forza Italia|work=la Repubblica|date=4 March 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014841/https://www.repubblica.it/speciali/politica/elezioni2018/2018/03/04/news/risultati_elezioni_politiche_pd_centrodestra_m5s_fi_lega-190424815/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I0-C12-P1-S1.12-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 9 May after weeks of political deadlock and the failure of various attempts of forming cabinets both between M5S\u2013[[Centre-right coalition|Centre-right]] and M5S\u2013[[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]], Di Maio and Salvini responded to President [[Sergio Mattarella]]'s ultimatum to appoint a neutral technocratic caretaker government by officially requesting that he allow them 24 more hours to achieve a governing agreement between their two parties.<ref>{{cite news|title=Mattarella postpones choice of caretaker premier amid new coalition govt talks|url=https://www.adnkronos.com/aki-en/politics/2018/05/09/mattarella-postpones-choice-caretaker-premier-amid-new-coalition-govt-talks_k6w71PMdtP04WhQ35gsF0I.html|agency=[[Adnkronos]]|date=9 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224018/https://www.adnkronos.com/aki-en/politics/2018/05/09/mattarella-postpones-choice-caretaker-premier-amid-new-coalition-govt-talks_k6w71PMdtP04WhQ35gsF0I.html|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ft.com/content/b253e5a4-53a0-11e8-b3ee-41e0209208ec|newspaper=Financial Times|accessdate=1 April 2019|date=9 May 2018|title=Italy's populist parties given 24 hours to avert fresh elections|url-access=subscription|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014725/https://www.ft.com/content/b253e5a4-53a0-11e8-b3ee-41e0209208ec|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Later that same day in the evening, [[Silvio Berlusconi]] publicly announced [[Forza Italia (2013)|Forza Italia]] would not support a M5S\u2013League government on a vote of confidence, but he would still maintain the centre-right alliance nonetheless, thus opening the doors to a possible majority government between the two parties.<ref>{{cite news|author=Paolo Gallori|author2=Monica Rubino|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/09/news/governo_salvini_ci_provero_fino_all_ultimo_-195890439/|newspaper=la Repubblica|publisher=GEDI Gruppo Editoriale|accessdate=1 April 2019|date=9 May 2018|title=Governo M5S-Lega, Berlusconi: nessun veto all'intesa ma no alla fiducia|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401225556/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/09/news/governo_salvini_ci_provero_fino_all_ultimo_-195890439/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 May, M5S and League reached an agreement in principle on a government program, likely clearing the way for the formation of a governing coalition between the two parties, but could not find an agreement regarding the members of a government cabinet, most importantly the Prime Minister. M5S and League leaders met with [[President of Italy|President]] [[Sergio Mattarella]] on 14 May to guide the formation of a new government.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.marketwatch.com/story/italys-populist-5-star-league-parties-reach-deal-on-government-program-2018-05-13|author=Giovanni Legorano|website=MarketWatch|date=13 May 2018|title=Italy's populist 5 Star, League parties reach deal on government program|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014729/https://www.marketwatch.com/story/italys-populist-5-star-league-parties-reach-deal-on-government-program-2018-05-13|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On their meeting with President Mattarella, both parties asked for an additional week of negotiations to agree on a detailed government program and a Prime Minister to lead the joint government. Both M5S and the League announced their intention to ask their respective members to vote on the government agreement by the weekend.<ref name=\"rai\">{{cite news|url=http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Giuseppe-Conte-un-giurista-per-il-governo-del-cambiamento-LEga-M5S-DI-Maio-premier-un-amico-del-popolo-59393a99-ea98-40d0-91bf-f915e9d5127c.html|title=Giuseppe Conte, un giurista per governo del cambiamento. Di Maio: Premier sar\u00e0 un amico del popolo|date=21 May 2018|work=RAInews|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402003051/http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Giuseppe-Conte-un-giurista-per-il-governo-del-cambiamento-LEga-M5S-DI-Maio-premier-un-amico-del-popolo-59393a99-ea98-40d0-91bf-f915e9d5127c.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/21/news/consultazioni_mattarella_convoca_m5s_alle_17_30_e_lega_alle_18-196958844/?ref=RHPPLF-BL-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|title=M5s e Lega da Mattarella. Di Maio: \"Conte premier di governo politico\". Salvini: \"Interesse italiani al centro|trans-title=[[Five Star Movement|M5s]] & [[Sergio Mattarella|Mattarella]] of Lega, [[Luigi Di Maio|Di Maio]] said 'Conte will be prime minister of a political government|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|newspaper=la Repubblica|publisher=GEDI Gruppo Editoriale|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014756/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/21/news/consultazioni_mattarella_convoca_m5s_alle_17_30_e_lega_alle_18-196958844/?ref=RHPPLF-BL-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 May, Conte was proposed by Di Maio and Salvini for the role of Prime Minister in the [[2018 Italian government formation|2018 Italian government]],<ref>{{cite news|url=https://formiche.net/2018/02/giuseppe-conte-scelto-luigi-maio-la-squadra-governo/|title=Chi \u00e8 Giuseppe Conte, scelto da Luigi Di Maio per la possibile squadra di governo|website=formiche.net|date=28 February 2018|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224020/https://formiche.net/2018/02/giuseppe-conte-scelto-luigi-maio-la-squadra-governo/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=bbc>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-44197351|publisher=BBC News|title=Italy populist government pact: Candidate for prime minister named|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402091842/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-44197351|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|date=21 May 2018|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/may/21/italy-populist-coalition-set-to-name-political-novice-as-pm-nominee|title=Italian president in talks as populist parties put forward novice for PM|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402002652/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/may/21/italy-populist-coalition-set-to-name-political-novice-as-pm-nominee|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> despite reports in the Italian press suggesting that President Mattarella still had significant reservations about the direction of the new government.<ref name=nyt>{{cite news|author=Horowitz, Jason|date=21 May 2018|title=Italy's Populists Offer Giuseppe Conte for Prime Minister; N.Y.U. Claim in Question|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/21/world/europe/italy-government-giuseppe-conte-di-maio.html|work=The New York Times|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233502/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/05/21/world/europe/italy-government-giuseppe-conte-di-maio.html|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 23 May, Conte was invited to the [[Quirinal Palace]] to receive the presidential mandate to form a new cabinet.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://apnews.com/eb60cc0ac97746b1aeb46be2121d9586|title=The Latest: Premier-designate confirms Italy's place in EU|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224015/https://apnews.com/eb60cc0ac97746b1aeb46be2121d9586|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/23/news/governo_conte_torna_in_bilico_tempi_piu_lunghi_mattarella_vuole_riflettere-197118162/?ref=RHPPLF-BL-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|author=Alberto Custodero|author2=Monica Rubino|title=Di Battista all'attacco di Mattarella: \"Non si opponga agli italiani\". La lunga giornata del Colle|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014825/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/23/news/governo_conte_torna_in_bilico_tempi_piu_lunghi_mattarella_vuole_riflettere-197118162/?ref=RHPPLF-BL-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In the traditional statement after the appointment, Conte said that he would be the \"defense lawyer of [[Italians|Italian people]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/governo-mattarella-conferisce-a-conte-l-incarico-saro-l-avvocato-difensore-degli-italiani-_3141680-201802a.shtml|title=Governo, Conte incaricato da Mattarella: \"Sar\u00f2 l'avvocato difensore degli italiani|language=it|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224018/https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/governo-mattarella-conferisce-a-conte-l-incarico-saro-l-avvocato-difensore-degli-italiani-_3141680-201802a.shtml|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte nel corso delle dichiarazioni in occasione del conferimento dell'incarico - 23 maggio 2018.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Conte during a press conference at the [[Quirinal Palace]], after receiving the task of forming a new cabinet]]\nOn 27 May, Conte renounced his office due to contrasts between Salvini and President Mattarella. Salvini proposed the university professor [[Paolo Savona]] as [[Italian Minister of Economy and Finances|Minister of Economy and Finances]], but Mattarella strongly opposed him, considering Savona too [[Eurosceptic]] and [[Anti-Germans (political current)|anti-German]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Tomasso Ciriaco|author2=Annalisa Cuzzocrea|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/27/news/governo_conte_mattarella_savona-197450521/|title=Governo, il giorno della rinuncia di Conte. Ecco come \u00e8 fallita la trattativa su Savona|date=27 May 2018|work=[[la Repubblica]]|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224015/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/27/news/governo_conte_mattarella_savona-197450521/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In his speech after Conte's resignation, Mattarella declared that the two parties wanted to bring Italy out of the [[Eurozone]] and as the guarantor of the Italian Constitution and the country's interest and stability he could not allow this.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/27/lora-piu-buia-di-mattarella-la-scelta-obbligata-di-difendere-linteresse-nazionale-dopo-il-no-dei-partiti-alla-soluzione-giorgetti-per-leconomia_a_23444708/|author=Alessandro De Angelis|title=L'ora pi\u00f9 buia di Mattarella: la scelta obbligata di difendere l'interesse nazionale dopo il no dei partiti alla soluzione Giorgetti per l'Economia|work=[[HuffPost]]|language=it|date=27 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014939/https://www.huffingtonpost.it/2018/05/27/lora-piu-buia-di-mattarella-la-scelta-obbligata-di-difendere-linteresse-nazionale-dopo-il-no-dei-partiti-alla-soluzione-giorgetti-per-leconomia_a_23444708/|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/27/news/governo_dopo_le_minacce_di_impeachment_sui_social_parte_la_solidarieta_a_mattarella-197516727/|author=Serena Riformato|title=Governo, firme e tweet di solidariet\u00e0 a Mattarella. Ma spuntano anche minacce di morte|date=27 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401225607/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/27/news/governo_dopo_le_minacce_di_impeachment_sui_social_parte_la_solidarieta_a_mattarella-197516727/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn the following day, Mattarella gave [[Carlo Cottarelli]], a former director of the [[International Monetary Fund]], the task of forming a new government.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/salvini_radio_capital_centrodestra-197543015/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I0-C12-P1-S1.12-T1|title=Cottarelli accetta l'incarico: \"Senza fiducia il Paese al voto dopo agosto|date=28 May 2018|work=[[la Repubblica]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014818/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/salvini_radio_capital_centrodestra-197543015/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I0-C12-P1-S1.12-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 28 May, the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] (PD) announced that it would abstain from voting the confidence to Cottarelli while the M5S and the center-right parties [[Forza Italia (2013)|Forza Italia]] (FI), [[Brothers of Italy]] (FdI) and the League announced their vote against.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/salvini_se_berlusconi_lo_vota_addio_alleanza_-197549039/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T2|title=Berlusconi: \"No alla fiducia e centrodestra unito al voto\". Ma Salvini: \"Alleanza con Fi? Ci penser\u00f2|date=28 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014848/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/salvini_se_berlusconi_lo_vota_addio_alleanza_-197549039/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T2|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/franceschini_pd_renzi_martina-197570543/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|title=Pd, Martina: \"Fiducia a Cottarelli\". Renzi: \"Salviamo il Paese\". E i dem: manifestazione nazionale a Roma il 1\u00b0 giugno|work=la Repubblica|date=28 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014853/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/28/news/franceschini_pd_renzi_martina-197570543/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nCottarelli was expected to submit his list of ministers for approval to President Mattarella on 29 May. On that and the following day, he held only informal consultations with the President, waiting for the formation of a \"political government\".<ref name=\":1\">{{cite news|url=https://roma.corriere.it/notizie/politica/18_maggio_30/governo-cottarelli-quirinale-mattarella-61982f12-63d6-11e8-9b4c-0d37dd8c9cfa.shtml|author=Giuseppe Gaetano|title=Incontro informale in corso tra Cottarelli e MattarellaI tre scenari possibili|work=[[Corriere della Sera]]|date=30 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190607164923/https://roma.corriere.it/notizie/politica/18_maggio_30/governo-cottarelli-quirinale-mattarella-61982f12-63d6-11e8-9b4c-0d37dd8c9cfa.shtml|archive-date=7 June 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=\":2\">{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/30/news/trattativa_m5s_lega_cottarelli_colle-197707709/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|author=Umberto Rosso|author2=Monica Rubino|title=Governo, Cottarelli vede Mattarella. Ora al lavoro alla Camera. Riparte la trattativa giallo-verde|date=30 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014857/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/30/news/trattativa_m5s_lega_cottarelli_colle-197707709/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Meanwhile, Salvini and Di Maio announced their willingness to restart the negotiations to form a political government and [[Giorgia Meloni]], leader of FdI, gave her support to the initiative.<ref name=\":1\"/><ref name=\":2\"/><ref>{{cite news|author=Alberto Custodero|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/29/news/di_maio_spero_voto_prima_possibile_ma_pronti_a_collaborare_con_mattarella_-197682177/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|title=Di Maio: \"Impeachment non-pi\u00f9 sul tavolo\". E si riapre l'ipotesi di un governo Lega-M5s|date=29 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014801/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/29/news/di_maio_spero_voto_prima_possibile_ma_pronti_a_collaborare_con_mattarella_-197682177/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I0-C12-P2-S1.12-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 31 May, M5S and the League declared of having reached an agreement about forming a new government without Paolo Savona as Finance Minister (he would become Minister of European Affairs instead) and with Conte at its head.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/31/news/governo_m5s_lega-197794180/|author=Carmelo Lopapa|title=Governo, Conte accetta l'incarico e presenta la lista: 18 ministri, 5 le donne. Tria all'Economia|work=la Repubblica|language=it|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401225609/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/31/news/governo_m5s_lega-197794180/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Giuseppe-Conte-riceve-e-accetta-incarico-Presentata-a-Mattarella-la-lista-dei-ministri-1d8b9d38-c0c1-40c1-a6e9-44558da0fe1a.html|title=Nasce il governo Conte. Presentata a Mattarella la lista dei ministri. Di Maio e Salvini vicepremier|agency=[[RaiNews]]|language=it|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402044240/http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Giuseppe-Conte-riceve-e-accetta-incarico-Presentata-a-Mattarella-la-lista-dei-ministri-1d8b9d38-c0c1-40c1-a6e9-44558da0fe1a.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===First Conte Cabinet===\n{{See also|Conte I Cabinet}}\n[[File:Cerimonia di insediamento del Governo Conte 2018.jpg|thumb|Conte with [[Paolo Gentiloni]] during the swearing-in ceremony]]\nOn 1 June 2018, Conte officially succeeded the Democrat [[Paolo Gentiloni]] at the head of the Italian government and was sworn in as the new prime minister in the afternoon.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lastampa.it/2018/05/31/italia/lannuncio-del-quirinale-conte-ha-accettato-lincarico-domani-giuramento-alle-0bBgKEhl0wxOO9g9bpTK1L/pagina.html|title=L'annuncio del Quirinale: \"Conte accetta l'incarico, domani si giura alle 16|work=[[La Stampa]]|date=31 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224019/https://www.lastampa.it/2018/05/31/italia/lannuncio-del-quirinale-conte-ha-accettato-lincarico-domani-giuramento-alle-0bBgKEhl0wxOO9g9bpTK1L/pagina.html|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> His cabinet was predominantly composed of members of the M5S and the League but also of prominent independent [[technocrat]]s like the [[Italian Minister of Foreign Affairs|Minister of Foreign Affairs]] [[Enzo Moavero Milanesi]], who previously served as the minister of European affairs in the government of [[Mario Monti]], the university professor [[Giovanni Tria]] as the [[Italian Minister of Economy and Finances|minister of economy and finances]] and economist [[Paolo Savona]], who served in the cabinet of [[Carlo Azeglio Ciampi]] in the 1990s and is currently known for his [[Eurosceptic]] views, who became the new minister of European affairs.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/31/news/governo_conte_premier_tria_all_economia_milnesi_agli_esteri_savona_alle_politiche_comunitarie-197852722/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P2-S1.8-T1|title=Nasce il governo Conte, Di Maio e Salvini vice. Ecco i ministri dell'esecutivo M5s-Lega|author=Alberto Custodero|date=31 May 2018|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014836/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/05/31/news/governo_conte_premier_tria_all_economia_milnesi_agli_esteri_savona_alle_politiche_comunitarie-197852722/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P2-S1.8-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-31/totoministri-ecco-nuova-squadra-governo-conte-195902.shtml?uuid=AEOyqIyE|author=Nicoletta Cottone|title=Nuovi ministri: la lista completa dell'esecutivo Lega-M5S|work=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014700/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-05-31/totoministri-ecco-nuova-squadra-governo-conte-195902.shtml?uuid=AEOyqIyE|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nBoth parties' leaders Salvini and Di Maio were appointed [[Deputy Prime Minister of Italy|Deputy Prime Ministers]]. While the first became [[Italian Minister of the Interior|Minister of the Interior]], with the main aim of drastically reducing the [[Immigration to Italy|number of illegal immigrants]], the latter served as [[Italian Minister of Economic Development|Minister of Economic Development]], [[Italian Minister of Labour and Social Policies|Labour and Social Policies]] to introduce the [[universal basic income]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/31/governo-conte-ecco-chi-sono-veramente-ministri-dai-politici-come-di-maio-salvini-bonafede-agli-istituzionali-come-moavero-poi-il-prof-di-educazione-fisica-e-il-generale/4381994/|title=Governo Conte, chi sono i ministri: da Di Maio e Salvini (con i fedelissimi) agli \"istituzionali\" come Moavero. Poi il prof di educazione fisica e il generale che indag\u00f2 su Terra dei Fuochi \u2013 Il Fatto Quotidiano|author=M. Castigliani|author2=D. Pretini|work=[[Il Fatto Quotidiano]]|language=it|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.lastampa.it/2018/06/01/italia/nasce-il-governo-legams-salvini-e-di-maio-vice-che-pesano-pi-del-premier-iWRvm6d4yZDNTGt1UQwpOO/pagina.html|title=Nasce il governo Lega-M5S: Salvini e Di Maio vice che pesano pi\u00f9 del premier|work=La Stampa|language=it|date=1 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224017/https://www.lastampa.it/2018/06/01/italia/nasce-il-governo-legams-salvini-e-di-maio-vice-che-pesano-pi-del-premier-iWRvm6d4yZDNTGt1UQwpOO/pagina.html|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe coalition of the two populist parties which Conte led was also known as [[Government of Change]],<ref>{{cite news|author=Luca Romano|date=23 May 2018|url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/premier-incaricato-conte-governo-cambiamento-1531213.html|title=Il premier incaricato Conte: \"Governo del cambiamento\"|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233337/http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/premier-incaricato-conte-governo-cambiamento-1531213.html|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> thanks to a document that summarized the electoral programmes of the two parties, which was called \"Contract for the Government of Change\".<ref>{{cite news|language=it|url=http://espresso.repubblica.it/palazzo/2018/05/18/news/contratto-di-governo-lega-m5s-ecco-il-testo-definitivo-1.322214|title=Contratto di governo Lega-M5s: ecco il testo|work=[[L'espresso]]|publisher=la Repubblica|date=18 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233345/http://espresso.repubblica.it/palazzo/2018/05/18/news/contratto-di-governo-lega-m5s-ecco-il-testo-definitivo-1.322214|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.rt.com/news/427573-italy-pm-euroskeptic-coalition/|title='Government of change': Euroskeptic coalition's choice for Italian PM officially approved|agency=[[RT (TV network)|RT]]|date=23 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233402/https://www.rt.com/news/427573-italy-pm-euroskeptic-coalition/|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte @ the EP (33199171148).jpg|thumb|left|Conte speaks to the [[European Parliament]] in February 2019]]\nDuring his speech before the investiture vote in the [[Italian Senate]] on 5 June, Conte announced his willingness to reduce [[illegal immigration]] and increase the contrast to human traffickers and smugglers. He also advocated a fight against [[political corruption]], the introduction of a law which regulates the [[conflict of interest]]s, a new bill which expands the [[right of self-defense]], a [[tax]]es reduction and a drastic cut to politics's costs, thanks to the [[Annuity|annuities]]' abolition.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/05/news/conte_discorso_fiducia_senato-198193413/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|author=Monica Rubino|title=Conte, il discorso della fiducia: \"Basta business dei migranti, daspo per corrotti e corruttori\". E apre alla Russia|language=it|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014816/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/05/news/conte_discorso_fiducia_senato-198193413/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-06-05/conte-via-discorso-programmatico-quale-conte-chiedera-fiducia--114755.shtml?uuid=AE51Te0E|author=Andrea Gagliardi|author2=Vittorio Nuti|title=Il Governo Conte ottiene la prima fiducia con 171 \"s\u00ec\". Salvini: \"No aumento Iva\"|work=Il Sole 24 Ore|language=it|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014655/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-06-05/conte-via-discorso-programmatico-quale-conte-chiedera-fiducia--114755.shtml?uuid=AE51Te0E|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>[http://www.governo.it/sites/governo.it/files/5giugno2018_Comunicazioni_Conte_Senato.pdf \"Comunicazioni del Presidente del Consiglio dei ministri. Senato della Repubblica \u2013 seduta del 5 giugno 2018. Resoconto stenografico\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612135955/http://www.governo.it/sites/governo.it/files/5giugno2018_Comunicazioni_Conte_Senato.pdf |date=12 June 2018 }} (PDF). Full text of his speech.</ref> Conte also proposed to lift off the [[International sanctions during the Ukrainian crisis|international sanctions]] against [[Russia]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/italy-prime-minister-giuseppe-conte-russia-sanctions-end-populist-five-star-vladimir-putin-crimea-a8385626.html|author=Jon Stone|title=Italy breaks with European allies and voices support for Russia after populist party takes power|work=[[The Independent]]|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402021830/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/italy-prime-minister-giuseppe-conte-russia-sanctions-end-populist-five-star-vladimir-putin-crimea-a8385626.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe Senate approved the [[confidence vote]] with 171 votes in favor and 117 against, with 25 abstentions.<ref>{{cite news|work=[[National Post]]|url=https://nationalpost.com/pmn/news-pmn/the-latest-tunisia-calls-italy-diplomat-over-salvini-remark|title=The Latest: Italy's populist govt wins 1st confidence vote|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> The cabinet was supported by M5S, Lega, two senators from [[Associative Movement Italians Abroad]] (MAIE) and two independents while the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] (PD), [[Forza Italia (2013)|Forza Italia]] (FI), [[Free and Equal (Italy)|Free and Equal]] (LeU) and other small leftist parties voted against it. The far-right [[Brothers of Italy]] (FdI) and other ten independent senators abstained.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-06-05/conte-via-discorso-programmatico-quale-conte-chiedera-fiducia--114755.shtml?uuid=AE51Te0E|title=Governo, 171 s\u00ec per la fiducia, Conte: euro non-in discussione. Salvini: no aumento Iva|work=[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]|language=it|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014655/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/notizie/2018-06-05/conte-via-discorso-programmatico-quale-conte-chiedera-fiducia--114755.shtml?uuid=AE51Te0E|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On the following day, he received 350 votes in favor out of 630 in the [[Chamber of Deputies (Italy)|Chamber of Deputies]], 236 votes against and 35 abstained.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/06/news/governo_conte_fiducia_camera-198287520/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|title=Camera, approvata la fiducia. Conte: \"Tratteremo con l'Ue sul nostro debito\". Delrio (Pd): \"Studi la Carta, non-sia un pupazzo|author=Alberto Custadero|work=[[la Repubblica]]|language=it|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014844/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/06/news/governo_conte_fiducia_camera-198287520/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I0-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> As in the Senate, PD, FI and LeU voted against the government while FdI abstained. Besides M5S and League, Conte received two votes from independent deputies and one vote from [[Vittorio Sgarbi]], a notable and controversial member of Forza Italia who has always heavily criticised the M5S, but decided to support the cabinet in respect of Salvini and with the hope that a M5S government could lead toward their failure.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/06/news/governo_conte_il_si_di_sgarbi_penso_malissimo_di_di_maio_ma_salvini_realizzera_il_programma_di_centrodestra_-198315097/|author=Concetto Vecchio|title=Governo, lo strappo di Sgarbi: \"Penso malissimo di Di Maio. Ma voto s\u00ec: Salvini realizzer\u00e0 il programma di centrodestra|work=la Repubblica|language=it|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224014/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2018/06/06/news/governo_conte_il_si_di_sgarbi_penso_malissimo_di_di_maio_ma_salvini_realizzera_il_programma_di_centrodestra_-198315097/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/06/06/governo-sgarbi-show-alla-camera-dove-ce-il-disordine-io-prospero-votero-la-fiducia-per-assistere-al-vostro-declino/4409507/|title=Governo, Sgarbi show alla Camera: \"Dove c'\u00e8 il disordine io prospero. Voter\u00f2 la fiducia per assistere al vostro decline|work=[[Il Fatto Quotidiano]]|language=it|date=6 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014712/https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/06/06/governo-sgarbi-show-alla-camera-dove-ce-il-disordine-io-prospero-votero-la-fiducia-per-assistere-al-vostro-declino/4409507/|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 5 February 2019, Conte became acting [[Italian Minister of European Affairs|Minister of European Affairs]] after the resignation of [[Paolo Savona]], who was elected President of the [[Commissione Nazionale per le Societ\u00e0 e la Borsa|Companies and Exchange Commission]] (CONSOB).<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2019/02/05/news/la_lega_accordo_con_i_5stelle_savona_va_alla_consob-218335939/|title=Savona alla Consob, interim del ministero a Conte|trans-title=Savona joins CONSOB as an interim minister in Conte's cabinet|date=5 February 2019|work=la Repubblica|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331004639/https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2019/02/05/news/la_lega_accordo_con_i_5stelle_savona_va_alla_consob-218335939/|archive-date=31 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://blendle.com/i/the-economist/wish-upon-five-stars/bnl-economist-20190208-bf5819cfa8c|title=Wish upon Five Stars|date=9 February 2019|work=[[The Economist]]|issue=9129|volume=430|page=28|access-date=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224016/https://blendle.com/i/the-economist/wish-upon-five-stars/bnl-economist-20190208-bf5819cfa8c|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> He held the ''ad interim'' office until 10 July 2019, when he appointed [[Lorenzo Fontana]]\u00a0as new minister.<ref>[https://www.ilpost.it/2019/07/10/conte-fontana-ministro/ Lorenzo Fontana sar\u00e0 il nuovo ministro degli Affari Europei], ''Il Post''</ref>\n\n===Resignation and reappointment===\n{{main|2019 Italian government crisis|Conte II Cabinet}}\n[[File:Sergio Mattarella and Giuseppe Conte 2019.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Conte announcing his resignation to President Mattarella]]\nIn August 2019, Deputy Prime Minister Salvini announced a motion of no confidence against Conte, after growing tensions within the majority.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Salvini-Subito-in-Aula-poi-le-elezioni-Conte-Dovra-spiegare-le-ragioni-della-crisi-648408f5-df6c-49f8-bf6d-a73532bd60ab.html|title=La Lega presenta al Senato una mozione di sfiducia a Conte. M5S attacca Salvini: \"Giullare\"|website=rainews|access-date=20 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190820183327/http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Salvini-Subito-in-Aula-poi-le-elezioni-Conte-Dovra-spiegare-le-ragioni-della-crisi-648408f5-df6c-49f8-bf6d-a73532bd60ab.html|archive-date=20 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Many political analysts believe the no confidence motion was an attempt to force early elections to improve Lega's standing in Parliament, ensuring Salvini could become the next Prime Minister.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/08/09/italys-league-files-no-confidence-motion-prime-minister-inbid/|title=Italy's League files no confidence motion in prime minister in bid to trigger election|first=Nick|last=Squires|date=9 August 2019|via=www.telegraph.co.uk|newspaper=The Telegraph|access-date=20 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190826042808/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2019/08/09/italys-league-files-no-confidence-motion-prime-minister-inbid/|archive-date=26 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 20 August, following the parliamentary debate at the Senate, in which Conte accused Salvini of being a political opportunist who \"had triggered the political crisis only to serve his personal interest\" and stated \"this government ends here\",<ref>{{Cite journal|journal=[[Financial Times]]|first=Ben|last=Hall|url=https://www.ft.com/content/2119e302-c32c-11e9-a8e9-296ca66511c9|date=20 August 2019|title=Conte resignation shows stakes are high in Italy's political crisis|access-date=28 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190821214903/https://www.ft.com/content/2119e302-c32c-11e9-a8e9-296ca66511c9|archive-date=21 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=guardian_resignation>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/20/italian-pm-expected-resign-giuseppe-conte|title=Italian PM resigns with attack on 'opportunist' Salvini|first=Angela|last=Giuffrida|date=20 August 2019|via=www.theguardian.com|newspaper=The Guardian|access-date=20 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190827235332/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/20/italian-pm-expected-resign-giuseppe-conte|archive-date=27 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> the Prime Minister resigned his post to [[Sergio Mattarella|President Mattarella]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/20/world/europe/italy-pm-giuseppe-conte-resign.html|title=Italy's Government Collapses, Turning Chaos into Crisis|first=Jason|last=Horowitz|date=20 August 2019|newspaper=The New York Times|access-date=20 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190826121315/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/08/20/world/europe/italy-pm-giuseppe-conte-resign.html|archive-date=26 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nHowever, during the round of the so-called consultations between Mattarella and the parliamentary groups, a possible new majority emerged, between the Five Star Movement and the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/topnews/2019/08/19/grasso-possibile-intesa-m5s-pd-leu_301fb033-f640-4d0f-bba3-ea37eb594c9b.html|title=Grasso, possibile intesa M5s-Pd-Leu - Ultima Ora|date=19 August 2019|website=Agenzia ANSA|access-date=28 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190819161904/http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/topnews/2019/08/19/grasso-possibile-intesa-m5s-pd-leu_301fb033-f640-4d0f-bba3-ea37eb594c9b.html|archive-date=19 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 28 August, PD's leader [[Nicola Zingaretti]] announced at the [[Quirinal Palace]] his favorable position on keeping Giuseppe Conte at the head of the new government,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/conte-wins-crucial-support-for-new-italian-govt-coalition/2019/08/28/a85203c4-c99c-11e9-9615-8f1a32962e04_story.html|title=Conte wins crucial support for new Italian govt coalition|website=Washington Post|access-date=28 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828200930/https://www.washingtonpost.com/business/conte-wins-crucial-support-for-new-italian-govt-coalition/2019/08/28/a85203c4-c99c-11e9-9615-8f1a32962e04_story.html|archive-date=28 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> and on same day, Mattarella summoned Conte to the Quirinal Palace for 29 August to give him the task of forming a new cabinet.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agi.it/politica/governo_pd_m5s_consultazioni-6094223/news/2019-08-28/|title=C'\u00e8 l'accordo tra M5s e Pd. Governo giallorosso ai nastri di partenza|website=Agi|access-date=28 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828182811/https://www.agi.it/politica/governo_pd_m5s_consultazioni-6094223/news/2019-08-28/|archive-date=28 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 4 September, Conte announced the ministers of his new cabinet, which was sworn in at the Quirinal Palace on the following day.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/05/news/governo_conte_accetta_l_incarico_oggi_il_giuramento_della_squadra_al_quirinale-235221666/|title=Governo, Conte e i ministri hanno giurato. Gentiloni in pole per successione a Moscovici|date=5 September 2019|website=Repubblica.it|access-date=5 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190905090044/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/05/news/governo_conte_accetta_l_incarico_oggi_il_giuramento_della_squadra_al_quirinale-235221666/|archive-date=5 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 9 September 2019 the Chamber of Deputies granted the confidence to the government with 343 votes in favour, 263 against and 3 abstentions.<ref>{{cite news |title=La Camera vota la fiducia con 343 s\u00ec, il premier replica alla Camera fra le proteste. Alzata anche una sedia |url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/09/news/governo_conte_fiducia_camera-235548089/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I235485988-C12-P1-S1.12-T1 |accessdate=9 September 2019 |work=Repubblica.it |date=9 September 2019 |language=it |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190910053844/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/09/news/governo_conte_fiducia_camera-235548089/?ref=RHPPTP-BL-I235485988-C12-P1-S1.12-T1 |archive-date=10 September 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Resoconto stenografico dell'Assemblea Seduta n. 222 di luned\u00ec 9 settembre 2019 |url=https://www.camera.it/leg18/410?idSeduta=0222&tipo=stenografico#sed0222.stenografico.tit00070.sub00030 |website=camera.it |publisher=Camera dei Deputati |accessdate=10 September 2019}}</ref> On 10 September 2019, in the second vote of confidence in the Senate, 169 lawmakers voted in favour of his government and 133 against.<ref>{{cite_web|url=https://thepublicsradio.org/article/italys-new-pro-europe-govt-wins-2nd-confidence-vote|title=Italy's new pro-EU govt wins vote, now faces 2020 budget|accessdate=10 September 2019|website=The Public's Radio|date=10 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191016205409/https://thepublicsradio.org/article/italys-new-pro-europe-govt-wins-2nd-confidence-vote|archive-date=16 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 September, after few days from the investiture vote, in an interview to ''[[la Repubblica]]'', former Prime Minister [[Matteo Renzi]] announced his intention to leave the PD, launching a new centrist and liberal party named [[Italia Viva]] (IV).<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rep.repubblica.it/pwa/intervista/2019/09/16/news/pd_renzi_scissione-236190189/?ref=RHPPLF-BH-I236210677-C8-P1-S1.8-T1|title=Renzi lascia il Pd: \"Uscire dal partito sar\u00e0 un bene per tutti. Anche per Conte\"|website=rep.repubblica.it}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/politica/19_settembre_17/renzi-il-nome-nuova-sfida-che-stiamo-lanciare-sara-italia-viva-8dbc9da4-d963-11e9-8812-2a1c8aa813a3.shtml|title=Renzi: \"Il nome della nuova sfida che stiamo per lanciare sar\u00e0 Italia viva\"|first=Redazione|last=Politica|date=17 September 2019|website=Corriere della Sera|access-date=2 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190924150038/https://www.corriere.it/politica/19_settembre_17/renzi-il-nome-nuova-sfida-che-stiamo-lanciare-sara-italia-viva-8dbc9da4-d963-11e9-8812-2a1c8aa813a3.shtml|archive-date=24 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In the interview he confirmed also the support to Conte's government.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/16/news/renzi_telefona_a_conte_e_annuncia_l_addio_al_pd-236192204/|title=Matteo Renzi lascia il Pd e fonda nuovo partito: telefona a Conte e annuncia l'addio al Pd, Le ragioni della svolta in una intervista a Repubblica|date=16 September 2019|website=Repubblica.it|access-date=2 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191002182626/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/09/16/news/renzi_telefona_a_conte_e_annuncia_l_addio_al_pd-236192204/|archive-date=2 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Two ministers and one undersecretary followed Renzi in his new movement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.avvenire.it/attualita/pagine/il-partito-di-renzi-italia-viva|title=L'iniziativa. Renzi saluta il Pd e lancia \"Italia viva\". \"Siamo 40 in Parlamento\"|date=17 September 2019|website=www.avvenire.it|access-date=2 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191002203847/https://www.avvenire.it/attualita/pagine/il-partito-di-renzi-italia-viva|archive-date=2 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019 the Minister of Education, University and Research [[Lorenzo Fioramonti]] resigned after disagreements with the rest of the cabinet regarding the recently approved 2020 budget bill. Fioramonti considered the share of funds dedicated to education and research to be insufficient.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Jones |first1=Gavin |title=Italy education minister resigns over lack of funds for ministry |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-politics-minister-resignation/italy-education-minister-resigns-over-lack-of-funds-for-ministry-idUSKBN1YT0Q4 |accessdate=26 December 2019 |work=Reuters |date=25 December 2019 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191225225032/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-politics-minister-resignation/italy-education-minister-resigns-over-lack-of-funds-for-ministry-idUSKBN1YT0Q4 |archive-date=25 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Conte took the ministerial role ''ad interim'', and announced his decision to split the Ministry of Education, University and Research into two: a [[Italian Minister of Public Education|Ministry of Public Education]] led by former undersecretary [[Lucia Azzolina]] (M5S), and a [[Italian Minister of University and Research|Ministry of University and Research]] led by the dean of the [[University of Naples Federico II]] [[Gaetano Manfredi]] (Independent), who were sworn in on 10 January.<ref>{{cite news |title=Conte:: \"Separare la Scuola dall'Universit\u00e0. Azzolina ministro dell'Istruzione e Manfredi della Ricerca\" |url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/12/28/news/conte_prescrizione_governo_conferenza_stampa_fine_anno-244526130/ |accessdate=28 December 2019 |work=Repubblica.it |date=28 December 2019 |language=it |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191228120724/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/12/28/news/conte_prescrizione_governo_conferenza_stampa_fine_anno-244526130/ |archive-date=28 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2020/01/10/governo-giurano-azzolina-e-manfredi-e-diventano-ministri-_c59c8837-8569-4324-95da-025f184a9f82.html |title=Governo: Giurano Azzolina e Manfredi e diventano ministri |access-date=12 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112104102/http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2020/01/10/governo-giurano-azzolina-e-manfredi-e-diventano-ministri-_c59c8837-8569-4324-95da-025f184a9f82.html |archive-date=12 January 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Policies==\n===Economic policies===\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte Centro Italia 1.jpg|thumb|Conte among people affected by the [[August 2016 Central Italy earthquake|2016 Central Italy earthquakes]]]]\nOne of Conte's main proposals was the scheduled reform of the [[Taxation in Italy|Italian tax system]], mainly promoted by the League and characterized by the introduction of [[flat tax]]es for businesses and individuals, with a no-tax area for low-income households and some small corrections to keep some degree of [[Progressive tax|tax progression]] as required by the [[Constitution of Italy|Italian Constitution]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://economia.ilmessaggero.it/economia_e_finanza/flat_tax_cos_e_detrazioni_simulatore-3782544.html|title=Flat tax, cos'\u00e8 e come funziona: due aliquote al 15 e 20%, premiati i redditi pi\u00f9 alti|trans-title=Flat tax, what it is and how it works: Two rates at 15 and 20%, higher incomes awarded|work=[[Il Messaggero]]|language=it|date=7 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612181034/https://economia.ilmessaggero.it/economia_e_finanza/flat_tax_cos_e_detrazioni_simulatore-3782544.html|archive-date=12 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.guidafisco.it/flat-tax-cos-e-come-funziona-domanda-durata-opzione-1859|title=Flat tax: cos'\u00e8 come funziona per famiglie e imprese e quali vantaggi?|trans-title=Flat tax: What is it like for families and businesses and what are the advantages?|language=it|date=1 April 2019|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014740/https://www.guidafisco.it/flat-tax-cos-e-come-funziona-domanda-durata-opzione-1859|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The government stressed that they will find the funds to implement it through the so-called \"fiscal peace\", that is a [[condonation]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://notizie.tiscali.it/politica/articoli/pace-fiscale-condono-lega-m5s/|title=La pace fiscale pentaleghista conferma che l'Italia \u00e8 una repubblica fondata sul condono|trans-title=The pentalghistic fiscal peace confirms that Italy is a republic founded on amnesty|author=Michael Pontrelli|language=it|date=8 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224026/https://notizie.tiscali.it/politica/articoli/pace-fiscale-condono-lega-m5s/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> However, many important economists{{who|date=June 2018}} and newspapers like ''[[Il Sole 24 Ore]]'' denounced that the condonation could not finance all the new tax system based on flat tax.<ref>{{cite news|work=Il Sole 24 Ore|url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/norme-e-tributi/2018-06-07/flat-tax-pace-fiscale-bonus-no-tax-area-perche-non-tornano-conti-222404.shtml?uuid=AEgXCE2E|title=Flat tax, dalla pace fiscale ai bonus alla no tax area: perch\u00e9 non-tornano i conti|author=Gianni Trovati|language=it|date=8 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014709/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/norme-e-tributi/2018-06-07/flat-tax-pace-fiscale-bonus-no-tax-area-perche-non-tornano-conti-222404.shtml?uuid=AEgXCE2E|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Conte's first government, introduced a flat tax with a 15% rate, applied to small entrepreneurs and self-employed with an amount of annual revenues inferior to \u20ac65,000. Despite the so-called \"flat regime\" was a proposal of the right-wing League, it was confirmed also by Conte's second government, with the centre-left.<ref>{{cite news |title=Manovra, Misiani: \"Per le partite Iva resta il regime forfettario fino a 65 mila euro\" |url=https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2019/10/22/news/partite_iva_misini_resta_il_regime_forfettario_fino_a_65_mila_euro_-239181146/ |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=Repubblica.it |date=22 October 2019 |language=it |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191211013152/https://www.repubblica.it/economia/2019/10/22/news/partite_iva_misini_resta_il_regime_forfettario_fino_a_65_mila_euro_-239181146/ |archive-date=11 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nDuring his first cabinet, his government rolled out the so-called \"citizens' income\" ({{lang-it|reddito di cittadinanza}}), a system of [[social welfare provision]] that provides a basic income and assistance in finding a job in order to help poor people and families.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy's government launches 'citizens' income' website |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20190204/italys-government-launches-citizens-income-scheme-website |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=thelocal.it |date=4 February 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191031154935/https://www.thelocal.it/20190204/italys-government-launches-citizens-income-scheme-website |archive-date=31 October 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Giuffrida |first1=Angela |title=Italy rolls out 'citizens' income' for the poor amid criticisms |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/mar/06/italy-rolls-out-citizens-income-for-the-poor-amid-criticisms |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=6 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191130040914/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/mar/06/italy-rolls-out-citizens-income-for-the-poor-amid-criticisms |archive-date=30 November 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The income is set to a maximum of \u20ac780 per month, and in its first year the program has almost 2.7 million applications.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hurst |first1=Luke |title=What is Italy's new 'Citizens' Income' scheme? {{!}} Euronews Answers |url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/03/06/what-is-italy-s-new-citizens-income-scheme-euronews-answers |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=euronews |agency=Reuters |date=6 March 2019 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191016155451/https://www.euronews.com/2019/03/06/what-is-italy-s-new-citizens-income-scheme-euronews-answers |archive-date=16 October 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=2.7 million people apply for Italy's basic income scheme |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20190424/million-people-apply-for-italys-basic-income-scheme |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=thelocal.it |date=24 April 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925071154/https://www.thelocal.it/20190424/million-people-apply-for-italys-basic-income-scheme |archive-date=25 September 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> The bill was later confirmed by Conte's second cabinet.<ref>{{cite news |title=Reddito di cittadinanza e Quota 100, il governo: \"Nessuna revisione all'ordine del giorno\" |url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2019/12/30/reddito-di-cittadinanza-e-quota-100-il-governo-nessuna-revisione-allordine-del-giorno/5642683/ |accessdate=4 January 2020 |work=Il Fatto Quotidiano |date=30 December 2019 |language=it-IT |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191231143703/https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2019/12/30/reddito-di-cittadinanza-e-quota-100-il-governo-nessuna-revisione-allordine-del-giorno/5642683/ |archive-date=31 December 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nDuring Conte's governments, more severe punishments for [[Tax evasion|tax dodgers]], which are a major problem in Italy, had been approved.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ansa.it/english/news/2018/06/05/jail-for-tax-dodgers-bans-for-corrupt-conte-2_30f0ebbb-5757-4ced-bf9d-32b51c9a8ec3.html|title=Jail for tax dodgers, bans for corrupt - Conte|agency=Agenzia Nazionale Stampa Associata|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014811/http://www.ansa.it/english/news/2018/06/05/jail-for-tax-dodgers-bans-for-corrupt-conte-2_30f0ebbb-5757-4ced-bf9d-32b51c9a8ec3.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> With the 2020 financial bill, the government introduced a bill which provided prison for \"great tax dodgers\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/10/22/news/manovra_accordo_vertice_maggioranza-239157635/|title=Manovra, accordo sul carcere agli evasori. A luglio la stretta sui contanti e le multe a chi non-usa il Pos|date=22 October 2019|website=Repubblica.it|access-date=24 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191024100151/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/10/22/news/manovra_accordo_vertice_maggioranza-239157635/|archive-date=24 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte @ the EP (46159375855).jpg|thumb|left|220px|Conte at the [[European Parliament]]]]\nIn September 2019, at the head of his second government, Conte launched the so-called \"Green New Deal\", named after the analogous [[Green New Deal|US proposed legislation]] that aimed to address [[Global warming|climate change]] and [[economic inequality]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.newscientist.com/article/2193592-green-new-deal-proposal-includes-free-higher-education-and-fair-pay/|title=Green New Deal proposal includes free higher education and fair pay|last=Whyte|first=Chelsea|date=12 February 2019|work=NewScientist|access-date=4 March 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190306042902/https://www.newscientist.com/article/2193592-green-new-deal-proposal-includes-free-higher-education-and-fair-pay/|archive-date=6 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In the same period, he praised students who [[September 2019 climate strikes|protested against climate change]], stating: \"The images of the squares of the [[Fridays for Future]] are extraordinary, with so many young people participating with such passion. From the government there is the utmost commitment to translate this request for change into concrete solutions. We all have a great responsibility.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/GiuseppeConteIT/status/1177562186144763904|title=Sono straordinarie le immagini delle piazze di #fridaysforfuture, con cos\u00ec tanti giovani che partecipano con tale passione. Da parte mia e del Governo c'\u00e8 il massimo impegno a tradurre questa richiesta di cambiamento in soluzioni concrete. Abbiamo tutti una grande responsabilit\u00e0pic.twitter.com/7RxMGzwcPz|first=Giuseppe|last=Conte|date=27 September 2019|access-date=2 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927125631/https://twitter.com/GiuseppeConteIT/status/1177562186144763904|archive-date=27 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2020, the cabinet increased to \u20ac100 per month the so-called \"Renzi bonus\", a monthly allowance introduced by [[Matteo Renzi]]'s government in 2014, recognized to holders of a total annual income not exceeding \u20ac24,600.<ref>[https://www.ipsoa.it/wkpedia/bonus-80-euro Bonus Renzi (\u20ac80) \u2013 Ipsoa]</ref> A total of 11.7 million people benefited of the bonus in 2020.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/cuneo-fiscale-bonus-renzi-sale-100-euro-117-milioni-contribuenti-ACCT1ECB |title=Cuneo fiscale, il bonus Renzi sale a 100 euro per 11,7 milioni di contribuenti |access-date=20 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200118135105/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/cuneo-fiscale-bonus-renzi-sale-100-euro-117-milioni-contribuenti-ACCT1ECB |archive-date=18 January 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIn April 2020, amid the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Europe|coronavirus pandemic]] which severely affected Europe, Conte became the most vocal supporter of the [[Eurobond (eurozone)|eurobond]]s' issuance to face the crisis,<ref>[https://www.agi.it/politica/news/2020-04-07/coronavirus-conte-mes-fase-2-8259417/ L'Italia non vuole attivare il fondo Salva-Stati e insiste sugli eurobond], ''agi.it''</ref> describing the [[European Stability Mechanism]] (ESM) as \"completely inadequate\".<ref>[https://www.milanofinanza.it/news/conte-stronca-il-mes-inadeguato-202004062145468694 Conte stronca il Mes: inadeguato], ''Milano Finanza''</ref> Conte found key allies in [[France]], [[Spain]], [[Belgium]], [[Ireland]], [[Portugal]], [[Greece]], [[Slovenia]] and [[Luxembourg]], which demanded more to be done in relation to coronavirus pandemic;<ref>[https://www.agi.it/economia/news/2020-03-25/coronabond-ue-pressioni-italia-francia-spagna-7852247/ Italia, Francia e Spagna chiedono all'Ue di dare via libera ai coronabond], ''agi.it''</ref> while [[Germany]], the [[Netherlands]], [[Austria]], [[Finland]] and [[Estonia]], strongly opposed the eurobonds.<ref>[https://www.corriere.it/economia/finanza/20_aprile_08/perche-germania-olanda-sono-contro-coronabond-proviamo-capirlo-ricapitolare-tutto-03472d1e-7964-11ea-afb4-c5f49a569528_preview.shtml?reason=unauthenticated&cat=1&cid=Q4JDr2Aj&pids=FR&credits=1&origin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.corriere.it%2Feconomia%2Ffinanza%2F20_aprile_08%2Fperche-germania-olanda-sono-contro-coronabond-proviamo-capirlo-ricapitolare-tutto-03472d1e-7964-11ea-afb4-c5f49a569528.shtml Coronabond, perch\u00e9 Germania e Olanda sono contro?], ''Corriere della Sera''</ref> Conte, during an interview to German weekly ''[[Die Zeit]]'', questioned: \"What do we want to do in Europe? Does each member state want to go its own way?\",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.dw.com/en/coronabonds-and-the-idea-of-european-financial-unity/a-52980433|title=Coronabonds and the idea of European financial unity|website=DW|date=1 April 2020}}</ref> he also added: \"If we are a union, now is the time to prove it.\"<ref>[https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/da-die-zeit-de-telegraaf-ora-conte-parla-direttamente-all-opinione-pubblica-europea-ADQIljH Da Die Zeit a De Telegraaf, ora Conte parla direttamente all\u2019opinione pubblica europea], ''Die Zeit''</ref> On 8 April, he stated \"we should loosened European fiscal rules, otherwise we would have to cancel Europe and everyone will do on their own.\"<ref>[https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2020/04/08/news/coronavirus_conte_allentare_regole_fiscali_o_fine_ue-253506669/ Coronavirus: Conte, allentare regole fiscali o fine Ue], la Repubblica</ref>\n\n===Immigration===\n[[File:-G7Biarritz (48632626161).jpg|thumb|right|220px|Conte with President [[Donald Trump]]. The [[U.S. President]] often praised Conte's immigration policies]]\nWhen Conte became Prime Minister in 2018, he acted quickly to deliver on promises to the government's anti-immigration base through strict controls on [[European migrant crisis|immigration to Italy]]. Since 2013, Italy had absorbed over 700,000 African migrants arriving by boat from [[Libya]].<ref>{{cite news|title=What will Italy's new government mean for migrants?|url=https://www.thelocal.it/20180521/what-will-italys-new-government-mean-for-migrants|publisher=The Local|agency=[[Agence France-Presse|AFP]]|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401231010/https://www.thelocal.it/20180521/what-will-italys-new-government-mean-for-migrants|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=African migrants fear for future as Italy struggles with surge in arrivals|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-migrants-africa/african-migrants-fear-for-future-as-italy-struggles-with-surge-in-arrivals-idUSKBN1A30QD|agency=Reuters|date=18 July 2017|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402002627/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-migrants-africa/african-migrants-fear-for-future-as-italy-struggles-with-surge-in-arrivals-idUSKBN1A30QD|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> During his premiership, Conte and his Interior Minister [[Matteo Salvini]] promoted stricter policies regarding immigration and public security.<ref>{{cite news|agency=Agenzia Giornalistica Italia|language=it|date=11 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|url=https://www.agi.it/breakingnews/migranti_conte_grazie_salvini_italia_non_piu_sola_il_premier_da_macron_e_merkel-4017213/news/2018-06-11/|title=Migranti: Conte, grazie Salvini, Italia non-piu' sola; il premier da Macron e Merkel|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402002624/https://www.agi.it/breakingnews/migranti_conte_grazie_salvini_italia_non_piu_sola_il_premier_da_macron_e_merkel-4017213/news/2018-06-11/|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAfter Conte's approval on 10 June 2018, Salvini announced the closure of Italian [[ports]], stating: \"Everyone in Europe is doing their own business, now Italy is also raising its head. Let's stop the business of illegal immigration\".<ref>{{cite news|work=[[La Stampa]]|url=https://www.lastampa.it/2018/06/11/italia/migranti-litalia-sfida-malta-salvini-chiudiamo-i-porti-bVoFCfoAr11187cT5qJ4rL/pagina.html|title=Migranti, l'Italia sfida Malta. Salvini: chiudiamo i porti|trans-title=Migrants, Italy challenges Malta. Salvini: We close the Ports|author=Fabio Albanese|language=it|date=11 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401224015/https://www.lastampa.it/2018/06/11/italia/migranti-litalia-sfida-malta-salvini-chiudiamo-i-porti-bVoFCfoAr11187cT5qJ4rL/pagina.html|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The vessel ''Aquarius'', which is operated jointly by ''[[M\u00e9decins Sans Fronti\u00e8res]]'' and ''[[SOS M\u00e9diterran\u00e9e]]'' and carried more than 600 migrants, was refused a port of disembarkation by the Italian authorities despite having been told to rescue the migrants by the same co-ordination centre. The Italian authority told the vessel to ask [[Malta]] to provide a disembarkation port, but Malta also refused.<ref>{{cite news|author=Mark Stone|url=https://news.sky.com/story/italy-shuts-ports-to-rescue-ship-carrying-over-600-migrants-11401125|title=More than 600 migrants running out of food as Italy shuts port to rescue ship|date=11 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190723093832/https://news.sky.com/story/italy-shuts-ports-to-rescue-ship-carrying-over-600-migrants-11401125|archive-date=23 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On the following day, the new Spanish Prime Minister [[Pedro S\u00e1nchez (politician)|Pedro S\u00e1nchez]] accepted the disputed migrant ship.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-44441386|title=Spain to accept disputed migrant ship Aquarius|publisher=BBC News|date=12 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190111192818/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-44441386|archive-date=11 January 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Conte accused French President [[Emmanuel Macron]] of hypocrisy after Macron said Italy was acting \"irresponsibly\" by refusing entry to migrants and suggested it had violated international maritime law.<ref>{{cite news|title=Italian foreign ministry summons French ambassador as tensions mount over port closures to refugee rescue boats|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/italy-port-closures-refugees-mediterranean-matteo-salvini-aquarius-emmanuel-macron-a8396916.html|work=The Independent|date=13 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402021834/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/italy-port-closures-refugees-mediterranean-matteo-salvini-aquarius-emmanuel-macron-a8396916.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 24 September 2018, the Council of Ministers approved the so-called \"Salvini decree\", which contained a series of hardline measures that will see the [[Italian government]] abolish key forms of protection for migrants and make it easier for them to be deported. The decree will also suspend the refugee application process of those who are considered \"socially dangerous\" or who have been convicted of a crime.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/sep/24/italian-government-approves-bill-anti-migrant-measures-matteo-salvini|work=[[The Guardian]]|title=Italian government approves Salvini bill targeting migrants|author=Giuffrida, Angela|publisher=[[Guardian Media Group]]|date=24 September 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190826133405/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/sep/24/italian-government-approves-bill-anti-migrant-measures-matteo-salvini|archive-date=26 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 23 September 2019, Italy and other four European countries, Germany, France, Malta and Finland, agreed on a draft deal to present to other EU countries on how to manage the migrant crisis and distribute those saved from the Mediterranean.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/09/23/five-eu-interior-ministers-agree-on-draft-migration-deal|title=Five EU interior ministers agree on draft migration deal|date=23 September 2019|website=euronews|access-date=25 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925072612/https://www.euronews.com/2019/09/23/five-eu-interior-ministers-agree-on-draft-migration-deal|archive-date=25 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> This agreement was considered a win for Conte and his new interior minister, [[Luciana Lamorgese]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ansa.it/english/news/politics/2019/09/24/migrant-agreement-is-turning-point-conte_dacde2b7-1806-4083-8142-a5a491b34fcf.html|title=Migrant agreement is turning point-Conte - English|date=24 September 2019|website=ANSA.it|access-date=25 September 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925072613/http://www.ansa.it/english/news/politics/2019/09/24/migrant-agreement-is-turning-point-conte_dacde2b7-1806-4083-8142-a5a491b34fcf.html|archive-date=25 September 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fanpage.it/politica/migranti-la-doppia-vittoria-di-lamorgese-salvini-disarmato-europa-resuscitata/|title=Migranti, la doppia vittoria di Lamorgese: Salvini disarmato, Europa resuscitata|website=Fanpage}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ilmattino.it/primopiano/politica/migranti_news_giuseppe_conte-4731793.html|title=Migranti, Conte: sar\u00e0 la Ue a gestire la redistribuzione|website=www.ilmattino.it|access-date=24 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191024095929/https://www.ilmattino.it/primopiano/politica/migranti_news_giuseppe_conte-4731793.html|archive-date=24 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 April 2020, amid the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|coronavirus pandemic]], the government closed all Italian ports until 31 July, stating that they do not ensure the necessary requirements for the classification and definition of \"safe place\", established by the [[Hamburg Rules]]\u00a0on maritime search and rescue.\"<ref>[https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/litalia-chiude-i-porti_it_5e8d89f2c5b6e1d10a6c2671?yhj&utm_hp_ref=it-homepage L'Italia chiude i porti], ''Huffington Post''</ref>\n\n===Ponte Morandi collapse===\n{{main|Ponte Morandi#Collapse}}\n[[File:Il Ponte Morandi dopo il crollo, visto da Est, dettaglio.jpg|thumb|220px|right|The collapsed section of [[Ponte Morandi]], [[Genoa]]]] \nOn 14 August 2018, during a torrential rainstorm over the city of [[Genoa]], a {{Convert|210|m|adj=on}} section of [[Ponte Morandi]] collapsed.<ref name=\"BBC-45183624\" /><ref name=\"BBC-45183624\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-45183624|title=Italy bridge: Dozens feared dead in Genoa as motorway collapses|work=BBC News|date=14 August 2018|accessdate=14 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180814110230/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-45183624|archive-date=14 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref> Between 30 and 35 cars and three trucks were reported to have fallen from the bridge, killing 43 people.<ref name=\"BBC-45182675\">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/live/world-europe-45182675|title=As it happened: Genoa motorway bridge disaster|first1=David|last1=Molloy|first2=Laurence|last2=Peter|first3=Ellis|last3=Palmer|work=BBC News|date=14 August 2018|access-date=14 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180815152610/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/live/world-europe-45182675|archive-date=15 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/liguria/crollo-ponte-morandi-una-testimone-tiranti-spezzati-insieme_3158532-201802a.shtml|title=Crollo ponte Morandi, una testimone: tiranti spezzati insieme|work=Tgcom24|access-date=18 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180817205239/http://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/cronaca/liguria/crollo-ponte-morandi-una-testimone-tiranti-spezzati-insieme_3158532-201802a.shtml|archive-date=17 August 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe day after the collapse, Conte declared a state of emergency for the [[Liguria]] region, which would last for a year.<ref name=\"BBC45193614\">{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-45193614 |title=Italy bridge: State of emergency follows Genoa disaster |work=BBC News |accessdate=15 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180815093914/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-45193614 |archive-date=15 August 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> The government put pressure on the managers of the road, Autostrade per l\u2019Italia, which is part of the [[Benetton family]] owned [[Atlantia (company)|Atlantia]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/economia/18_agosto_17/choc-benetton-genova-3911bea8-a25d-11e8-b2f9-d4ce42b355f4.shtml|title=Lo choc dei Benetton. A Genova i manager chiederanno scusa|last=Pica|first=Paola|work=Corriere della Sera|access-date=18 August 2018|language=it-IT}}</ref> The M5S asked the revocation of license to Benetton family and the [[nationalization]] of Autostrade per l'Italia.<ref>[https://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2020/01/01/autostrade-via-alla-revoca-delle-concessioni.-di-maio-benetton-perderanno-profitti_d451b32a-ee93-46f5-941c-7036219ec477.html Autostrade, via alla revoca delle concessioni. Di Maio: 'Benetton perderanno profitti'] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200107152119/http://www.ansa.it/sito/notizie/politica/2020/01/01/autostrade-via-alla-revoca-delle-concessioni.-di-maio-benetton-perderanno-profitti_d451b32a-ee93-46f5-941c-7036219ec477.html |date=7 January 2020 }}, ANSA</ref> However, despite bitter controversies, the revocation has not yet been implemented.\n\nThe last two cable-stayed pillars of the bridge were demolished [[explosive demolition|using a tonne of explosives]] on 28 June 2019. The complete bridge was planned to be removed, along with multiple damaged houses in the surrounding area.<ref name=bbc-20190628>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/av/world-europe-48797883/morandi-bridge-towers-demolished-in-genoa |title=Morandi bridge towers demolished in Genoa |work=BBC News |date=28 June 2019 |accessdate=28 June 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190628113346/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/av/world-europe-48797883/morandi-bridge-towers-demolished-in-genoa |archive-date=28 June 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> A replacement bridge, designed by Italian architect [[Renzo Piano]], has been under construction since 25 June 2019, and is set to be opened in the first half of 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.engineering.com/BIM/ArticleID/18231/After-Bridge-Tragedy-Genoa-Selects-a-New-Design.aspx|title=After Bridge Tragedy, Genoa Selects a New Design|date=2019-01-10|website=www.engineering.com|language=en-US|access-date=3 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825091927/https://www.engineering.com/BIM/ArticleID/18231/After-Bridge-Tragedy-Genoa-Selects-a-New-Design.aspx|archive-date=25 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Constitutional reform===\nUnder Conte's governments, the [[Italian Parliament]] approved the so-called \"[[Riccardo Fraccaro|Fraccaro]] Reform\", from the name of the M5S deputy who was the bill's first signatory.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rainews.it/tgr/trento/articoli/2019/10/tnt-camera-dei-deputati-riforma-fraccaro-taglio-parlamentari-trentino-alto-adige-dbb4795d-063b-47be-a171-d467a65ee157.html|title=La Camera approva la riforma Fraccaro. Via al taglio dei parlamentari - TGR Trento|website=TGR|access-date=24 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191024095931/https://www.rainews.it/tgr/trento/articoli/2019/10/tnt-camera-dei-deputati-riforma-fraccaro-taglio-parlamentari-trentino-alto-adige-dbb4795d-063b-47be-a171-d467a65ee157.html|archive-date=24 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The reform was finally approved by the Parliament, with the fourth and final vote in the Chamber of Deputies on 8 October with 553 votes in favor and 14 against. In the final vote, the bill was supported both by the majority and the opposition;<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sciorilli Borrelli |first1=Silvia |title=Italian lawmakers want fewer Italian lawmakers |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/italian-lawmakers-want-fewer-seats-in-parliament-vote-referendum/ |accessdate=24 October 2019 |work=POLITICO |date=8 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009141725/https://www.politico.eu/article/italian-lawmakers-want-fewer-seats-in-parliament-vote-referendum/ |archive-date=9 October 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> only the liberal party [[More Europe]] (+Eu) and other small groups voted against.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://it.notizie.yahoo.com/taglio-dei-parlamentari-orfini-la-riforma-fa-schifo-chi-sono-i-contrari-080204412.html|title=Taglio dei parlamentari, Orfini: \"La riforma fa schifo\". Chi sono i contrari|website=it.notizie.yahoo.com|access-date=24 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009115403/https://it.notizie.yahoo.com/taglio-dei-parlamentari-orfini-la-riforma-fa-schifo-chi-sono-i-contrari-080204412.html|archive-date=9 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The reform provided a cut in the number of MPs, which would shrink from 630 to 400 deputies and from 315 to 200 senators.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy shrinks parliament 'to save \u20ac1bn' |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-49979103 |accessdate=24 October 2019 |work=BBC News |date=8 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009093221/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-49979103 |archive-date=9 October 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nAfter the approval, Conte stated: \"The cut to the parliamentarians is a reform that will bring to a greater efficiency of the parliamentary jobs. Now, citizens to be closer to the institutions. It is a historical passage that, together with other projected reform, will be a prelude to greater efficiency of our parliamentary system.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2019/10/08/taglio-parlamentari-e-legge-montecitorio-approva-con-553-si-di-maio-fatto-storico-saremo-leali-su-contrappesi-conte-riforme-riduce-i-costi-e-dara-piu-efficienza/5504346/|title=Taglio parlamentari \u00e8 legge: Montecitorio approva con 553 S\u00ec. Di Maio: \"Fatto storico, saremo leali su contrappesi\". Conte: \"Riforma riduce i costi e dar\u00e0 pi\u00f9 efficienza\"|date=8 October 2019|website=Il Fatto Quotidiano|access-date=24 October 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191011174152/https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2019/10/08/taglio-parlamentari-e-legge-montecitorio-approva-con-553-si-di-maio-fatto-storico-saremo-leali-su-contrappesi-conte-riforme-riduce-i-costi-e-dara-piu-efficienza/5504346/|archive-date=11 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe [[2020 Italian constitutional referendum|referendum]] to approve the reform was scheduled on 29 March, however it was postponed due to the [[2020 coronavirus outbreak in Italy|coronavirus pandemic]] which severely affected Italy.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.interno.gov.it/it/notizie/rinviato-referendum-29-marzo-sul-taglio-dei-parlamentari |title=inviato il referendum del 29 marzo sul taglio dei parlamentari |access-date=10 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200314100154/https://www.interno.gov.it/it/notizie/rinviato-referendum-29-marzo-sul-taglio-dei-parlamentari |archive-date=14 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n===Coronavirus pandemic===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy}}\nIn February 2020, Italy became one of the world's main centres for confirmed cases of [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]], a respiratory disease caused by the [[SARS-CoV-2]] virus that originated in [[China]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/salute/ricerca/coronavirus_italia_prima_contagi_europa-5068457.html |title=Coronavirus, Italia prima in Europa per numero di contagi: \u00e8 caccia ai focolai |access-date=23 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200223000631/https://www.ilmessaggero.it/salute/ricerca/coronavirus_italia_prima_contagi_europa-5068457.html |archive-date=23 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> As of April 2020, over 170,000 coronavirus cases were confirmed, affecting mainly [[Lombardy]], [[Emilia-Romagna]], [[Veneto]] and [[Piedmont]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-italia-nuovi-contagi-lombardia-veneto-245e72d4-5540-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml|title=Coronavirus, due casi a Milano|last=online|first=Simona Ravizza e redazione|date=2020-02-22|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-02-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222225105/https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-italia-nuovi-contagi-lombardia-veneto-245e72d4-5540-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml|archive-date=22 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n[[File:2020 coronavirus task force.jpg|thumb|220px|left|Italian [[Conte II Cabinet|government]] task force to face the coronavirus pandemic]]\nIn late January, the government banned all flights from and to China, becoming the first European country to adopt this measure.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://roma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/01/30/news/coronavirus_turisti_cinesi-247194041/ |title=Coronavirus, primi due casi confermati in Italia: sono turisti cinesi a Roma. Chiuso il traffico aereo con la Cina |access-date=23 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200225152158/https://roma.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/01/30/news/coronavirus_turisti_cinesi-247194041/ |archive-date=25 February 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 22 February, the [[Council of Ministers of Italy|Council of Ministers]] announced a bill to contain the COVID-19 outbreak, quarantining more than 50,000 people from 11 different municipalities in [[Northern Italy]]. Prime Minister Conte stated: \"In the outbreak areas, entry and exit will not be provided. Suspension of work activities and sport events has already been ordered in those areas.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/decreto_governo_contro_coronavirus-249308355/|title=Coronavirus, decreto del governo: nei comuni focolaio stop ad ingressi ed uscite. Conte: \"Non trasformeremo l'Italia in un lazzaretto\"|date=2020-02-22|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-22}}</ref>\n\nSchools were closed in 10 municipalities in Lombardy, one in Veneto and in Emilia-Romagna. In some areas, all public events were cancelled and commercial activities were halted.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_21/scuole-chiuse-il-coronavirus-lombardia-lodi-piacenza-codogno-a190ccee-54bd-11ea-9196-da7d305401b7.shtml|title=Quali sono i Comuni che hanno chiuso le scuole per il Coronavirus|last=online|first=Redazione|date=2020-02-21|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref> Regional train services suspended the stops in the most affected areas \u2013 with trains not stopping at Codogno, Maleo and Casalpusterlengo stations.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.corriere.it/cronache/20_febbraio_22/coronavirus-treni-fermi-ore-lecce-milano-nessuno-stop-comuni-rischio-lodigiano-431e997c-553d-11ea-8418-2150c9ca483e.shtml|title=Coronavirus, treni fermi per ore a Lecce e Milano. I convogli non-fermano nei Comuni a rischio del Lodigiano|last=online|first=Redazione|date=2020-02-22|website=Corriere della Sera|language=it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/coronavirus_il_comune_di_milano_sospende_dal_lavoro_i_dipendenti_che_abitano_delle_zone_coinvolte-249252812/|title=Coronavirus, per una settimana didattica sospesa nelle universit\u00e0 lombarde. Comune di Milano e grandi aziende: i lavoratori a rischio restano a casa|date=2020-02-22|website=la Repubblica|language=it|access-date=2020-02-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200222165821/https://milano.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/02/22/news/coronavirus_il_comune_di_milano_sospende_dal_lavoro_i_dipendenti_che_abitano_delle_zone_coinvolte-249252812/|archive-date=22 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> Universities in Lombardy suspended all activities from 23 February.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://news.unipv.it/?p=46130|title=news.unipv \u2013 Coronavirus: Sospensione delle attivit\u00e0 didattiche dal 24/2 all\u20191/03|website=news.unipv|language=it-IT|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unimi.it/it/coronavirus-misure-urgenti-la-comunita-universitaria|title=Coronavirus: misure urgenti per la comunit\u00e0 universitaria {{!}} Universit\u00e0 degli Studi di Milano Statale|website=www.unimi.it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.unibg.it/node/9238|title=Sospensione precauzionale delle attivit\u00e0 didattiche {{!}} Universit\u00e0 degli studi di Bergamo|website=www.unibg.it|access-date=2020-02-23}}</ref>\n\nOn 8 March 2020, Prime Minister Conte extended the quarantine to all of [[Lombardy]] and 14 other northern provinces, [[2020 Italy coronavirus lockdown|putting more than a quarter of the national population under lockdown]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Coronavirus: Northern Italy quarantines 16 million people |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51787238 |website=BBC |accessdate=8 March 2020 |date=8 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308000026/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-middle-east-51787238 |archive-date=8 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> On the following day, he announced in a press conference that all measures previously applied only in the so-called \"red zones\" had been extended to the whole country, putting ''de facto'' 60 million people in lockdown. He later proceeded to officially sign the executive decree.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/09/europe/coronavirus-italy-lockdown-intl/index.html |title=All of Italy is in lockdown as coronavirus cases rise |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309190226/https://edition.cnn.com/2020/03/09/europe/coronavirus-italy-lockdown-intl/index.html |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/09/coronavirus-italy-prime-minister-country-lockdown?utm_term=Autofeed&CMP=twt_gu&utm_medium&utm_source=Twitter#Echobox=1583793579 |title=Coronavirus: Italian PM extends lockdown to entire country |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323165905/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/09/coronavirus-italy-prime-minister-country-lockdown?utm_term=Autofeed&CMP=twt_gu&utm_medium&utm_source=Twitter#Echobox=1583793579 |archive-date=23 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> This measure was described as the largest lockdown in human history.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/08/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-quarantine.html |title=On Day 1 of Broad Lockdown, a Debate Arises: Can Italians Follow the Rules? |access-date=9 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309095039/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/08/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-quarantine.html |archive-date=9 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2020/3/7/21169637/italy-lockdown-lombardy-coronavirus-outbreak|title=Italy locks down northern region in response to coronavirus outbreak|first=Kim|last=Lyons|date=7 March 2020|website=The Verge|accessdate=8 March 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308071135/https://www.theverge.com/2020/3/7/21169637/italy-lockdown-lombardy-coronavirus-outbreak|archive-date=8 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Horowitz |first1=Jason |title=Italy Locks Down Much of the Country\u2019s North Over the Coronavirus |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/07/world/europe/coronavirus-italy.html |accessdate=8 March 2020 |work=The New York Times |date=7 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308002308/https://www.nytimes.com/2020/03/07/world/europe/coronavirus-italy.html |archive-date=8 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=Italia>[https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-milan-lombardy-lockdowns/2020/03/07/403fcea2-60b3-11ea-ac50-18701e14e06d_story.html To contain coronavirus, Italy will restrict movement across much of its northern region, including the city of Milan] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200309111222/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/italy-coronavirus-milan-lombardy-lockdowns/2020/03/07/403fcea2-60b3-11ea-ac50-18701e14e06d_story.html |date=9 March 2020 }}, ''[[Washington Post]]'', Chico Harlan and Stefano Pitrelli, 7 March 2020. Retrieved 8 March 2020.</ref>\n\nThe lockdown measures, despite being widely approved by [[public opinion]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=De Feo |first1=Gianluca |title=Sondaggio Demos: gradimento per Conte alle stelle |url=https://www.youtrend.it/2020/03/20/sondaggio-demos-gradimento-per-conte-alle-stelle/ |website=YouTrend |accessdate=22 March 2020 |language=it-IT |date=20 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322105609/https://www.youtrend.it/2020/03/20/sondaggio-demos-gradimento-per-conte-alle-stelle/ |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> were also described as the largest suppression of [[constitutional right]]s in the history of the republic.<ref>{{cite news |title=Blog {{!}} Coronavirus, la sospensione delle libert\u00e0 costituzionali \u00e8 realt\u00e0. Ma per me ce la stiamo cavando bene |url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/18/coronavirus-la-sospensione-delle-liberta-costituzionali-e-realta-ma-per-me-ce-la-stiamo-cavando-bene/5739296/ |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Il Fatto Quotidiano |date=18 March 2020 |language=it-IT |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322105608/https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/18/coronavirus-la-sospensione-delle-liberta-costituzionali-e-realta-ma-per-me-ce-la-stiamo-cavando-bene/5739296/ |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Un uomo solo \u00e8 al comando dell\u2019Italia, e nessuno ha niente da ridire |url=https://www.linkiesta.it/2020/03/italia-coronavirus-conte-uomo-solo-al-comando/ |accessdate=4 March 2020 |work=Linkiesta |date=24 March 2020 |language=it-IT |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324114753/https://www.linkiesta.it/2020/03/italia-coronavirus-conte-uomo-solo-al-comando/ |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 20 March, the [[Ministry of Health (Italy)|Ministry of Health]] ordered tighter regulations on free movement. The new measures banned open-air sports and running, except individually and in close proximity of one's residence.  Parks, playgrounds and public green were closed down. Furthermore, movement across the country was further restricted, by banning \"any movement towards a residence different from the main one\", including holiday homes, during weekends and holidays.<ref>{{cite news |title=Le nuove restrizioni decise dal governo |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/20/ordinanza-coronavirus-attivita-sportiva-correre/ |accessdate=21 March 2020 |work=Il Post |date=20 March 2020 |language=it-IT |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321084610/https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/20/ordinanza-coronavirus-attivita-sportiva-correre/ |archive-date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> While on the following day, Conte announced further restrictions within the nationwide lockdown, by halting all non-essential production, industries and businesses in Italy,<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus, Milano trema: 634 casi in un giorno. Fontana chiama Conte: chiudere tutto, Esercito per strada |url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_milano_casi_contagi_lombardia_ultime_notizie-5121166.html |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=ilmessaggero.it |language=it |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320134113/https://www.ilmessaggero.it/italia/coronavirus_milano_casi_contagi_lombardia_ultime_notizie-5121166.html |archive-date=20 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> following the rise in the number of new cases and deaths in the previous days.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Farrer |first1=Martin |title=Italy: PM warns of worst crisis since WW2 as coronavirus deaths leap by almost 800 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/22/italian-pm-warns-of-worst-crisis-since-ww2-as-coronavirus-deaths-leap-by-almost-800 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=22 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322101342/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/mar/22/italian-pm-warns-of-worst-crisis-since-ww2-as-coronavirus-deaths-leap-by-almost-800 |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=De Angelis |first1=Alessandro |title=\"Chiudete tutto, anche le fabbriche\" (di A. De Angelis) |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/giorgio-gori-chiudete-tutto-anche-le-fabbriche_it_5e74ad81c5b63c3b648e6263 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=L'HuffPost |date=20 March 2020 |language=it |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200321172447/https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/giorgio-gori-chiudete-tutto-anche-le-fabbriche_it_5e74ad81c5b63c3b648e6263 |archive-date=21 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 24 March, in a live-streamed press conference, Conte announced a new decree approved by the Council of Ministers. The decree imposed higher fines for the violation of the restrictive measures, and a regulation of the relationship between government and Parliament during the emergency. It included also the possibility of reducing or suspending public and private transport, and gave the regional governments power to impose additional restrictive regulations in their Regions for a maximum of seven days before being confirmed by national decree.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy announces fines of up to \u20ac3,000 for breaking quarantine rules |url=https://www.thelocal.it/20200324/italy-announces-fines-of-up-to-3000-for-breaking-quarantine-rules |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=thelocal.it |date=24 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325091256/https://www.thelocal.it/20200324/italy-announces-fines-of-up-to-3000-for-breaking-quarantine-rules |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Cosa ha detto Giuseppe Conte |url=https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/24/decreto-restrizioni-sanzioni-coronavirus/ |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=Il Post |date=24 March 2020 |language=it-IT |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200325091256/https://www.ilpost.it/2020/03/24/decreto-restrizioni-sanzioni-coronavirus/ |archive-date=25 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nOn 1 April, Conte's government extended the period of lockdown until 13 April.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Henley |first1=Jon |title=Italy extends lockdown amid signs coronavirus infection rate is easing |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/01/italy-extends-lockdown-amid-signs-coronavirus-infection-rate-is-easing |accessdate=1 April 2020 |work=The Guardian |date=1 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200401135230/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/01/italy-extends-lockdown-amid-signs-coronavirus-infection-rate-is-easing |archive-date=1 April 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> While on 6 April, Conte announced a new economic stimulus plan, consisting of \u20ac200 billion of state-guaranteed loans to companies and additional \u20ac200 billion of guarantees to support exports.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Leali |first1=Giorgio |title=Italy adopts \u20ac400B liquidity plan amid coronavirus crisis |url=https://www.politico.eu/article/italy-adopts-e400b-liquidity-plan-amid-coronavirus-crisis/ |accessdate=7 April 2020 |work=POLITICO |date=6 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 April, Conte made further announcements extending the lockdown until the 3rd of May, allowing some specific businesses, like [[bookstore]]s\u00a0and [[silviculture]] activities, to reopen under specific safe measures.<ref>[https://www.repubblica.it/cronaca/2020/04/10/news/coronavirus_giuseppe_conte_riaperture-253677426/?ref=RHPPTP-BH-I253671889-C12-P2-S2.4-T1 Coronavirus, il premier Conte: \"Chiusura fino al 3 maggio, non possiamo cedere adesso\"]</ref> On the same day, he appointed a [[task force]] to relaunch Italy after the crisis; the team was led by [[Vittorio Colao]] and composed by a total of nineteen members, chosen among university professors, managers and public administration officers, which notably included [[Mariana Mazzucato]] and [[Enrico Giovannini]].<ref>[https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/politica/2020/04/10/coronavirus-ecco-task-force-per-fase_pxW186qVm9sQHlupjz2wGN.html Coronavirus, ecco la task force per la Fase 2]</ref>\n\n===Foreign policy===\n{{See also|List of official trips made by Giuseppe Conte}}\n[[File:President Trump Meets with the Prime Minister of the Italian Republic (49173499077).jpg|thumb|Conte with U.S. President [[Donald Trump]] in December 2019]]\nSince the beginning of his term as prime minister, Conte's [[foreign policy]] has been characterized by a lenient approach to Russia. For example, he advocated the repeal of international sanctions against Russia, which according to him damage the [[Italian economy]].<ref>[https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/mondo/putin-a-roma-conte-contro-le-sanzioni-a-mosca-sono-un-danno-per-tutti-_3218344-201902a.shtml Putin a Roma, Conte contro le sanzioni a Mosca: \"Sono un danno per tutti\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190704215947/https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/mondo/putin-a-roma-conte-contro-le-sanzioni-a-mosca-sono-un-danno-per-tutti-_3218344-201902a.shtml |date=4 July 2019 }}, TgCom24</ref> He also considered Russia a strategic partner in the [[War on Terror|fight]] against [[Islamic terrorism]].<ref>{{cite news|language=it|url=http://www.askanews.it/video/2018/06/05/conte-appartenenza-alla-nato-ma-apriremo-alla-russia-20180605_video_16453330/|title=Conte: appartenenza alla Nato ma apriremo alla Russia|agency=[[ASCA (news agency)|ASCA]]|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401180005/http://www.askanews.it/video/2018/06/05/conte-appartenenza-alla-nato-ma-apriremo-alla-russia-20180605_video_16453330/|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> However, Conte stressed that under his leadership Italy will remain an active member of [[NATO]] and a close ally of the [[United States]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/conte-restiamo-nella-nato-e-con-usa-ma-via-sanzioni-alla-russia_3144252-201802a.shtml|title=Conte: restiamo nella Nato e con Usa ma via sanzioni alla Russia|language=it|date=5 July 2018|trans-title=Conte: We remain in NATO and with the USA but via sanctions against Russia|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401192645/https://www.tgcom24.mediaset.it/politica/conte-restiamo-nella-nato-e-con-usa-ma-via-sanzioni-alla-russia_3144252-201802a.shtml|archive-date=1 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The good relations between the two administration became evident in March 2020, during the [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic|coronavirus pandemic]]. After a phone call with Conte, Russian president [[Vladimir Putin]] arranged the [[Russian Armed Forces|Russian army]] to send military medics, special disinfection vehicles and other medical equipment to Italy, which was the European country hardest hit by coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news |title=Russian army to send coronavirus help to Italy after Putin phone call |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-russia-italy/russian-army-to-send-coronavirus-help-to-italy-after-putin-phone-call-idUSKBN219081 |accessdate=22 March 2020 |work=Reuters |date=22 March 2020 |language=en |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200322092901/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-russia-italy/russian-army-to-send-coronavirus-help-to-italy-after-putin-phone-call-idUSKBN219081 |archive-date=22 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nDuring his premiership, Conte built a close relationship with [[U.S. President]] [[Donald Trump]]. Since the beginning of Conte's government, Trump considered him a key ally during international meetings.<ref>[https://www.thelocal.it/20180615/trump-praises-conte-as-very-strong-on-immigration Trump praises Conte as 'very strong' on immigration], ''The Local''</ref>  On 8 and 9 June, Conte participated in his first [[44th G7 summit|G7 summit]], hosted by Prime Minister [[Justin Trudeau]] in [[Canada]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tg24.sky.it/mondo/photogallery/2018/06/08/g7-conte-incontro-leader.html|title=G7, il primo incontro del premier Conte con gli altri leader. FOTO - Sky TG24|date=8 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233435/https://tg24.sky.it/mondo/photogallery/2018/06/08/g7-conte-incontro-leader.html|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> During the summit, he was the only leader to back President Trump and his proposal to readmit Russia into the G7.<ref>{{cite news|agency=Reuters|date=8 June 2018|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/g7-summit-italy-russia/italys-new-pm-backs-trump-on-re-admitting-russia-into-the-g7-idUSR1N1SZ002|title=Italy's new PM backs Trump on re-admitting Russia into the G7|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331004627/https://www.reuters.com/article/g7-summit-italy-russia/italys-new-pm-backs-trump-on-re-admitting-russia-into-the-g7-idUSR1N1SZ002|archive-date=31 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> However, he later assumed a more [[pro-Europe]]an view, shared by the other five leaders, condemning [[Trump tariffs]] on [[steel]] and [[aluminium]] exported by the [[European Union]].<ref>{{cite news|date=9 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|url=https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2018/06/09/news/conte_vede_macron_al_g7_e_non_rompe_con_l_ue_il_tweet_di_macron_condividiamo_l_europa_-198544751/|title=G7, Trudeau: \"Documento finale firmato da tutti\". Trump va via e chiede riammissione Russia|work=la Repubblica|language=it|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190331004636/https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2018/06/09/news/conte_vede_macron_al_g7_e_non_rompe_con_l_ue_il_tweet_di_macron_condividiamo_l_europa_-198544751/|archive-date=31 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On the following day, Conte was thanked for his positions on Russia and his populist stance by President Trump, who invited him to the [[White House]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2018/06/09/trump-italy-prime-minister-white-house-giuseppe-conte-635009|title=Trump: Italy's populist prime minister to visit White House|author=Brent D. Griffiths|website=[[Politico]]|date=9 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233237/https://www.politico.com/story/2018/06/09/trump-italy-prime-minister-white-house-giuseppe-conte-635009|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 28 June, Conte participated in his first [[European Council]] meeting and blocked a joint EU trade and defense statement criticizing Trump's tariff policy.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-eu-summit-conte-idUSKBN1JO2UF|title=Italy blocks joint text on trade, defense at EU summit|date=28 June 2018|agency=[[Reuters]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233208/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-eu-summit-conte-idUSKBN1JO2UF|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2018, Trump praised Conte, describing him as a \"really great leader\" and \"very strong on immigration\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://video.corriere.it/trump-il-primo-ministro-italiano-conte-fantastico-severo-sull-immigrazione-questo-momento-paga/d065ab42-70a9-11e8-8f08-e72858c58491|title=Trump: \"Il primo ministro italiano Conte \u00e8 fantastico. \u00c8 severo sull'immigrazione e in questo momento paga\"|date=15 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233402/https://video.corriere.it/trump-il-primo-ministro-italiano-conte-fantastico-severo-sull-immigrazione-questo-momento-paga/d065ab42-70a9-11e8-8f08-e72858c58491|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Trump also endorsed Conte during the [[2019 Italian government formation#Political crisis|2019 Italian political crisis]], hoping that he could remain Prime Minister.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.agi.it/politica/trump_endorsement_conte-6090415/news/2019-08-27/|title=L'endorsement di Trump per il Conte-bis|website=Agi|access-date=30 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830123932/https://www.agi.it/politica/trump_endorsement_conte-6090415/news/2019-08-27/|archive-date=30 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> On 31 March 2020, President Trump announced that the [[United States]] would send 100 million dollars of medical aids to Italy.<ref>[https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/31/coronavirus-trump-annuncia-100-milioni-di-dollari-di-aiuti-allitalia-giuseppi-era-molto-contento-poi-mostra-macchina-per-test-rapido/5754858/ Trump annuncia: \"Aiuti sanitari all'Italia per 100 milioni di dollari\", compresi kit per i test veloci], ''Huffington Post''</ref> After few days, during an interview at the [[NBC]], Conte described Trump as \"Italy's most true and loyal friend\".<ref>[https://www.washingtonexaminer.com/news/italian-prime-minister-thanks-trump-for-being-countrys-true-and-loyal-friend-through-pandemic Italian prime minister thanks Trump for being country's 'true and loyal friend' through pandemic], ''Washington Examiner''</ref> On 11 Apri, Trump issued an [[executive order]] in which he allowed U.S. militaries deployed in Italy to assist Italian law enforcement in facing the crisis.<ref>[https://www.repubblica.it/esteri/2020/04/11/news/l_ordine_esecutivo_di_trump_per_l_italia_contro_il_coronavirus_mobilitiamo_anche_i_nosri_30_mila_soldati_-253733750/ 'ordine esecutivo di Trump: \"Per l'Italia contro il coronavirus mobilitiamo anche i nostri 30 mila soldati\"], ''la Repubblica''</ref>\n\n[[File:-G7Biarritz (48616362963).jpg|thumb|left|Conte and other leaders at the [[45th G7 summit]] in Biarritz, France]]\nAt the beginning of his political career, Conte was described as a [[populist]]\u00a0and [[Eurosceptic]] politician, openly critic towards the EU, whose economic and financial rules were described as \"old and outdated\".<ref>[https://www.politico.eu/article/giuseppe-conte-interview-shake-up-europe-italy/ Italian PM: We want to shake things up in Europe], ''Politico''</ref> However, he later toned down his Eurosceptic rhetoric, thus still remaining a vocal [[anti-austerity]] leader, as it became evidence during the 2020 coronavirus pandemic, which severely affected Europe.<ref>[https://www.ilgazzettino.it/italia/primopiano/conte_sente_von_der_leyen_italia_non_accettera_compromessi_al_ribasso_italia_europa_eurobond_si_mes_no-5158555.html Conte sente Von Der Leyen: \u00abL'Italia non accetter\u00e0 compromessi al ribasso\u00bb. L'Italia all'Europa: \u00abEurobond s\u00ec, Mes no\u00bb] ''Il Gazzettino''</ref>\n\nIn March 2019, Conte and the Chinese President [[Xi Jinping]] [[2019 Xi Jinping Italy and France visit|signed in Rome]] 29 economic and institutional agreements amounting to 2.5 billion [[euro]]s, including a [[memorandum of understanding]] vis-\u00e0-vis the [[Belt and Road Initiative]] investments program.<ref>{{cite news|date=23 March 2019|accessdate=1 April 2019|url=https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/03/23/news/xi_jinping_cina_italia_villa_madama_accordi_commerciali_conte_mattarella_di_maio-222293765/|title=Cina-Italia, firmati gli accordi. Di Maio: \"Valgono 2,5 miliardi ma con un potenziale di 20\". Gelo con Salvini|work=la Repubblica|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233258/https://www.repubblica.it/politica/2019/03/23/news/xi_jinping_cina_italia_villa_madama_accordi_commerciali_conte_mattarella_di_maio-222293765/|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.quotidiano.net/politica/xi-jinping-in-italia-1.4504422|title=Xi Jinping a Roma, firmato il Memorandum su Via della Seta. \"Grazie Italia, un successo\"|publisher=QuotidianoNet|date=23 March 2019|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233249/https://www.quotidiano.net/politica/xi-jinping-in-italia-1.4504422|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In August 2019, he took part, as caretaker Prime Minister, in the [[45th G7 summit]] in [[Biarritz]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/conte-resiste-nel-fortino-dorato-di-biarritz_it_5d62a7c1e4b0b59d2576492f|title=Conte resiste nel 'fortino dorato' di Biarritz (da Biarritz A. Mauro)|date=25 August 2019|website=L'HuffPost|access-date=27 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190827205147/https://www.huffingtonpost.it/entry/conte-resiste-nel-fortino-dorato-di-biarritz_it_5d62a7c1e4b0b59d2576492f|archive-date=27 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The main topics of the summit included [[global trade]], [[climate change]], taxing technology companies,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2019/08/24/world/24reuters-g7-summit-trump.html |title=Trump Arrives in Biarritz for Testing G7 Summit |date=24 August 2019 |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=27 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825014058/https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2019/08/24/world/24reuters-g7-summit-trump.html |archive-date=25 August 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> but also [[Iran nuclear deal]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2019/08/24/world/24reuters-g7-summit-tusk.html |title=G7 Summit to Be 'a Difficult Test of Unity': EU's Tusk |date=24 August 2019 |newspaper=The New York Times |access-date=27 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825014152/https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2019/08/24/world/24reuters-g7-summit-tusk.html |archive-date=25 August 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> and [[2019 Amazon wildfires]].<ref name=\"theguardian_Phillips_20190822\">{{Cite news| issn = 0261-3077| last1 = Phillips| first1 = Tom| last2 = correspondent| first2 = Latin America| title = Amazon rainforest fires: Macron calls for 'international crisis' to lead G7 discussions| work = The Guardian| access-date = 23 August 2019| date = 23 August 2019| url = https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/23/amazon-rainforest-fires-macron-calls-for-international-crisis-to-lead-g7-discussions| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190914153151/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2019/aug/23/amazon-rainforest-fires-macron-calls-for-international-crisis-to-lead-g7-discussions| archive-date = 14 September 2019| url-status = live}}</ref>\n\nConte criticized the [[2019 Turkish offensive into north-eastern Syria]]. He stated that the offensive puts the region's civilians and stability in jeopardy.<ref>[https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/10/world-reacts-turkey-military-operation-northeast-syria-191009181335266.html \"World reacts to Turkey's military operation in northeast Syria\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191013104614/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2019/10/world-reacts-turkey-military-operation-northeast-syria-191009181335266.html |date=13 October 2019 }}. Al Jazeera. 10 October 2019.</ref>\n\nIn January 2020, the situation of the [[Libyan Civil War (2014\u2013present)|Libyan Civil War]] became increasingly worrying, with the troops of field marshal [[Khalifa Haftar]] approaching [[Tripoli]]. During the crisis, Prime Minister Conte had a series of bilateral meetings in Rome both with Haftar and [[Fayez al-Sarraj]], the Chairman of the [[Presidential Council (Libya)|Presidential Council of Libya]], who are considered two of the main contenders in the civil war.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/libia-sarraj-palazzo-chigi-incontrare-conte-ACnuMOBB |title=Libia, Haftar annuncia il cessate il fuoco. L\u2019incontro Conte-Sarraj |access-date=12 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112102519/https://www.ilsole24ore.com/art/libia-sarraj-palazzo-chigi-incontrare-conte-ACnuMOBB |archive-date=12 January 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> After pressures from the international community, on 12 January Haftar announced a [[ceasefire]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/libyan-forces-loyal-haftar-announce-conditional-ceasefire-200112004206081.html |title=Libyan forces loyal to Haftar announce conditional ceasefire |access-date=12 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200112102519/https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2020/01/libyan-forces-loyal-haftar-announce-conditional-ceasefire-200112004206081.html |archive-date=12 January 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Political views and public image==\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte EC.jpg|thumb|right|220px|Conte at the [[European Council]]]]\nDuring his first cabinet, Conte has often been considered a [[Neo-nationalism|neo-nationalist]] politician,<ref>{{cite news|work=[[Financial Times]]|date=25 May 2018|title=Market turmoil hits Conte's road to Rome|url=https://www.ft.com/content/7ad0ff6a-6028-11e8-9334-2218e7146b04}}</ref> however, since September 2019, when he became the head of a [[centre-left]] coalition government, he toned down his nationalist rhetoric.<ref>[https://www.lastampa.it/topnews/primo-piano/2019/08/30/news/juncker-loda-la-metamorfosi-di-conte-e-la-rivendica-e-come-con-tsipras-1.37394484 Juncker loda la metamorfosi di Conte e la rivendica: \u201c\u00c8 come con Tsipras\u201d], ''La Stampa''</ref> Despite being labeled as a post-ideological leader,<ref>[https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/in-edicola/articoli/2019/09/20/dalema-benedice-il-nuovo-conte-post-ideologico-tra-selfie-e-salsicce/5465121/ D\u2019Alema benedice il nuovo Conte post-ideologico, tra selfie e salsicce], ''Il Fatto Quotidiano''</ref> Conte described his political ideal as \"new [[Renaissance humanism|humanism]]\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/esteri/2019/05/09/conte-mondo-non-piu-eurocentrico-italia-per-nuovo-umanesimo_lnB5GN6crUz1kLLJzdScaI.html|title=Conte: \"Mondo non-pi\u00f9 eurocentrico, Italia per nuovo umanesimo\"|website=Adnkronos|access-date=29 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190829090056/https://www.adnkronos.com/fatti/esteri/2019/05/09/conte-mondo-non-piu-eurocentrico-italia-per-nuovo-umanesimo_lnB5GN6crUz1kLLJzdScaI.html|archive-date=29 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fanpage.it/politica/il-testo-completo-del-discorso-di-giuseppe-conte-al-senato/|title=Il testo completo del discorso di Giuseppe Conte al Senato|website=Fanpage|access-date=29 August 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190831215502/https://www.fanpage.it/politica/il-testo-completo-del-discorso-di-giuseppe-conte-al-senato/|archive-date=31 August 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nDuring an interview in 2018, Conte said he used to vote for the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] before approaching the M5S during the late 2010s.<ref>[https://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/non-sono-dei-5-stelle-spunta-video-che-sbugiarda-conte-1746983.html \"Non sono dei 5 Stelle\", ma spunta un video \u200bche sbugiarda Conte], ''Il Giornale''</ref> He also added that today \"the ideological schemes of the 20th century are no longer adequate to represent the current [[political system]]\" and it should be \"more important and correct to evaluate the work of a political force on how it is positioned on the respect of fundamental [[Human rights|rights]] and freedoms\".<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-ecco-chi-e-il-nome-piu-quotato-per-guidare-il-governo-lega-m5s/4369287/|title=Giuseppe Conte, ecco chi \u00e8 il presidente del consiglio del governo Lega-M5s|date=31 May 2018|work=Il Fatto Quotidiano|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180527064732/https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/20/giuseppe-conte-ecco-chi-e-il-nome-piu-quotato-per-guidare-il-governo-lega-m5s/4369287/|archive-date=27 May 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn his inaugural speech at the Senate on 5 June 2018,<ref name=\"rep_050618\">{{cite web|title=Il discorso di Conte in Senato, la versione integrale|url=http://download.repubblica.it/pdf/2018/politica/presidente05062018.pdf|work=[[la Repubblica]]|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191215113342/http://download.repubblica.it/pdf/2018/politica/presidente05062018.pdf|archive-date=15 December 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media|date=5 June 2018|title=Dichiarazioni programmatiche - L'intervento del Presidente Conte al Senato|medium=official video|language=it|url=http://www.governo.it/media/dichiarazioni-programmatiche/9515|accessdate=1 April 2019|location=Italy|publisher=Governo Italiano - Presidenza del Consiglio dei Ministri|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014835/http://www.governo.it/media/dichiarazioni-programmatiche/9515|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> in response to attacks on government political forces accused of being populist and [[anti-establishment]], Conte replied that \"if populism is the attitude of the ruling class to listen to the people's needs [...] and if anti-establishment means aiming at introducing a new system able to remove old privileges and encrusted power, well, these political forces deserve both these epithets\".<ref>[https://www.nytimes.com/2018/06/05/world/europe/italy-government-giuseppe-conte.html \"Italy's New Populist Government Articulates Vision, but Few Specifics\"] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180611190303/https://www.nytimes.com/2018/06/05/world/europe/italy-government-giuseppe-conte.html |date=11 June 2018 }}.</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Highlights: Italian Prime Minister Giuseppe Conte's inaugural speech|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-politics-speech-highlights/highlights-italian-prime-minister-giuseppe-contes-inaugural-speech-idUSKCN1J118M|agency=[[Reuters]]|date=5 June 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402002640/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-italy-politics-speech-highlights/highlights-italian-prime-minister-giuseppe-contes-inaugural-speech-idUSKCN1J118M|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite AV media|date=5 June 2018|title=Conte: \"Noi populisti? Ascoltiamo la gente|medium=video|language=Italian|url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/video/politica/conte-noi-populisti-ascoltiamo-gente-1536881.html|accessdate=1 April 2019|location=Italy|work=[[il Giornale]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014704/http://www.ilgiornale.it/video/politica/conte-noi-populisti-ascoltiamo-gente-1536881.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nHe also opposed the \"hypertrophy of Italian laws\", advocating the repeal of useless laws and supported a simplification of [[bureaucracy]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/primopiano/politica/conte_premier_governo_m5s_lega-3744907.html|date=21 May 2018|author=Diodato Pirone|title=Conte, giurista anti-burocrazia con un passato a sinistra|trans-title=Conte, former anti-bureaucracy lawyer joins the left|work=[[Il Messaggero]]|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014743/https://www.ilmessaggero.it/primopiano/politica/conte_premier_governo_m5s_lega-3744907.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> As a professor, Conte strongly opposed the [[school reform]] legislation promoted by [[Matteo Renzi]]'s government in 2015, known as \"The Good School\", which, according to him, must be completely revised.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.orizzontescuola.it/giuseppe-conte-rivedere-pressoche-integralmente-la-riforma-della-cattiva-scuola/|title=Giuseppe Conte: rivedere, pressoch\u00e9 integralmente, la riforma della cattiva scuola|date=21 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014725/https://www.orizzontescuola.it/giuseppe-conte-rivedere-pressoche-integralmente-la-riforma-della-cattiva-scuola/|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nAccording to public opinion surveys, Conte's approval rating was always above 50% during all his first cabinet, then dropping to 40% in the early months of his second government.<ref>[https://www.youtrend.it/2020/03/20/sondaggio-demos-gradimento-per-conte-alle-stelle/ Sondaggio Demos: gradimento per Conte alle stelle], ''YouTrend''</ref> However, in March 2020, amid the coronavirus crisis, his approval rating rose to 71%, one of the highest rating ever for an Italian Prime Minister.<ref>[https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2020/03/19/coronavirus-fiducia-record-per-conte-e-il-governo-hanno-il-sostegno-di-7-italiani-su-10-tra-i-leader-zaia-piace-piu-di-salvini/5741739/ Coronavirus, fiducia record per Conte e il governo: hanno il sostegno di 7 italiani su 10. Tra i leader Zaia piace pi\u00f9 di Salvini], ''Il Fatto Quotidiano''</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nGiuseppe Conte married Valentina Fico, a lawyer from [[Rome]] and daughter of a former director of the Santa Cecilia [[music school|conservatory]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.donnemagazine.it/giuseppe-conte-moglie/|title=Valentina Fico, chi \u00e8 l'ex moglie di Giuseppe Conte|first=Olga|last=Luce|date=29 August 2019|website=Donne Magazine|access-date=10 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324011119/https://www.donnemagazine.it/giuseppe-conte-moglie/|archive-date=24 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref> They have a child, Niccol\u00f2, born in 2007.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.it/news/politica/2018/05/21/giuseppe-conte-chi-e-il-professore-di-sinistra-chiamato-a-fare-il-premier|title=Giuseppe Conte, chi \u00e8 il professore (di sinistra) che potrebbe diventare premier|date=21 May 2018|access-date=10 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190724085132/https://www.vanityfair.it/news/politica/2018/05/21/giuseppe-conte-chi-e-il-professore-di-sinistra-chiamato-a-fare-il-premier|archive-date=24 July 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> However, they divorced after a few years.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://social.excite.it/Attualita/Politica/Ecco-chi-e-l-ex-moglie-di-Giuseppe-Conte|title=Ecco chi \u00e8 l'ex moglie di Giuseppe Conte|website=Excite}}</ref> Conte is currently engaged with Olivia Paladino (born 1979),<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://social.excite.it/Attualita/Politica/Ecco-chi-e-Olivia-Paladino-l-affascinante-fidanzata-del-premier-Conte|title=Ecco chi \u00e8 Olivia Paladino, l'affascinante fidanzata del premier Conte|website=Excite}}</ref> daughter of the Roman entrepreneur Cesare Paladino and the [[Sweden|Swedish]] actress [[Ewa Aulin]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.letteradonna.it/it/articoli/ritratti/2018/06/04/giuseppe-conte-compagna-olivia-paladino/26009/|title=Chi \u00e8 Olivia Paladino, la compagna del premier Giuseppe Conte - LetteraDonna|access-date=10 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612144331/https://www.letteradonna.it/it/articoli/ritratti/2018/06/04/giuseppe-conte-compagna-olivia-paladino/26009/|archive-date=12 June 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nConte is an avid supporter of [[A.S. Roma]], a passion that arose when he studied in [[Rome]] at the Sapienza University.<ref>[https://www.tpi.it/news/giuseppe-conte-squadra-calcio-20180606128675/ Quali sono le squadre del cuore di Giuseppe Conte e degli ex premier italiani], TPI</ref>\n\nHe is a [[Roman Catholic]] and a devout votary to [[Padre Pio|Padre Pio of Pietrelcina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/devoto-padre-pio-secchione-e-sinistra-financial-times-1530345.html|title=Devoto di Padre Pio, secchione e di sinistra. Il \"Financial Times\" lo stronca: un novellino|work=il Giornale|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190402014716/http://www.ilgiornale.it/news/politica/devoto-padre-pio-secchione-e-sinistra-financial-times-1530345.html|archive-date=2 April 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Controversies==\n[[File:Giuseppe Conte Quirinale 2019.jpg|thumb|220px|Giuseppe Conte in August 2019]]\nOn 21 May 2018, when Conte was proposed to President Mattarella as candidate for prime minister,<ref name=bbc/> ''[[The New York Times]]'' questioned his summer stays at [[New York University]] (NYU) listed in his official [[curriculum vitae]]<ref name=cv/> in an article asserting that a NYU spokeswoman could not find Conte in university \"records as either a student or faculty member\".<ref name=nyt/><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/22/giuseppe-conte-nyt-nel-cv-studi-alla-new-york-university-non-risultano-allateneo-accademici-visiting-scholar-non-sono-registrati/4372768/|title=Giuseppe Conte, Nyt: \"Nel cv studi alla New York University che non-risultano all'ateneo\". Accademici: \"Visiting scholar non-sono registrati\"|work=Il Fatto Quotidiano|date=22 May 2018|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190330233208/https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2018/05/22/giuseppe-conte-nyt-nel-cv-studi-alla-new-york-university-non-risultano-allateneo-accademici-visiting-scholar-non-sono-registrati/4372768/|archive-date=30 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Similar doubts arose concerning his study period in France at the [[Sorbonne University]].<ref name=theguardian>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/may/22/italy-giuseppe-conte-cv-new-york-university|title=Doubts raised over academic credentials of proposed Italian PM|author=Kirchgaessner, Stephanie|author2=Giuffrida, Angela|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328231104/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2018/may/22/italy-giuseppe-conte-cv-new-york-university|archive-date=28 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nThe following day, the [[Associated Press]] reported in an article published also by ''The New York Times'' that the NYU spokeswoman added that \"while Mr. Conte had no official status at NYU, he was granted permission to conduct research in the NYU law library\" during the period listed in his official curriculum vitae.<ref name=cv/><ref>{{cite news|title=The Latest: Italy PM pick had 'no official status' at NYU|url=https://www.apnews.com/d7e4f88200524150806030baec55b919|agency=Associated Press|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190328231037/https://www.apnews.com/d7e4f88200524150806030baec55b919|archive-date=28 March 2019|url-status=live}}<br />{{cite news|title=The Latest: Italy PM pick had 'no official status' at NYU|url=https://www.nytimes.com/aponline/2018/05/22/world/europe/ap-eu-italy-politics-the-latest.html|work=The New York Times|agency=[[Associated Press]]|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019}}</ref> Similarly, the [[Duquesne University]] of [[Pittsburgh]] and the [[University of Malta]] found no record of him in their archives,<ref>{{cite news|author1=Lorenzo De Cicco|author2=Francesca Pierantozzi|author3=Flavio Pompetti|date=22 May 2018|title=Conte, dopo New York anche le universit\u00e0 di Malta e Pittsburgh: \"Non ha mai studiato o insegnato ufficialmente qui\"|url=https://www.ilmessaggero.it/primopiano/politica/giuseppe_conte_curriculum_universita_pittsburgh-3748598.html|work=Il Messaggero|language=it|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329025146/https://www.ilmessaggero.it/primopiano/politica/giuseppe_conte_curriculum_universita_pittsburgh-3748598.html|archive-date=29 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> although it was confirmed that Conte held lectures at the old university building in [[Valletta]], Malta, for the Foundation for International Studies.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20180522/local/did-italys-prime-minister-candidate-lecture-in-Malta.679733|title=Italian prime minister candidate says he lectured in Malta - but the University has no record of him|newspaper=Times of Malta|date=22 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329002409/https://www.timesofmalta.com/articles/view/20180522/local/did-italys-prime-minister-candidate-lecture-in-Malta.679733|archive-date=29 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> [[Yale University]], contacted by another newspaper, confirmed that he was a visiting scholar there for three months.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_25/conte-curriculum-yale-conferma-visiting-scholar-tre-mesi-eabf3c82-5fa7-11e8-989a-8761ed483ece.shtml|title=Conte e il curriculum, Yale conferma: \"Visiting scholar per tre mesi\"|author=Sarcina, Giuseppe|work=Corriere della Sera|date=25 May 2018|accessdate=1 April 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180612140217/https://www.corriere.it/politica/18_maggio_25/conte-curriculum-yale-conferma-visiting-scholar-tre-mesi-eabf3c82-5fa7-11e8-989a-8761ed483ece.shtml|archive-date=12 June 2018|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nMoreover, Conte stated in his CV that he had worked for his legal studies at the Kulturinstitut in [[Vienna]], Austria, but this is a language school, not a law school.<ref name=theguardian/>\n\n==Authored books==\n*{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gpBBDwAAQBAJ|title=Il volontariato. Libert\u00e0 dei privati e mediazione giuridica dello Stato|last=Conte|first=Giuseppe|last2=Landini|first2=Sara|year=1996|isbn=9788899459772|publisher=Pioda|location=[[Rome]]|author-mask=with}}\n*{{cite book|title=Matrimonio civile e teoria della simulazione|year=1996|publisher=Pioda|location=[[Rome]]|oclc=1088868085}}\n*{{cite book|title=La simulazione del matrimonio nella teoria del negozio giuridico|year=1999|isbn=9788813220068|publisher=CEDAM|location=[[Padua]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=Le regole della solidarit\u00e0. Iniziative non-profit dei privati e mediazione dei pubblici poteri|year=2001|publisher=Pioda|location=[[Rome]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=Il danno non-patrimoniale|year=2018|publisher=Giuffr\u00e8|location=[[Milan]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=La formazione del contratto|year=2018|isbn=9788814203770|publisher=Giuffr\u00e8|location=[[Milan]]}}\n*{{cite book|title=L'impresa responsabile|year=2018|isbn=9788814227035|publisher=Giuffr\u00e8|location=[[Milan]]}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Commons category}}\n*University of Florence [https://www.unifi.it/p-doc2-2016-0-A-2b333b2d322c-1.html personal page] (including CV and publication list in English)\n*{{Scopus id}}\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-off}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Paolo Gentiloni]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Prime Minister of Italy]]|years=2018\u2013present}}\n{{s-inc}}\n|-\n{{s-prec|italy}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Roberto Fico]]|as=[[List of Presidents of the Italian Chamber of Deputies|President of the Chamber of Deputies]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Italian order of precedence|Order of precedence of Italy]]<br />''{{small|as Prime Minister}}''|years=}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Marta Cartabia]]<br />''{{small|{{nowrap|as [[Constitutional Court of Italy|President of the Constitutional Court]]}}}}''}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Prime Ministers of Italy}}\n{{Offices of italy}}\n{{European Council}}\n{{Current NATO leaders}}\n{{Current G8 Leaders}}\n{{Current G20 Leaders}}\n{{Conte I Cabinet}}\n{{Conte II Cabinet}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Conte, Giuseppe}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:Conte I Cabinet]]\n[[Category:Conte II Cabinet]]\n[[Category:Italian jurists]]\n[[Category:Italian Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Foggia]]\n[[Category:Prime Ministers of Italy]]\n[[Category:Roma Tre University faculty]]\n[[Category:Sapienza University of Rome alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Florence faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Malta faculty]]\n[[Category:University of Sassari faculty]]\n[[Category:Yale Law School alumni]]\n[[Category:Independent politicians in Italy]]\n", "name_user": "Ritchie92", "label": "safe", "comment": "Filled in 3 bare reference(s) with reFill 2", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Giuseppe_Conte"}
{"title_page": "Latvian National Symphony Orchestra", "text_new": "{{short description|Latvian symphony orchestra}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{use list-defined references|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox orchestra\n| name                = Latvian National Symphony Orchestra\n| type                = \n| native_name         = {{nobreak|Latvijas Nacion\u0101lais simfoniskais or\u0137estris}}\n| native_name_lang    = lv\n| short_name          = \n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| alt                 = \n| former_name         = {{ubl|Latvian Radio Centre Orchestra|Latvian RSO}}\n| founded             = {{Start date|1926}}\n| disbanded           = \n| later_name          = \n| location            = [[Riga]], Latvia\n| concert_hall        = [[Large Guild, Riga|Great Guild Hall]], [[Riga]]\n| principal_conductor = [[Andris Poga]]\n| music_director      = \n| website             = {{url|lnso.lv}}\n}}\nThe '''Latvian National Symphony Orchestra''' (LNSO), {{lang-lv|'''Latvijas Nacion\u0101lais simfoniskais or\u0137estris'''|italic=no}}, is the principal [[symphony orchestra]] of [[Latvia]]. It was founded in 1926 as the '''Latvian Radio Centre Orchestra''' by the conductor [[Arv\u012bds P\u0101rups]], and was the first permanent orchestra in the country.{{r|grove}}  \n\nLNSO's mission is to offer the Latvian public musical performances of the whole orchestral repertoire from the classics to contemporary compositions and to introduce audiences abroad with [[Latvian Music|Latvian music]]. One of the LNSO's most important priorities is to attract young listeners with educational programmes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.lnso.lv/par-lnso|title=PAR LNSO|website=LNSO|language=en|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\nThe LNSO is a six-time winner of the [http://www.muzikasbalva.lv/ Latvian Grand Music Award] (1993, 2009, 2012, 2013, 2016 and 2019).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.muzikasbalva.lv/laureati|title=Liel\u0101 m\u016bzikas balva - Laure\u0101ti|website=www.muzikasbalva.lv|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\nSince 2013 the music director of the LNSO is [[Andris Poga]]. Beginning with the 2021/2022 season Poga will take up the position of chief conductor of the [[Stavanger Symphony Orchestra]].\n\nThe LNSO\u2019s past guest conductors include Latvians [[Arv\u012bds Jansons]], [[Mariss Jansons]] and [[Andris Nelsons]], as well as [[Valery Gergiev]], [[Neeme J\u00e4rvi]], [[Paavo J\u00e4rvi]], [[Kirill Kondrashin]], [[Kurt Masur]], [[Krzysztof Penderecki]], [[Gennady Rozhdestvensky]], [[Yevgeny Svetlanov]], [[Yuri Simonov]], and many others.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.lnso.lv/par-lnso|title=PAR LNSO|website=LNSO|language=en|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\nIn recent years the LNSO has performed at the [[Philharmonie de Paris]] and the [[Th\u00e9\u00e2tre des Champs-\u00c9lys\u00e9es|Th\u00e9\u00e2tre des Champs Elys\u00e9es]], the [[Alte Oper]] [[Frankfurt]] and the Grand Th\u00e9\u00e2tre of [[Aix-en-Provence]] among many other European [[concert halls]]. The orchestra has participated in music festivals in [[France]], [[Germany]] and [[Switzerland]] as well as the [[Bratislava Music Festival]]. On its most recent tours the LNSO teamed up with world-renowned soloists such as Latvian violinist [[Baiba Skride]], cellist [[Alexander Kniazev|Alexander Knyazev]], pianists [[Nicholas Angelich]], [[Boris Berezovsky (pianist)|Boris Berezovsky]], [[Lukas Geniu\u0161as]] and [[Lucas Debargue]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.lnso.lv/par-lnso|title=PAR LNSO|website=LNSO|language=en|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to regular symphonic concerts, the orchestra also broadcasts and records. Its primary performance venue is the [[Large Guild, Riga|Great Guild Hall]] in [[Riga]].{{r|szu|page=307}}\n\n== Music Directors and Chief Conductors ==\n\n* [[Arv\u012bds P\u0101rups]] (1926\u20131928)\n* [[J\u0101nis Medi\u0146\u0161]] (1928\u20131944)\n* [[Dmitrijs Ku\u013ckovs]] (1945\u20131949)\n* [[Edgars Tons]] (1963\u20131966)\n* [[Leon\u012bds V\u012bgners]] (1949\u20131963, 1966\u20131974)\n* [[Vassily Sinaisky]] (1975\u20131987)\n* [[Paul M\u00e4gi]] (1990\u20131994)\n* [[Terje Mikkelsen]] (1997\u20132001)\n* [[Olari Elts]] (2001\u20132005)\n* [[Karel Mark Chichon]] (2009\u20132012)\n* [[Andris Poga]] (2013\u2013present)\n\n==Selected recordings==\n* [[Inessa Galante]] Debut recital Latvian National Symphony Orchestra Conducted by [[Alexander Vilumanis]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=grove>Joachim Braun, Arnolds Kloti\u0146\u0161, Martin Boiko (2001). [http://www.oxfordmusiconline.com/grovemusic/view/10.1093/gmo/9781561592630.001.0001/omo-9781561592630-e-0000042158 Latvia]. ''Grove Music Online''. {{subscription required}}.</ref>\n\n<ref name=szu>Szu Ping Chan (editor) (2009). [https://books.google.it/books?id=eP30EnnP_5UC&pg=PA307 ''Anthem Guide to the Opera, Concert Halls and Classical Music Venues of Europe'']. London; New York: Anthem Press. {{isbn|9781843312727}}.</ref>\n\n}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Classical music in Latvia]]\n[[Category:Latvian orchestras]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 1926]]\n[[Category:National orchestras]]\n[[Category:Arts organizations established in 1926]]\n\n\n{{Orchestra-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Latvian symphony orchestra}}\n{{use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{use list-defined references|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use British English|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox orchestra\n| name                = Latvian National Symphony Orchestra\n| type                = \n| native_name         = {{nobreak|Latvijas Nacion\u0101lais simfoniskais or\u0137estris}}\n| native_name_lang    = lv\n| short_name          = \n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| alt                 = \n| former_name         = {{ubl|Latvian Radio Centre Orchestra|Latvian RSO}}\n| founded             = {{Start date|1926}}\n| disbanded           = \n| later_name          = \n| location            = [[Riga]], Latvia\n| concert_hall        = [[Large Guild, Riga|Great Guild Hall]], [[Riga]]\n| principal_conductor = [[Andris Poga]]\n| music_director      = \n| website             = {{url|lnso.lv}}\n}}\nThe '''Latvian National Symphony Orchestra''' (LNSO), {{lang-lv|'''Latvijas Nacion\u0101lais simfoniskais or\u0137estris'''|italic=no}}, is the principal [[symphony orchestra]] of [[Latvia]]. It was founded in 1926 as the '''Latvian Radio Centre Orchestra''' by the conductor [[Arv\u012bds P\u0101rups]], and was the first permanent orchestra in the country.{{r|grove}}  \n\nLNSO's mission is to offer the Latvian public musical performances of the whole orchestral repertoire from the classics to contemporary compositions and to introduce audiences abroad with [[Latvian Music|Latvian music]]. One of the LNSO's most important priorities is to attract young listeners with educational programmes.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.lnso.lv/par-lnso|title=PAR LNSO|website=LNSO|language=en|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\nThe LNSO is a six-time winner of the [http://www.muzikasbalva.lv/ Latvian Grand Music Award] (1993, 2009, 2012, 2013, 2016 and 2019).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.muzikasbalva.lv/laureati|title=Liel\u0101 m\u016bzikas balva - Laure\u0101ti|website=www.muzikasbalva.lv|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\nSince 2013 the music director of the LNSO is [[Andris Poga]]. Beginning with the 2021/2022 season Poga will take up the position of chief conductor of the [[Stavanger Symphony Orchestra]].\n\nThe LNSO\u2019s past guest conductors include Latvians [[Arv\u012bds Jansons]], [[Mariss Jansons]] and [[Andris Nelsons]], as well as [[Valery Gergiev]], [[Neeme J\u00e4rvi]], [[Paavo J\u00e4rvi]], [[Kirill Kondrashin]], [[Kurt Masur]], [[Krzysztof Penderecki]], [[Gennady Rozhdestvensky]], [[Yevgeny Svetlanov]], [[Yuri Simonov]], and many others.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.lnso.lv/par-lnso|title=PAR LNSO|website=LNSO|language=en|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\nIn recent years the LNSO has performed at the [[Philharmonie de Paris]] and the [[Th\u00e9\u00e2tre des Champs-\u00c9lys\u00e9es|Th\u00e9\u00e2tre des Champs Elys\u00e9es]], the [[Alte Oper]] [[Frankfurt]] and the Grand Th\u00e9\u00e2tre of [[Aix-en-Provence]] among many other European [[concert halls]]. The orchestra has participated in music festivals in [[France]], [[Germany]] and [[Switzerland]] as well as the [[Bratislava Music Festival]]. On its most recent tours the LNSO teamed up with Latvian violinist [[Baiba Skride]], cellist [[Alexander Kniazev|Alexander Knyazev]], pianists [[Nicholas Angelich]], [[Boris Berezovsky (pianist)|Boris Berezovsky]], [[Lukas Geniu\u0161as]] and [[Lucas Debargue]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.lnso.lv/par-lnso|title=PAR LNSO|website=LNSO|language=en|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to regular symphonic concerts, the orchestra also broadcasts and records. Its primary performance venue is the [[Large Guild, Riga|Great Guild Hall]] in [[Riga]].{{r|szu|page=307}}\n\n== Music Directors and Chief Conductors ==\n\n* [[Arv\u012bds P\u0101rups]] (1926\u20131928)\n* [[J\u0101nis Medi\u0146\u0161]] (1928\u20131944)\n* [[Dmitrijs Ku\u013ckovs]] (1945\u20131949)\n* [[Edgars Tons]] (1963\u20131966)\n* [[Leon\u012bds V\u012bgners]] (1949\u20131963, 1966\u20131974)\n* [[Vassily Sinaisky]] (1975\u20131987)\n* [[Paul M\u00e4gi]] (1990\u20131994)\n* [[Terje Mikkelsen]] (1997\u20132001)\n* [[Olari Elts]] (2001\u20132005)\n* [[Karel Mark Chichon]] (2009\u20132012)\n* [[Andris Poga]] (2013\u2013present)\n\n==Selected recordings==\n* [[Inessa Galante]] Debut recital Latvian National Symphony Orchestra Conducted by [[Alexander Vilumanis]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n\n<ref name=grove>Joachim Braun, Arnolds Kloti\u0146\u0161, Martin Boiko (2001). [http://www.oxfordmusiconline.com/grovemusic/view/10.1093/gmo/9781561592630.001.0001/omo-9781561592630-e-0000042158 Latvia]. ''Grove Music Online''. {{subscription 